8453 bool LValueExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryPreIncDec(const UnaryOperator *UO) {
8454  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && !Info.keepEvaluatingAfterFailure())
8455  return Error(UO);
8456 
8457  if (!this->Visit(UO->getSubExpr()))
8458  return false;
8459 
8460  return handleIncDec(
8461  this->Info, UO, Result, UO->getSubExpr()->getType(),
8462  UO->isIncrementOp(), nullptr);
8463 }
8464 
8465 bool LValueExprEvaluator::VisitCompoundAssignOperator(
8466  const CompoundAssignOperator *CAO) {
8467  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && !Info.keepEvaluatingAfterFailure())
8468  return Error(CAO);
8469 
8470  bool Success = true;
8471 
8472  // C++17 onwards require that we evaluate the RHS first.
8473  APValue RHS;
8474  if (!Evaluate(RHS, this->Info, CAO->getRHS())) {
8475  if (!Info.noteFailure())
8476  return false;
8477  Success = false;
8478  }
8479 
8480  // The overall lvalue result is the result of evaluating the LHS.
8481  if (!this->Visit(CAO->getLHS()) || !Success)
8482  return false;
8483 
8484  return handleCompoundAssignment(
8485  this->Info, CAO,
8486  Result, CAO->getLHS()->getType(), CAO->getComputationLHSType(),
8487  CAO->getOpForCompoundAssignment(CAO->getOpcode()), RHS);
8488 }
8489 
8490 bool LValueExprEvaluator::VisitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *E) {
8491  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && !Info.keepEvaluatingAfterFailure())
8492  return Error(E);
8493 
8494  bool Success = true;
8495 
8496  // C++17 onwards require that we evaluate the RHS first.
8497  APValue NewVal;
8498  if (!Evaluate(NewVal, this->Info, E->getRHS())) {
8499  if (!Info.noteFailure())
8500  return false;
8501  Success = false;
8502  }
8503 
8504  if (!this->Visit(E->getLHS()) || !Success)
8505  return false;
8506 
8507  if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 &&
8508  !HandleUnionActiveMemberChange(Info, E->getLHS(), Result))
8509  return false;
8510 
8511  return handleAssignment(this->Info, E, Result, E->getLHS()->getType(),
8512  NewVal);
8513 }

8515 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8516 // Pointer Evaluation
8517 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8518 
8519 /// Attempts to compute the number of bytes available at the pointer
8520 /// returned by a function with the alloc_size attribute. Returns true if we
8521 /// were successful. Places an unsigned number into `Result`.
8522 ///
8523 /// This expects the given CallExpr to be a call to a function with an
8524 /// alloc_size attribute.
8525 static bool getBytesReturnedByAllocSizeCall(const ASTContext &Ctx,
8526  const CallExpr *Call,
8527  llvm::APInt &Result) {
8528  const AllocSizeAttr *AllocSize = getAllocSizeAttr(Call);
8529 
8530  assert(AllocSize && AllocSize->getElemSizeParam().isValid());
8531  unsigned SizeArgNo = AllocSize->getElemSizeParam().getASTIndex();
8532  unsigned BitsInSizeT = Ctx.getTypeSize(Ctx.getSizeType());
8533  if (Call->getNumArgs() <= SizeArgNo)
8534  return false;
8535 
8536  auto EvaluateAsSizeT = [&](const Expr *E, APSInt &Into) {
8537  Expr::EvalResult ExprResult;
8538  if (!E->EvaluateAsInt(ExprResult, Ctx, Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects))
8539  return false;
8540  Into = ExprResult.Val.getInt();
8541  if (Into.isNegative() || !Into.isIntN(BitsInSizeT))
8542  return false;
8543  Into = Into.zextOrSelf(BitsInSizeT);
8544  return true;
8545  };
8546 
8547  APSInt SizeOfElem;
8548  if (!EvaluateAsSizeT(Call->getArg(SizeArgNo), SizeOfElem))
8549  return false;
8550 
8551  if (!AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().isValid()) {
8552  Result = std::move(SizeOfElem);
8553  return true;
8554  }
8555 
8556  APSInt NumberOfElems;
8557  unsigned NumArgNo = AllocSize->getNumElemsParam().getASTIndex();
8558  if (!EvaluateAsSizeT(Call->getArg(NumArgNo), NumberOfElems))
8559  return false;
8560 
8561  bool Overflow;
8562  llvm::APInt BytesAvailable = SizeOfElem.umul_ov(NumberOfElems, Overflow);
8563  if (Overflow)
8564  return false;
8565 
8566  Result = std::move(BytesAvailable);
8567  return true;
8568 }
8569 
8570 /// Convenience function. LVal's base must be a call to an alloc_size
8571 /// function.
8572 static bool getBytesReturnedByAllocSizeCall(const ASTContext &Ctx,
8573  const LValue &LVal,
8574  llvm::APInt &Result) {
8575  assert(isBaseAnAllocSizeCall(LVal.getLValueBase()) &&
8576  "Can't get the size of a non alloc_size function");
8577  const auto *Base = LVal.getLValueBase().get<const Expr *>();
8578  const CallExpr *CE = tryUnwrapAllocSizeCall(Base);
8579  return getBytesReturnedByAllocSizeCall(Ctx, CE, Result);
8580 }
8581 
8582 /// Attempts to evaluate the given LValueBase as the result of a call to
8583 /// a function with the alloc_size attribute. If it was possible to do so, this
8584 /// function will return true, make Result's Base point to said function call,
8585 /// and mark Result's Base as invalid.
8586 static bool evaluateLValueAsAllocSize(EvalInfo &Info, APValue::LValueBase Base,
8587  LValue &Result) {
8588  if (Base.isNull())
8589  return false;
8590 
8591  // Because we do no form of static analysis, we only support const variables.
8592  //
8593  // Additionally, we can't support parameters, nor can we support static
8594  // variables (in the latter case, use-before-assign isn't UB; in the former,
8595  // we have no clue what they'll be assigned to).
8596  const auto *VD =
8597  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(Base.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl *>());
8598  if (!VD || !VD->isLocalVarDecl() || !VD->getType().isConstQualified())
8599  return false;
8600 
8601  const Expr *Init = VD->getAnyInitializer();
8602  if (!Init)
8603  return false;
8604 
8605  const Expr *E = Init->IgnoreParens();
8606  if (!tryUnwrapAllocSizeCall(E))
8607  return false;
8608 
8609  // Store E instead of E unwrapped so that the type of the LValue's base is
8610  // what the user wanted.
8611  Result.setInvalid(E);
8612 
8613  QualType Pointee = E->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
8614  Result.addUnsizedArray(Info, E, Pointee);
8615  return true;
8616 }
8617 
8618 namespace {
8619 class PointerExprEvaluator
8620  : public ExprEvaluatorBase<PointerExprEvaluator> {
8621  LValue &Result;
8622  bool InvalidBaseOK;
8623 
8624  bool Success(const Expr *E) {
8625  Result.set(E);
8626  return true;
8627  }
8628 
8629  bool evaluateLValue(const Expr *E, LValue &Result) {
8630  return EvaluateLValue(E, Result, Info, InvalidBaseOK);
8631  }
8632 
8633  bool evaluatePointer(const Expr *E, LValue &Result) {
8634  return EvaluatePointer(E, Result, Info, InvalidBaseOK);
8635  }
8636 
8637  bool visitNonBuiltinCallExpr(const CallExpr *E);
8638 public:
8639 
8640  PointerExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &info, LValue &Result, bool InvalidBaseOK)
8641  : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(info), Result(Result),
8642  InvalidBaseOK(InvalidBaseOK) {}
8643 
8644  bool Success(const APValue &V, const Expr *E) {
8645  Result.setFrom(Info.Ctx, V);
8646  return true;
8647  }
8648  bool ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) {
8649  Result.setNull(Info.Ctx, E->getType());
8650  return true;
8651  }
8652 
8653  bool VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E);
8654  bool VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr* E);
8655  bool VisitUnaryAddrOf(const UnaryOperator *E);
8656  bool VisitObjCStringLiteral(const ObjCStringLiteral *E)
8657  { return Success(E); }
8658  bool VisitObjCBoxedExpr(const ObjCBoxedExpr *E) {
8659  if (E->isExpressibleAsConstantInitializer())
8660  return Success(E);
8661  if (Info.noteFailure())
8662  EvaluateIgnoredValue(Info, E->getSubExpr());
8663  return Error(E);
8664  }
8665  bool VisitAddrLabelExpr(const AddrLabelExpr *E)
8666  { return Success(E); }
8667  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E);
8668  bool VisitBuiltinCallExpr(const CallExpr *E, unsigned BuiltinOp);
8669  bool VisitBlockExpr(const BlockExpr *E) {
8670  if (!E->getBlockDecl()->hasCaptures())
8671  return Success(E);
8672  return Error(E);
8673  }
8674  bool VisitCXXThisExpr(const CXXThisExpr *E) {
8675  // Can't look at 'this' when checking a potential constant expression.
8676  if (Info.checkingPotentialConstantExpression())
8677  return false;
8678  if (!Info.CurrentCall->This) {
8679  if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
8680  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_this) << E->isImplicit();
8681  else
8682  Info.FFDiag(E);
8683  return false;
8684  }
8685  Result = *Info.CurrentCall->This;
8686  // If we are inside a lambda's call operator, the 'this' expression refers
8687  // to the enclosing '*this' object (either by value or reference) which is
8688  // either copied into the closure object's field that represents the '*this'
8689  // or refers to '*this'.
8690  if (isLambdaCallOperator(Info.CurrentCall->Callee)) {
8691  // Ensure we actually have captured 'this'. (an error will have
8692  // been previously reported if not).
8693  if (!Info.CurrentCall->LambdaThisCaptureField)
8694  return false;
8695 
8696  // Update 'Result' to refer to the data member/field of the closure object
8697  // that represents the '*this' capture.
8698  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, E, Result,
8699  Info.CurrentCall->LambdaThisCaptureField))
8700  return false;
8701  // If we captured '*this' by reference, replace the field with its referent.
8702  if (Info.CurrentCall->LambdaThisCaptureField->getType()
8703  ->isPointerType()) {
8704  APValue RVal;
8705  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, E->getType(), Result,
8706  RVal))
8707  return false;
8708 
8709  Result.setFrom(Info.Ctx, RVal);
8710  }
8711  }
8712  return true;
8713  }
8714 
8715  bool VisitCXXNewExpr(const CXXNewExpr *E);
8716 
8717  bool VisitSourceLocExpr(const SourceLocExpr *E) {
8718  assert(E->isStringType() && "SourceLocExpr isn't a pointer type?");
8719  APValue LValResult = E->EvaluateInContext(
8720  Info.Ctx, Info.CurrentCall->CurSourceLocExprScope.getDefaultExpr());
8721  Result.setFrom(Info.Ctx, LValResult);
8722  return true;
8723  }
8724 
8725  bool VisitSYCLUniqueStableNameExpr(const SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr *E) {
8726  std::string ResultStr = E->ComputeName(Info.Ctx);
8727 
8728  QualType CharTy = Info.Ctx.CharTy.withConst();
8729  APInt Size(Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(Info.Ctx.getSizeType()),
8730  ResultStr.size() + 1);
8731  QualType ArrayTy = Info.Ctx.getConstantArrayType(CharTy, Size, nullptr,
8732  ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8733 
8734  StringLiteral *SL =
8735  StringLiteral::Create(Info.Ctx, ResultStr, StringLiteral::Ascii,
8736  /*Pascal*/ false, ArrayTy, E->getLocation());
8737 
8738  evaluateLValue(SL, Result);
8739  Result.addArray(Info, E, cast<ConstantArrayType>(ArrayTy));
8740  return true;
8741  }
8742 
8743  bool VisitSYCLUniqueStableIdExpr(const SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr *E) {
8744  std::string ResultStr = E->ComputeName(Info.Ctx);
8745 
8746  QualType CharTy = Info.Ctx.CharTy.withConst();
8747  APInt Size(Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(Info.Ctx.getSizeType()),
8748  ResultStr.size() + 1);
8749  QualType ArrayTy = Info.Ctx.getConstantArrayType(CharTy, Size, nullptr,
8750  ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8751 
8752  StringLiteral *SL =
8753  StringLiteral::Create(Info.Ctx, ResultStr, StringLiteral::Ascii,
8754  /*Pascal*/ false, ArrayTy, E->getLocation());
8755 
8756  evaluateLValue(SL, Result);
8757  Result.addArray(Info, E, cast<ConstantArrayType>(ArrayTy));
8758  return true;
8759  }

8761  // FIXME: Missing: @protocol, @selector
8762 };
8763 } // end anonymous namespace

8765 static bool EvaluatePointer(const Expr* E, LValue& Result, EvalInfo &Info,
8766  bool InvalidBaseOK) {
8767  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
8768  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->hasPointerRepresentation());
8769  return PointerExprEvaluator(Info, Result, InvalidBaseOK).Visit(E);
8770 }
8771 
8772 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
8773  if (E->getOpcode() != BO_Add &&
8774  E->getOpcode() != BO_Sub)
8775  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
8776 
8777  const Expr *PExp = E->getLHS();
8778  const Expr *IExp = E->getRHS();
8779  if (IExp->getType()->isPointerType())
8780  std::swap(PExp, IExp);
8781 
8782  bool EvalPtrOK = evaluatePointer(PExp, Result);
8783  if (!EvalPtrOK && !Info.noteFailure())
8784  return false;
8785 
8786  llvm::APSInt Offset;
8787  if (!EvaluateInteger(IExp, Offset, Info) || !EvalPtrOK)
8788  return false;
8789 
8790  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Sub)
8791  negateAsSigned(Offset);
8792 
8793  QualType Pointee = PExp->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
8794  return HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Result, Pointee, Offset);
8795 }
8796 
8797 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryAddrOf(const UnaryOperator *E) {
8798  return evaluateLValue(E->getSubExpr(), Result);
8799 }
8800 
8801 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
8802  const Expr *SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
8803 
8804  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
8805  default:
8806  break;
8807  case CK_BitCast:
8808  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
8809  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
8810  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
8811  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
8812  if (!Visit(SubExpr))
8813  return false;
8814  // Bitcasts to cv void* are static_casts, not reinterpret_casts, so are
8815  // permitted in constant expressions in C++11. Bitcasts from cv void* are
8816  // also static_casts, but we disallow them as a resolution to DR1312.
8817  if (!E->getType()->isVoidPointerType()) {
8818  if (!Result.InvalidBase && !Result.Designator.Invalid &&
8819  !Result.IsNullPtr &&
8820  Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Result.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx),
8821  E->getType()->getPointeeType()) &&
8822  Info.getStdAllocatorCaller("allocate")) {
8823  // Inside a call to std::allocator::allocate and friends, we permit
8824  // casting from void* back to cv1 T* for a pointer that points to a
8825  // cv2 T.
8826  } else {
8827  Result.Designator.setInvalid();
8828  if (SubExpr->getType()->isVoidPointerType())
8829  CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_cast)
8830  << 3 << SubExpr->getType();
8831  else
8832  CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_cast) << 2;
8833  }
8834  }
8835  if (E->getCastKind() == CK_AddressSpaceConversion && Result.IsNullPtr)
8836  ZeroInitialization(E);
8837  return true;
8838 
8839  case CK_DerivedToBase:
8840  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
8841  if (!evaluatePointer(E->getSubExpr(), Result))
8842  return false;
8843  if (!Result.Base && Result.Offset.isZero())
8844  return true;
8845 
8846  // Now figure out the necessary offset to add to the base LV to get from
8847  // the derived class to the base class.
8848  return HandleLValueBasePath(Info, E, E->getSubExpr()->getType()->
8849  castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType(),
8850  Result);
8851 
8852  case CK_BaseToDerived:
8853  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
8854  return false;
8855  if (!Result.Base && Result.Offset.isZero())
8856  return true;
8857  return HandleBaseToDerivedCast(Info, E, Result);
8858 
8859  case CK_Dynamic:
8860  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
8861  return false;
8862  return HandleDynamicCast(Info, cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E), Result);
8863 
8864  case CK_NullToPointer:
8865  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
8866  return ZeroInitialization(E);
8867 
8868  case CK_IntegralToPointer: {
8869  CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_cast) << 2;
8870 
8871  APValue Value;
8872  if (!EvaluateIntegerOrLValue(SubExpr, Value, Info))
8873  break;
8874 
8875  if (Value.isInt()) {
8876  unsigned Size = Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(E->getType());
8877  uint64_t N = Value.getInt().extOrTrunc(Size).getZExtValue();
8878  Result.Base = (Expr*)nullptr;
8879  Result.InvalidBase = false;
8880  Result.Offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(N);
8881  Result.Designator.setInvalid();
8882  Result.IsNullPtr = false;
8883  return true;
8884  } else {
8885  // Cast is of an lvalue, no need to change value.
8886  Result.setFrom(Info.Ctx, Value);
8887  return true;
8888  }
8889  }
8890 
8891  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay: {
8892  if (SubExpr->isGLValue()) {
8893  if (!evaluateLValue(SubExpr, Result))
8894  return false;
8895  } else {
8896  APValue &Value = Info.CurrentCall->createTemporary(
8897  SubExpr, SubExpr->getType(), ScopeKind::FullExpression, Result);
8898  if (!EvaluateInPlace(Value, Info, Result, SubExpr))
8899  return false;
8900  }
8901  // The result is a pointer to the first element of the array.
8902  auto *AT = Info.Ctx.getAsArrayType(SubExpr->getType());
8903  if (auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
8904  Result.addArray(Info, E, CAT);
8905  else
8906  Result.addUnsizedArray(Info, E, AT->getElementType());
8907  return true;
8908  }
8909 
8910  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
8911  return evaluateLValue(SubExpr, Result);
8912 
8913  case CK_LValueToRValue: {
8914  LValue LVal;
8915  if (!evaluateLValue(E->getSubExpr(), LVal))
8916  return false;
8917 
8918  APValue RVal;
8919  // Note, we use the subexpression's type in order to retain cv-qualifiers.
8920  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, E->getSubExpr()->getType(),
8921  LVal, RVal))
8922  return InvalidBaseOK &&
8923  evaluateLValueAsAllocSize(Info, LVal.Base, Result);
8924  return Success(RVal, E);
8925  }
8926  }
8927 
8928  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
8929 }
8930 
8931 static CharUnits GetAlignOfType(EvalInfo &Info, QualType T,
8932  UnaryExprOrTypeTrait ExprKind) {
8933  // C++ [expr.alignof]p3:
8934  // When alignof is applied to a reference type, the result is the
8935  // alignment of the referenced type.
8936  if (const ReferenceType *Ref = T->getAs<ReferenceType>())
8937  T = Ref->getPointeeType();
8938 
8939  if (T.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned())
8940  return CharUnits::One();
8941 
8942  const bool AlignOfReturnsPreferred =
8943  Info.Ctx.getLangOpts().getClangABICompat() <= LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver7;
8944 
8945  // __alignof is defined to return the preferred alignment.
8946  // Before 8, clang returned the preferred alignment for alignof and _Alignof
8947  // as well.
8948  if (ExprKind == UETT_PreferredAlignOf || AlignOfReturnsPreferred)
8949  return Info.Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(
8950  Info.Ctx.getPreferredTypeAlign(T.getTypePtr()));
8951  // alignof and _Alignof are defined to return the ABI alignment.
8952  else if (ExprKind == UETT_AlignOf)
8953  return Info.Ctx.getTypeAlignInChars(T.getTypePtr());
8954  else
8955  llvm_unreachable("GetAlignOfType on a non-alignment ExprKind");
8956 }
8957 
8958 static CharUnits GetAlignOfExpr(EvalInfo &Info, const Expr *E,
8959  UnaryExprOrTypeTrait ExprKind) {
8960  E = E->IgnoreParens();
8961 
8962  // The kinds of expressions that we have special-case logic here for
8963  // should be kept up to date with the special checks for those
8964  // expressions in Sema.
8965 
8966  // alignof decl is always accepted, even if it doesn't make sense: we default
8967  // to 1 in those cases.
8968  if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
8969  return Info.Ctx.getDeclAlign(DRE->getDecl(),
8970  /*RefAsPointee*/true);
8971 
8972  if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
8973  return Info.Ctx.getDeclAlign(ME->getMemberDecl(),
8974  /*RefAsPointee*/true);
8975 
8976  return GetAlignOfType(Info, E->getType(), ExprKind);
8977 }
8978 
8979 static CharUnits getBaseAlignment(EvalInfo &Info, const LValue &Value) {
8980  if (const auto *VD = Value.Base.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl *>())
8981  return Info.Ctx.getDeclAlign(VD);
8982  if (const auto *E = Value.Base.dyn_cast<const Expr *>())
8983  return GetAlignOfExpr(Info, E, UETT_AlignOf);
8984  return GetAlignOfType(Info, Value.Base.getTypeInfoType(), UETT_AlignOf);
8985 }
8986 
8987 /// Evaluate the value of the alignment argument to __builtin_align_{up,down},
8988 /// __builtin_is_aligned and __builtin_assume_aligned.
8989 static bool getAlignmentArgument(const Expr *E, QualType ForType,
8990  EvalInfo &Info, APSInt &Alignment) {
8991  if (!EvaluateInteger(E, Alignment, Info))
8992  return false;
8993  if (Alignment < 0 || !Alignment.isPowerOf2()) {
8994  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_alignment) << Alignment;
8995  return false;
8996  }
8997  unsigned SrcWidth = Info.Ctx.getIntWidth(ForType);
8998  APSInt MaxValue(APInt::getOneBitSet(SrcWidth, SrcWidth - 1));
8999  if (APSInt::compareValues(Alignment, MaxValue) > 0) {
9000  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_alignment_too_big)
9001  << MaxValue << ForType << Alignment;
9002  return false;
9003  }
9004  // Ensure both alignment and source value have the same bit width so that we
9005  // don't assert when computing the resulting value.
9006  APSInt ExtAlignment =
9007  APSInt(Alignment.zextOrTrunc(SrcWidth), /*isUnsigned=*/true);
9008  assert(APSInt::compareValues(Alignment, ExtAlignment) == 0 &&
9009  "Alignment should not be changed by ext/trunc");
9010  Alignment = ExtAlignment;
9011  assert(Alignment.getBitWidth() == SrcWidth);
9012  return true;
9013 }
9014 
9015 // To be clear: this happily visits unsupported builtins. Better name welcomed.
9016 bool PointerExprEvaluator::visitNonBuiltinCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
9017  if (ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCallExpr(E))
9018  return true;
9019 
9020  if (!(InvalidBaseOK && getAllocSizeAttr(E)))
9021  return false;
9022 
9023  Result.setInvalid(E);
9024  QualType PointeeTy = E->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9025  Result.addUnsizedArray(Info, E, PointeeTy);
9026  return true;
9027 }
9028 
9029 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
9030  if (IsConstantCall(E))
9031  return Success(E);
9032 
9033  if (unsigned BuiltinOp = E->getBuiltinCallee())
9034  return VisitBuiltinCallExpr(E, BuiltinOp);
9035 
9036  return visitNonBuiltinCallExpr(E);
9037 }
9038 
9039 // Determine if T is a character type for which we guarantee that
9040 // sizeof(T) == 1.
9041 static bool isOneByteCharacterType(QualType T) {
9042  return T->isCharType() || T->isChar8Type();
9043 }
9044 
9045 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitBuiltinCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
9046  unsigned BuiltinOp) {
9047  switch (BuiltinOp) {
9048  case Builtin::BI__builtin_addressof:
9049  return evaluateLValue(E->getArg(0), Result);
9050  case Builtin::BI__builtin_assume_aligned: {
9051  // We need to be very careful here because: if the pointer does not have the
9052  // asserted alignment, then the behavior is undefined, and undefined
9053  // behavior is non-constant.
9054  if (!evaluatePointer(E->getArg(0), Result))
9055  return false;
9056 
9057  LValue OffsetResult(Result);
9058  APSInt Alignment;
9059  if (!getAlignmentArgument(E->getArg(1), E->getArg(0)->getType(), Info,
9060  Alignment))
9061  return false;
9062  CharUnits Align = CharUnits::fromQuantity(Alignment.getZExtValue());
9063 
9064  if (E->getNumArgs() > 2) {
9065  APSInt Offset;
9066  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(2), Offset, Info))
9067  return false;
9068 
9069  int64_t AdditionalOffset = -Offset.getZExtValue();
9070  OffsetResult.Offset += CharUnits::fromQuantity(AdditionalOffset);
9071  }
9072 
9073  // If there is a base object, then it must have the correct alignment.
9074  if (OffsetResult.Base) {
9075  CharUnits BaseAlignment = getBaseAlignment(Info, OffsetResult);
9076 
9077  if (BaseAlignment < Align) {
9078  Result.Designator.setInvalid();
9079  // FIXME: Add support to Diagnostic for long / long long.
9080  CCEDiag(E->getArg(0),
9081  diag::note_constexpr_baa_insufficient_alignment) << 0
9082  << (unsigned)BaseAlignment.getQuantity()
9083  << (unsigned)Align.getQuantity();
9084  return false;
9085  }
9086  }
9087 
9088  // The offset must also have the correct alignment.
9089  if (OffsetResult.Offset.alignTo(Align) != OffsetResult.Offset) {
9090  Result.Designator.setInvalid();
9091 
9092  (OffsetResult.Base
9093  ? CCEDiag(E->getArg(0),
9094  diag::note_constexpr_baa_insufficient_alignment) << 1
9095  : CCEDiag(E->getArg(0),
9096  diag::note_constexpr_baa_value_insufficient_alignment))
9097  << (int)OffsetResult.Offset.getQuantity()
9098  << (unsigned)Align.getQuantity();
9099  return false;
9100  }
9101 
9102  return true;
9103  }
9104  case Builtin::BI__builtin_align_up:
9105  case Builtin::BI__builtin_align_down: {
9106  if (!evaluatePointer(E->getArg(0), Result))
9107  return false;
9108  APSInt Alignment;
9109  if (!getAlignmentArgument(E->getArg(1), E->getArg(0)->getType(), Info,
9110  Alignment))
9111  return false;
9112  CharUnits BaseAlignment = getBaseAlignment(Info, Result);
9113  CharUnits PtrAlign = BaseAlignment.alignmentAtOffset(Result.Offset);
9114  // For align_up/align_down, we can return the same value if the alignment
9115  // is known to be greater or equal to the requested value.
9116  if (PtrAlign.getQuantity() >= Alignment)
9117  return true;
9118 
9119  // The alignment could be greater than the minimum at run-time, so we cannot
9120  // infer much about the resulting pointer value. One case is possible:
9121  // For `_Alignas(32) char buf[N]; __builtin_align_down(&buf[idx], 32)` we
9122  // can infer the correct index if the requested alignment is smaller than
9123  // the base alignment so we can perform the computation on the offset.
9124  if (BaseAlignment.getQuantity() >= Alignment) {
9125  assert(Alignment.getBitWidth() <= 64 &&
9126  "Cannot handle > 64-bit address-space");
9127  uint64_t Alignment64 = Alignment.getZExtValue();
9128  CharUnits NewOffset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
9129  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_align_down
9130  ? llvm::alignDown(Result.Offset.getQuantity(), Alignment64)
9131  : llvm::alignTo(Result.Offset.getQuantity(), Alignment64));
9132  Result.adjustOffset(NewOffset - Result.Offset);
9133  // TODO: diagnose out-of-bounds values/only allow for arrays?
9134  return true;
9135  }
9136  // Otherwise, we cannot constant-evaluate the result.
9137  Info.FFDiag(E->getArg(0), diag::note_constexpr_alignment_adjust)
9138  << Alignment;
9139  return false;
9140  }
9141  case Builtin::BI__builtin_operator_new:
9142  return HandleOperatorNewCall(Info, E, Result);
9143  case Builtin::BI__builtin_launder:
9144  return evaluatePointer(E->getArg(0), Result);
9145  case Builtin::BIstrchr:
9146  case Builtin::BIwcschr:
9147  case Builtin::BImemchr:
9148  case Builtin::BIwmemchr:
9149  if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
9150  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_function)
9151  << /*isConstexpr*/0 << /*isConstructor*/0
9152  << (std::string("'") + Info.Ctx.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinOp) + "'");
9153  else
9154  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_invalid_subexpr_in_const_expr);
9155  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9156  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strchr:
9157  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wcschr:
9158  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memchr:
9159  case Builtin::BI__builtin_char_memchr:
9160  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemchr: {
9161  if (!Visit(E->getArg(0)))
9162  return false;
9163  APSInt Desired;
9164  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(1), Desired, Info))
9165  return false;
9166  uint64_t MaxLength = uint64_t(-1);
9167  if (BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIstrchr &&
9168  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIwcschr &&
9169  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_strchr &&
9170  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_wcschr) {
9171  APSInt N;
9172  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(2), N, Info))
9173  return false;
9174  MaxLength = N.getExtValue();
9175  }
9176  // We cannot find the value if there are no candidates to match against.
9177  if (MaxLength == 0u)
9178  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9179  if (!Result.checkNullPointerForFoldAccess(Info, E, AK_Read) ||
9180  Result.Designator.Invalid)
9181  return false;
9182  QualType CharTy = Result.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx);
9183  bool IsRawByte = BuiltinOp == Builtin::BImemchr ||
9184  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_memchr;
9185  assert(IsRawByte ||
9186  Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
9187  CharTy, E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType()));
9188  // Pointers to const void may point to objects of incomplete type.
9189  if (IsRawByte && CharTy->isIncompleteType()) {
9190  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_ltor_incomplete_type) << CharTy;
9191  return false;
9192  }
9193  // Give up on byte-oriented matching against multibyte elements.
9194  // FIXME: We can compare the bytes in the correct order.
9195  if (IsRawByte && !isOneByteCharacterType(CharTy)) {
9196  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memchr_unsupported)
9197  << (std::string("'") + Info.Ctx.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinOp) + "'")
9198  << CharTy;
9199  return false;
9200  }
9201  // Figure out what value we're actually looking for (after converting to
9202  // the corresponding unsigned type if necessary).
9203  uint64_t DesiredVal;
9204  bool StopAtNull = false;
9205  switch (BuiltinOp) {
9206  case Builtin::BIstrchr:
9207  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strchr:
9208  // strchr compares directly to the passed integer, and therefore
9209  // always fails if given an int that is not a char.
9210  if (!APSInt::isSameValue(HandleIntToIntCast(Info, E, CharTy,
9211  E->getArg(1)->getType(),
9212  Desired),
9213  Desired))
9214  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9215  StopAtNull = true;
9216  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9217  case Builtin::BImemchr:
9218  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memchr:
9219  case Builtin::BI__builtin_char_memchr:
9220  // memchr compares by converting both sides to unsigned char. That's also
9221  // correct for strchr if we get this far (to cope with plain char being
9222  // unsigned in the strchr case).
9223  DesiredVal = Desired.trunc(Info.Ctx.getCharWidth()).getZExtValue();
9224  break;
9225 
9226  case Builtin::BIwcschr:
9227  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wcschr:
9228  StopAtNull = true;
9229  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9230  case Builtin::BIwmemchr:
9231  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemchr:
9232  // wcschr and wmemchr are given a wchar_t to look for. Just use it.
9233  DesiredVal = Desired.getZExtValue();
9234  break;
9235  }
9236 
9237  for (; MaxLength; --MaxLength) {
9238  APValue Char;
9239  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, CharTy, Result, Char) ||
9240  !Char.isInt())
9241  return false;
9242  if (Char.getInt().getZExtValue() == DesiredVal)
9243  return true;
9244  if (StopAtNull && !Char.getInt())
9245  break;
9246  if (!HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Result, CharTy, 1))
9247  return false;
9248  }
9249  // Not found: return nullptr.
9250  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9251  }
9252 
9253  case Builtin::BImemcpy:
9254  case Builtin::BImemmove:
9255  case Builtin::BIwmemcpy:
9256  case Builtin::BIwmemmove:
9257  if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
9258  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_function)
9259  << /*isConstexpr*/0 << /*isConstructor*/0
9260  << (std::string("'") + Info.Ctx.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinOp) + "'");
9261  else
9262  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_invalid_subexpr_in_const_expr);
9263  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9264  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memcpy:
9265  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memmove:
9266  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcpy:
9267  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemmove: {
9268  bool WChar = BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwmemcpy ||
9269  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwmemmove ||
9270  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcpy ||
9271  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemmove;
9272  bool Move = BuiltinOp == Builtin::BImemmove ||
9273  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwmemmove ||
9274  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_memmove ||
9275  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemmove;
9276 
9277  // The result of mem* is the first argument.
9278  if (!Visit(E->getArg(0)))
9279  return false;
9280  LValue Dest = Result;
9281 
9282  LValue Src;
9283  if (!EvaluatePointer(E->getArg(1), Src, Info))
9284  return false;
9285 
9286  APSInt N;
9287  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(2), N, Info))
9288  return false;
9289  assert(!N.isSigned() && "memcpy and friends take an unsigned size");
9290 
9291  // If the size is zero, we treat this as always being a valid no-op.
9292  // (Even if one of the src and dest pointers is null.)
9293  if (!N)
9294  return true;
9295 
9296  // Otherwise, if either of the operands is null, we can't proceed. Don't
9297  // try to determine the type of the copied objects, because there aren't
9298  // any.
9299  if (!Src.Base || !Dest.Base) {
9300  APValue Val;
9301  (!Src.Base ? Src : Dest).moveInto(Val);
9302  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_null)
9303  << Move << WChar << !!Src.Base
9304  << Val.getAsString(Info.Ctx, E->getArg(0)->getType());
9305  return false;
9306  }
9307  if (Src.Designator.Invalid || Dest.Designator.Invalid)
9308  return false;
9309 
9310  // We require that Src and Dest are both pointers to arrays of
9311  // trivially-copyable type. (For the wide version, the designator will be
9312  // invalid if the designated object is not a wchar_t.)
9313  QualType T = Dest.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx);
9314  QualType SrcT = Src.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx);
9315  if (!Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T, SrcT)) {
9316  // FIXME: Consider using our bit_cast implementation to support this.
9317  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_type_pun) << Move << SrcT << T;
9318  return false;
9319  }
9320  if (T->isIncompleteType()) {
9321  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_incomplete_type) << Move << T;
9322  return false;
9323  }
9324  if (!T.isTriviallyCopyableType(Info.Ctx)) {
9325  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_nontrivial) << Move << T;
9326  return false;
9327  }
9328 
9329  // Figure out how many T's we're copying.
9330  uint64_t TSize = Info.Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(T).getQuantity();
9331  if (!WChar) {
9332  uint64_t Remainder;
9333  llvm::APInt OrigN = N;
9334  llvm::APInt::udivrem(OrigN, TSize, N, Remainder);
9335  if (Remainder) {
9336  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_unsupported)
9337  << Move << WChar << 0 << T << toString(OrigN, 10, /*Signed*/false)
9338  << (unsigned)TSize;
9339  return false;
9340  }
9341  }
9342 
9343  // Check that the copying will remain within the arrays, just so that we
9344  // can give a more meaningful diagnostic. This implicitly also checks that
9345  // N fits into 64 bits.
9346  uint64_t RemainingSrcSize = Src.Designator.validIndexAdjustments().second;
9347  uint64_t RemainingDestSize = Dest.Designator.validIndexAdjustments().second;
9348  if (N.ugt(RemainingSrcSize) || N.ugt(RemainingDestSize)) {
9349  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_unsupported)
9350  << Move << WChar << (N.ugt(RemainingSrcSize) ? 1 : 2) << T
9351  << toString(N, 10, /*Signed*/false);
9352  return false;
9353  }
9354  uint64_t NElems = N.getZExtValue();
9355  uint64_t NBytes = NElems * TSize;
9356 
9357  // Check for overlap.
9358  int Direction = 1;
9359  if (HasSameBase(Src, Dest)) {
9360  uint64_t SrcOffset = Src.getLValueOffset().getQuantity();
9361  uint64_t DestOffset = Dest.getLValueOffset().getQuantity();
9362  if (DestOffset >= SrcOffset && DestOffset - SrcOffset < NBytes) {
9363  // Dest is inside the source region.
9364  if (!Move) {
9365  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_overlap) << WChar;
9366  return false;
9367  }
9368  // For memmove and friends, copy backwards.
9369  if (!HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Src, T, NElems - 1) ||
9370  !HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Dest, T, NElems - 1))
9371  return false;
9372  Direction = -1;
9373  } else if (!Move && SrcOffset >= DestOffset &&
9374  SrcOffset - DestOffset < NBytes) {
9375  // Src is inside the destination region for memcpy: invalid.
9376  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcpy_overlap) << WChar;
9377  return false;
9378  }
9379  }
9380 
9381  while (true) {
9382  APValue Val;
9383  // FIXME: Set WantObjectRepresentation to true if we're copying a
9384  // char-like type?
9385  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, T, Src, Val) ||
9386  !handleAssignment(Info, E, Dest, T, Val))
9387  return false;
9388  // Do not iterate past the last element; if we're copying backwards, that
9389  // might take us off the start of the array.
9390  if (--NElems == 0)
9391  return true;
9392  if (!HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Src, T, Direction) ||
9393  !HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Dest, T, Direction))
9394  return false;
9395  }
9396  }
9397 
9398  default:
9399  break;
9400  }
9401 
9402  return visitNonBuiltinCallExpr(E);
9403 }
9404 
9405 static bool EvaluateArrayNewInitList(EvalInfo &Info, LValue &This,
9406  APValue &Result, const InitListExpr *ILE,
9407  QualType AllocType);
9408 static bool EvaluateArrayNewConstructExpr(EvalInfo &Info, LValue &This,
9409  APValue &Result,
9410  const CXXConstructExpr *CCE,
9411  QualType AllocType);
9412 
9413 bool PointerExprEvaluator::VisitCXXNewExpr(const CXXNewExpr *E) {
9414  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
9415  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_new);
9416 
9417  // We cannot speculatively evaluate a delete expression.
9418  if (Info.SpeculativeEvaluationDepth)
9419  return false;
9420 
9421  FunctionDecl *OperatorNew = E->getOperatorNew();
9422 
9423  bool IsNothrow = false;
9424  bool IsPlacement = false;
9425  if (OperatorNew->isReservedGlobalPlacementOperator() &&
9426  Info.CurrentCall->isStdFunction() && !E->isArray()) {
9427  // FIXME Support array placement new.
9428  assert(E->getNumPlacementArgs() == 1);
9429  if (!EvaluatePointer(E->getPlacementArg(0), Result, Info))
9430  return false;
9431  if (Result.Designator.Invalid)
9432  return false;
9433  IsPlacement = true;
9434  } else if (!OperatorNew->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
9435  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_new_non_replaceable)
9436  << isa<CXXMethodDecl>(OperatorNew) << OperatorNew;
9437  return false;
9438  } else if (E->getNumPlacementArgs()) {
9439  // The only new-placement list we support is of the form (std::nothrow).
9440  //
9441  // FIXME: There is no restriction on this, but it's not clear that any
9442  // other form makes any sense. We get here for cases such as:
9443  //
9444  // new (std::align_val_t{N}) X(int)
9445  //
9446  // (which should presumably be valid only if N is a multiple of
9447  // alignof(int), and in any case can't be deallocated unless N is
9448  // alignof(X) and X has new-extended alignment).
9449  if (E->getNumPlacementArgs() != 1 ||
9450  !E->getPlacementArg(0)->getType()->isNothrowT())
9451  return Error(E, diag::note_constexpr_new_placement);
9452 
9453  LValue Nothrow;
9454  if (!EvaluateLValue(E->getPlacementArg(0), Nothrow, Info))
9455  return false;
9456  IsNothrow = true;
9457  }
9458 
9459  const Expr *Init = E->getInitializer();
9460  const InitListExpr *ResizedArrayILE = nullptr;
9461  const CXXConstructExpr *ResizedArrayCCE = nullptr;
9462  bool ValueInit = false;
9463 
9464  QualType AllocType = E->getAllocatedType();
9465  if (Optional<const Expr *> ArraySize = E->getArraySize()) {
9466  const Expr *Stripped = *ArraySize;
9467  for (; auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Stripped);
9468  Stripped = ICE->getSubExpr())
9469  if (ICE->getCastKind() != CK_NoOp &&
9470  ICE->getCastKind() != CK_IntegralCast)
9471  break;
9472 
9473  llvm::APSInt ArrayBound;
9474  if (!EvaluateInteger(Stripped, ArrayBound, Info))
9475  return false;
9476 
9477  // C++ [expr.new]p9:
9478  // The expression is erroneous if:
9479  // -- [...] its value before converting to size_t [or] applying the
9480  // second standard conversion sequence is less than zero
9481  if (ArrayBound.isSigned() && ArrayBound.isNegative()) {
9482  if (IsNothrow)
9483  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9484 
9485  Info.FFDiag(*ArraySize, diag::note_constexpr_new_negative)
9486  << ArrayBound << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange();
9487  return false;
9488  }
9489 
9490  // -- its value is such that the size of the allocated object would
9491  // exceed the implementation-defined limit
9492  if (ConstantArrayType::getNumAddressingBits(Info.Ctx, AllocType,
9493  ArrayBound) >
9494  ConstantArrayType::getMaxSizeBits(Info.Ctx)) {
9495  if (IsNothrow)
9496  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9497 
9498  Info.FFDiag(*ArraySize, diag::note_constexpr_new_too_large)
9499  << ArrayBound << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange();
9500  return false;
9501  }
9502 
9503  // -- the new-initializer is a braced-init-list and the number of
9504  // array elements for which initializers are provided [...]
9505  // exceeds the number of elements to initialize
9506  if (!Init) {
9507  // No initialization is performed.
9508  } else if (isa<CXXScalarValueInitExpr>(Init) ||
9509  isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(Init)) {
9510  ValueInit = true;
9511  } else if (auto *CCE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Init)) {
9512  ResizedArrayCCE = CCE;
9513  } else {
9514  auto *CAT = Info.Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(Init->getType());
9515  assert(CAT && "unexpected type for array initializer");
9516 
9517  unsigned Bits =
9518  std::max(CAT->getSize().getBitWidth(), ArrayBound.getBitWidth());
9519  llvm::APInt InitBound = CAT->getSize().zextOrSelf(Bits);
9520  llvm::APInt AllocBound = ArrayBound.zextOrSelf(Bits);
9521  if (InitBound.ugt(AllocBound)) {
9522  if (IsNothrow)
9523  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9524 
9525  Info.FFDiag(*ArraySize, diag::note_constexpr_new_too_small)
9526  << toString(AllocBound, 10, /*Signed=*/false)
9527  << toString(InitBound, 10, /*Signed=*/false)
9528  << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange();
9529  return false;
9530  }
9531 
9532  // If the sizes differ, we must have an initializer list, and we need
9533  // special handling for this case when we initialize.
9534  if (InitBound != AllocBound)
9535  ResizedArrayILE = cast<InitListExpr>(Init);
9536  }
9537 
9538  AllocType = Info.Ctx.getConstantArrayType(AllocType, ArrayBound, nullptr,
9539  ArrayType::Normal, 0);
9540  } else {
9541  assert(!AllocType->isArrayType() &&
9542  "array allocation with non-array new");
9543  }
9544 
9545  APValue *Val;
9546  if (IsPlacement) {
9547  AccessKinds AK = AK_Construct;
9548  struct FindObjectHandler {
9549  EvalInfo &Info;
9550  const Expr *E;
9551  QualType AllocType;
9552  const AccessKinds AccessKind;
9553  APValue *Value;
9554 
9555  typedef bool result_type;
9556  bool failed() { return false; }
9557  bool found(APValue &Subobj, QualType SubobjType) {
9558  // FIXME: Reject the cases where [basic.life]p8 would not permit the
9559  // old name of the object to be used to name the new object.
9560  if (!Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(SubobjType, AllocType)) {
9561  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_placement_new_wrong_type) <<
9562  SubobjType << AllocType;
9563  return false;
9564  }
9565  Value = &Subobj;
9566  return true;
9567  }
9568  bool found(APSInt &Value, QualType SubobjType) {
9569  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_construct_complex_elem);
9570  return false;
9571  }
9572  bool found(APFloat &Value, QualType SubobjType) {
9573  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_construct_complex_elem);
9574  return false;
9575  }
9576  } Handler = {Info, E, AllocType, AK, nullptr};
9577 
9578  CompleteObject Obj = findCompleteObject(Info, E, AK, Result, AllocType);
9579  if (!Obj || !findSubobject(Info, E, Obj, Result.Designator, Handler))
9580  return false;
9581 
9582  Val = Handler.Value;
9583 
9584  // [basic.life]p1:
9585  // The lifetime of an object o of type T ends when [...] the storage
9586  // which the object occupies is [...] reused by an object that is not
9587  // nested within o (6.6.2).
9588  *Val = APValue();
9589  } else {
9590  // Perform the allocation and obtain a pointer to the resulting object.
9591  Val = Info.createHeapAlloc(E, AllocType, Result);
9592  if (!Val)
9593  return false;
9594  }
9595 
9596  if (ValueInit) {
9597  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(AllocType);
9598  if (!EvaluateInPlace(*Val, Info, Result, &VIE))
9599  return false;
9600  } else if (ResizedArrayILE) {
9601  if (!EvaluateArrayNewInitList(Info, Result, *Val, ResizedArrayILE,
9602  AllocType))
9603  return false;
9604  } else if (ResizedArrayCCE) {
9605  if (!EvaluateArrayNewConstructExpr(Info, Result, *Val, ResizedArrayCCE,
9606  AllocType))
9607  return false;
9608  } else if (Init) {
9609  if (!EvaluateInPlace(*Val, Info, Result, Init))
9610  return false;
9611  } else if (!getDefaultInitValue(AllocType, *Val)) {
9612  return false;
9613  }
9614 
9615  // Array new returns a pointer to the first element, not a pointer to the
9616  // array.
9617  if (auto *AT = AllocType->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
9618  Result.addArray(Info, E, cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT));
9619 
9620  return true;
9621 }

9628  : public ExprEvaluatorBase<MemberPointerExprEvaluator> {
9629  MemberPtr &Result;

9632  Result = MemberPtr(D);
9633  return true;
9634  }
9635 public:
9636 
9637  MemberPointerExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &Info, MemberPtr &Result)
9638  : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(Info), Result(Result) {}
9639 
9640  bool Success(const APValue &V, const Expr *E) {
9641  Result.setFrom(V);
9642  return true;
9643  }

9645  return Success((const ValueDecl*)nullptr);
9646  }

9652 
9653 static bool EvaluateMemberPointer(const Expr *E, MemberPtr &Result,
9654  EvalInfo &Info) {
9655  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
9656  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isMemberPointerType());
9657  return MemberPointerExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E);
9658 }
9659 
9660 bool MemberPointerExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
9661  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
9662  default:
9663  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
9664 
9665  case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
9666  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
9667  return ZeroInitialization(E);
9668 
9669  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer: {
9670  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
9671  return false;
9672  if (E->path_empty())
9673  return true;
9674  // Base-to-derived member pointer casts store the path in derived-to-base
9675  // order, so iterate backwards. The CXXBaseSpecifier also provides us with
9676  // the wrong end of the derived->base arc, so stagger the path by one class.
9677  typedef std::reverse_iterator<CastExpr::path_const_iterator> ReverseIter;
9678  for (ReverseIter PathI(E->path_end() - 1), PathE(E->path_begin());
9679  PathI != PathE; ++PathI) {
9680  assert(!(*PathI)->isVirtual() && "memptr cast through vbase");
9681  const CXXRecordDecl *Derived = (*PathI)->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9682  if (!Result.castToDerived(Derived))
9683  return Error(E);
9684  }
9685  const Type *FinalTy = E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>()->getClass();
9686  if (!Result.castToDerived(FinalTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl()))
9687  return Error(E);
9688  return true;
9689  }
9690 
9691  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
9692  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
9693  return false;
9694  for (CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathI = E->path_begin(),
9695  PathE = E->path_end(); PathI != PathE; ++PathI) {
9696  assert(!(*PathI)->isVirtual() && "memptr cast through vbase");
9697  const CXXRecordDecl *Base = (*PathI)->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9698  if (!Result.castToBase(Base))
9699  return Error(E);
9700  }
9701  return true;
9702  }
9703 }
9704 
9705 bool MemberPointerExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryAddrOf(const UnaryOperator *E) {
9706  // C++11 [expr.unary.op]p3 has very strict rules on how the address of a
9707  // member can be formed.
9708  return Success(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->getSubExpr())->getDecl());
9709 }

9723  : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(info), This(This), Result(Result) {}

9726  Result = V;
9727  return true;
9728  }

9730  return ZeroInitialization(E, E->getType());
9731  }
9732  bool ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E, QualType T);
9733

9736  }

9743  bool VisitCXXInheritedCtorInitExpr(const CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr *E);
9744  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E, QualType T);
9745  bool VisitCXXStdInitializerListExpr(const CXXStdInitializerListExpr *E);
9746  bool VisitBinCmp(const BinaryOperator *E);
9747  };

9749 
9750 /// Perform zero-initialization on an object of non-union class type.
9751 /// C++11 [dcl.init]p5:
9752 /// To zero-initialize an object or reference of type T means:
9753 /// [...]
9754 /// -- if T is a (possibly cv-qualified) non-union class type,
9755 /// each non-static data member and each base-class subobject is
9756 /// zero-initialized
9757 static bool HandleClassZeroInitialization(EvalInfo &Info, const Expr *E,
9758  const RecordDecl *RD,
9759  const LValue &This, APValue &Result) {
9760  assert(!RD->isUnion() && "Expected non-union class type");
9761  const CXXRecordDecl *CD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
9762  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitStruct(), CD ? CD->getNumBases() : 0,
9763  std::distance(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end()));
9764 
9765  if (RD->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
9766  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Info.Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
9767 
9768  if (CD) {
9769  unsigned Index = 0;
9770  for (CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_iterator I = CD->bases_begin(),
9771  End = CD->bases_end(); I != End; ++I, ++Index) {
9772  const CXXRecordDecl *Base = I->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9773  LValue Subobject = This;
9774  if (!HandleLValueDirectBase(Info, E, Subobject, CD, Base, &Layout))
9775  return false;
9776  if (!HandleClassZeroInitialization(Info, E, Base, Subobject,
9777  Result.getStructBase(Index)))
9778  return false;
9779  }
9780  }
9781 
9782  for (const auto *I : RD->fields()) {
9783  // -- if T is a reference type, no initialization is performed.
9784  if (I->isUnnamedBitfield() || I->getType()->isReferenceType())
9785  continue;
9786 
9787  LValue Subobject = This;
9788  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, E, Subobject, I, &Layout))
9789  return false;
9790 
9791  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(I->getType());
9792  if (!EvaluateInPlace(
9793  Result.getStructField(I->getFieldIndex()), Info, Subobject, &VIE))
9794  return false;
9795  }
9796 
9797  return true;
9798 }
9799 
9800 bool RecordExprEvaluator::ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E, QualType T) {
9801  const RecordDecl *RD = T->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
9802  if (RD->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
9803  if (RD->isUnion()) {
9804  // C++11 [dcl.init]p5: If T is a (possibly cv-qualified) union type, the
9805  // object's first non-static named data member is zero-initialized
9806  RecordDecl::field_iterator I = RD->field_begin();
9807  while (I != RD->field_end() && (*I)->isUnnamedBitfield())
9808  ++I;
9809  if (I == RD->field_end()) {
9810  Result = APValue((const FieldDecl*)nullptr);
9811  return true;
9812  }
9813 
9814  LValue Subobject = This;
9815  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, E, Subobject, *I))
9816  return false;
9817  Result = APValue(*I);
9818  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(I->getType());
9819  return EvaluateInPlace(Result.getUnionValue(), Info, Subobject, &VIE);
9820  }
9821 
9822  if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(RD) && cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)->getNumVBases()) {
9823  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_virtual_base) << RD;
9824  return false;
9825  }
9826 
9827  return HandleClassZeroInitialization(Info, E, RD, This, Result);
9828 }
9829 
9830 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
9831  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
9832  default:
9833  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
9834 
9835  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
9836  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
9837 
9838  case CK_DerivedToBase:
9839  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase: {
9840  APValue DerivedObject;
9841  if (!Evaluate(DerivedObject, Info, E->getSubExpr()))
9842  return false;
9843  if (!DerivedObject.isStruct())
9844  return Error(E->getSubExpr());
9845 
9846  // Derived-to-base rvalue conversion: just slice off the derived part.
9847  APValue *Value = &DerivedObject;
9848  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9849  for (CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathI = E->path_begin(),
9850  PathE = E->path_end(); PathI != PathE; ++PathI) {
9851  assert(!(*PathI)->isVirtual() && "record rvalue with virtual base");
9852  const CXXRecordDecl *Base = (*PathI)->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9853  Value = &Value->getStructBase(getBaseIndex(RD, Base));
9854  RD = Base;
9855  }
9856  Result = *Value;
9857  return true;
9858  }
9859  }
9860 }
9861 
9862 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitInitListExpr(const InitListExpr *E) {
9863  if (E->isTransparent())
9864  return Visit(E->getInit(0));
9865 
9866  const RecordDecl *RD = E->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
9867  if (RD->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
9868  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Info.Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
9869  auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
9870 
9871  EvalInfo::EvaluatingConstructorRAII EvalObj(
9872  Info,
9873  ObjectUnderConstruction{This.getLValueBase(), This.Designator.Entries},
9874  CXXRD && CXXRD->getNumBases());
9875 
9876  if (RD->isUnion()) {
9877  const FieldDecl *Field = E->getInitializedFieldInUnion();
9878  Result = APValue(Field);
9879  if (!Field)
9880  return true;
9881 
9882  // If the initializer list for a union does not contain any elements, the
9883  // first element of the union is value-initialized.
9884  // FIXME: The element should be initialized from an initializer list.
9885  // Is this difference ever observable for initializer lists which
9886  // we don't build?
9887  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(Field->getType());
9888  const Expr *InitExpr = E->getNumInits() ? E->getInit(0) : &VIE;
9889 
9890  LValue Subobject = This;
9891  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, InitExpr, Subobject, Field, &Layout))
9892  return false;
9893 
9894  // Temporarily override This, in case there's a CXXDefaultInitExpr in here.
9895  ThisOverrideRAII ThisOverride(*Info.CurrentCall, &This,
9896  isa<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(InitExpr));
9897 
9898  if (EvaluateInPlace(Result.getUnionValue(), Info, Subobject, InitExpr)) {
9899  if (Field->isBitField())
9900  return truncateBitfieldValue(Info, InitExpr, Result.getUnionValue(),
9901  Field);
9902  return true;
9903  }
9904 
9905  return false;
9906  }
9907 
9908  if (!Result.hasValue())
9909  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitStruct(), CXXRD ? CXXRD->getNumBases() : 0,
9910  std::distance(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end()));
9911  unsigned ElementNo = 0;
9912  bool Success = true;
9913 
9914  // Initialize base classes.
9915  if (CXXRD && CXXRD->getNumBases()) {
9916  for (const auto &Base : CXXRD->bases()) {
9917  assert(ElementNo < E->getNumInits() && "missing init for base class");
9918  const Expr *Init = E->getInit(ElementNo);
9919 
9920  LValue Subobject = This;
9921  if (!HandleLValueBase(Info, Init, Subobject, CXXRD, &Base))
9922  return false;
9923 
9924  APValue &FieldVal = Result.getStructBase(ElementNo);
9925  if (!EvaluateInPlace(FieldVal, Info, Subobject, Init)) {
9926  if (!Info.noteFailure())
9927  return false;
9928  Success = false;
9929  }
9930  ++ElementNo;
9931  }
9932 
9933  EvalObj.finishedConstructingBases();
9934  }
9935 
9936  // Initialize members.
9937  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
9938  // Anonymous bit-fields are not considered members of the class for
9939  // purposes of aggregate initialization.
9940  if (Field->isUnnamedBitfield())
9941  continue;
9942 
9943  LValue Subobject = This;
9944 
9945  bool HaveInit = ElementNo < E->getNumInits();
9946 
9947  // FIXME: Diagnostics here should point to the end of the initializer
9948  // list, not the start.
9949  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, HaveInit ? E->getInit(ElementNo) : E,
9950  Subobject, Field, &Layout))
9951  return false;
9952 
9953  // Perform an implicit value-initialization for members beyond the end of
9954  // the initializer list.
9955  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(HaveInit ? Info.Ctx.IntTy : Field->getType());
9956  const Expr *Init = HaveInit ? E->getInit(ElementNo++) : &VIE;
9957 
9958  // Temporarily override This, in case there's a CXXDefaultInitExpr in here.
9959  ThisOverrideRAII ThisOverride(*Info.CurrentCall, &This,
9960  isa<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(Init));
9961 
9962  APValue &FieldVal = Result.getStructField(Field->getFieldIndex());
9963  if (!EvaluateInPlace(FieldVal, Info, Subobject, Init) ||
9964  (Field->isBitField() && !truncateBitfieldValue(Info, Init,
9965  FieldVal, Field))) {
9966  if (!Info.noteFailure())
9967  return false;
9968  Success = false;
9969  }
9970  }
9971 
9972  EvalObj.finishedConstructingFields();
9973 
9974  return Success;
9975 }
9976 
9977 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E,
9978  QualType T) {
9979  // Note that E's type is not necessarily the type of our class here; we might
9980  // be initializing an array element instead.
9981  const CXXConstructorDecl *FD = E->getConstructor();
9982  if (FD->isInvalidDecl() || FD->getParent()->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
9983 
9984  bool ZeroInit = E->requiresZeroInitialization();
9985  if (CheckTrivialDefaultConstructor(Info, E->getExprLoc(), FD, ZeroInit)) {
9986  // If we've already performed zero-initialization, we're already done.
9987  if (Result.hasValue())
9988  return true;
9989 
9990  if (ZeroInit)
9991  return ZeroInitialization(E, T);
9992 
9993  return getDefaultInitValue(T, Result);
9994  }
9995 
9996  const FunctionDecl *Definition = nullptr;
9997  auto Body = FD->getBody(Definition);
9998 
9999  if (!CheckConstexprFunction(Info, E->getExprLoc(), FD, Definition, Body))
10000  return false;
10001 
10002  // Avoid materializing a temporary for an elidable copy/move constructor.
10003  if (E->isElidable() && !ZeroInit) {
10004  // FIXME: This only handles the simplest case, where the source object
10005  // is passed directly as the first argument to the constructor.
10006  // This should also handle stepping though implicit casts and
10007  // and conversion sequences which involve two steps, with a
10008  // conversion operator followed by a converting constructor.
10009  const Expr *SrcObj = E->getArg(0);
10010  assert(SrcObj->isTemporaryObject(Info.Ctx, FD->getParent()));
10011  assert(Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(E->getType(), SrcObj->getType()));
10012  if (const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *ME =
10013  dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(SrcObj))
10014  return Visit(ME->getSubExpr());
10015  }
10016 
10017  if (ZeroInit && !ZeroInitialization(E, T))
10018  return false;
10019 
10020  auto Args = llvm::makeArrayRef(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs());
10021  return HandleConstructorCall(E, This, Args,
10022  cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Definition), Info,
10023  Result);
10024 }
10025 
10026 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitCXXInheritedCtorInitExpr(
10027  const CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr *E) {
10028  if (!Info.CurrentCall) {
10029  assert(Info.checkingPotentialConstantExpression());
10030  return false;
10031  }
10032 
10033  const CXXConstructorDecl *FD = E->getConstructor();
10034  if (FD->isInvalidDecl() || FD->getParent()->isInvalidDecl())
10035  return false;
10036 
10037  const FunctionDecl *Definition = nullptr;
10038  auto Body = FD->getBody(Definition);
10039 
10040  if (!CheckConstexprFunction(Info, E->getExprLoc(), FD, Definition, Body))
10041  return false;
10042 
10043  return HandleConstructorCall(E, This, Info.CurrentCall->Arguments,
10044  cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Definition), Info,
10045  Result);
10046 }
10047 
10048 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitCXXStdInitializerListExpr(
10049  const CXXStdInitializerListExpr *E) {
10050  const ConstantArrayType *ArrayType =
10051  Info.Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(E->getSubExpr()->getType());
10052 
10053  LValue Array;
10054  if (!EvaluateLValue(E->getSubExpr(), Array, Info))
10055  return false;
10056 
10057  // Get a pointer to the first element of the array.
10058  Array.addArray(Info, E, ArrayType);
10059 
10060  auto InvalidType = [&] {
10061  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_unsupported_layout)
10062  << E->getType();
10063  return false;
10064  };
10065 
10066  // FIXME: Perform the checks on the field types in SemaInit.
10067  RecordDecl *Record = E->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
10068  RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = Record->field_begin();
10069  if (Field == Record->field_end())
10070  return InvalidType();
10071 
10072  // Start pointer.
10073  if (!Field->getType()->isPointerType() ||
10074  !Info.Ctx.hasSameType(Field->getType()->getPointeeType(),
10075  ArrayType->getElementType()))
10076  return InvalidType();
10077 
10078  // FIXME: What if the initializer_list type has base classes, etc?
10079  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitStruct(), 0, 2);
10080  Array.moveInto(Result.getStructField(0));
10081 
10082  if (++Field == Record->field_end())
10083  return InvalidType();
10084 
10085  if (Field->getType()->isPointerType() &&
10086  Info.Ctx.hasSameType(Field->getType()->getPointeeType(),
10087  ArrayType->getElementType())) {
10088  // End pointer.
10089  if (!HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, Array,
10090  ArrayType->getElementType(),
10091  ArrayType->getSize().getZExtValue()))
10092  return false;
10093  Array.moveInto(Result.getStructField(1));
10094  } else if (Info.Ctx.hasSameType(Field->getType(), Info.Ctx.getSizeType()))
10095  // Length.
10096  Result.getStructField(1) = APValue(APSInt(ArrayType->getSize()));
10097  else
10098  return InvalidType();
10099 
10100  if (++Field != Record->field_end())
10101  return InvalidType();
10102 
10103  return true;
10104 }
10105 
10106 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitLambdaExpr(const LambdaExpr *E) {
10107  const CXXRecordDecl *ClosureClass = E->getLambdaClass();
10108  if (ClosureClass->isInvalidDecl())
10109  return false;
10110 
10111  const size_t NumFields =
10112  std::distance(ClosureClass->field_begin(), ClosureClass->field_end());
10113 
10114  assert(NumFields == (size_t)std::distance(E->capture_init_begin(),
10115  E->capture_init_end()) &&
10116  "The number of lambda capture initializers should equal the number of "
10117  "fields within the closure type");
10118 
10119  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitStruct(), /*NumBases*/0, NumFields);
10120  // Iterate through all the lambda's closure object's fields and initialize
10121  // them.
10122  auto *CaptureInitIt = E->capture_init_begin();
10123  bool Success = true;
10124  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Info.Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(ClosureClass);
10125  for (const auto *Field : ClosureClass->fields()) {
10126  assert(CaptureInitIt != E->capture_init_end());
10127  // Get the initializer for this field
10128  Expr *const CurFieldInit = *CaptureInitIt++;
10129 
10130  // If there is no initializer, either this is a VLA or an error has
10131  // occurred.
10132  if (!CurFieldInit)
10133  return Error(E);
10134 
10135  LValue Subobject = This;
10136 
10137  if (!HandleLValueMember(Info, E, Subobject, Field, &Layout))
10138  return false;
10139 
10140  APValue &FieldVal = Result.getStructField(Field->getFieldIndex());
10141  if (!EvaluateInPlace(FieldVal, Info, Subobject, CurFieldInit)) {
10142  if (!Info.keepEvaluatingAfterFailure())
10143  return false;
10144  Success = false;
10145  }
10146  }
10147  return Success;
10148 }
10149 
10150 static bool EvaluateRecord(const Expr *E, const LValue &This,
10151  APValue &Result, EvalInfo &Info) {
10152  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
10153  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isRecordType() &&
10154  "can't evaluate expression as a record rvalue");
10155  return RecordExprEvaluator(Info, This, Result).Visit(E);
10156 }

10158 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10159 // Temporary Evaluation
10160 //
10161 // Temporaries are represented in the AST as rvalues, but generally behave like
10162 // lvalues. The full-object of which the temporary is a subobject is implicitly
10163 // materialized so that a reference can bind to it.
10164 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10165 namespace {
10166 class TemporaryExprEvaluator
10167  : public LValueExprEvaluatorBase<TemporaryExprEvaluator> {
10168 public:
10169  TemporaryExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &Info, LValue &Result) :
10170  LValueExprEvaluatorBaseTy(Info, Result, false) {}
10171 
10172  /// Visit an expression which constructs the value of this temporary.
10173  bool VisitConstructExpr(const Expr *E) {
10174  APValue &Value = Info.CurrentCall->createTemporary(
10175  E, E->getType(), ScopeKind::FullExpression, Result);
10176  return EvaluateInPlace(Value, Info, Result, E);
10177  }
10178 
10179  bool VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
10180  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
10181  default:
10182  return LValueExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
10183 
10184  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
10185  return VisitConstructExpr(E->getSubExpr());
10186  }
10187  }
10188  bool VisitInitListExpr(const InitListExpr *E) {
10189  return VisitConstructExpr(E);
10190  }
10191  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E) {
10192  return VisitConstructExpr(E);
10193  }
10194  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
10195  return VisitConstructExpr(E);
10196  }
10197  bool VisitCXXStdInitializerListExpr(const CXXStdInitializerListExpr *E) {
10198  return VisitConstructExpr(E);
10199  }
10200  bool VisitLambdaExpr(const LambdaExpr *E) {
10201  return VisitConstructExpr(E);
10202  }
10203 };
10204 } // end anonymous namespace

10208  assert(!E->isValueDependent());

10210  return TemporaryExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E);

10251 static bool EvaluateVector(const Expr* E, APValue& Result, EvalInfo &Info) {
10252  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isVectorType() &&
10253  "not a vector prvalue");

10256 
10257 bool VectorExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
10258  const VectorType *VTy = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>();
10259  unsigned NElts = VTy->getNumElements();
10260 
10261  const Expr *SE = E->getSubExpr();
10262  QualType SETy = SE->getType();
10263 
10264  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
10265  case CK_VectorSplat: {
10266  APValue Val = APValue();
10267  if (SETy->isIntegerType()) {
10268  APSInt IntResult;
10269  if (!EvaluateInteger(SE, IntResult, Info))
10270  return false;
10271  Val = APValue(std::move(IntResult));
10272  } else if (SETy->isRealFloatingType()) {
10273  APFloat FloatResult(0.0);
10274  if (!EvaluateFloat(SE, FloatResult, Info))
10275  return false;
10276  Val = APValue(std::move(FloatResult));
10277  } else {
10278  return Error(E);
10279  }
10280 
10281  // Splat and create vector APValue.
10282  SmallVector<APValue, 4> Elts(NElts, Val);
10283  return Success(Elts, E);
10284  }
10285  case CK_BitCast: {
10286  // Evaluate the operand into an APInt we can extract from.
10287  llvm::APInt SValInt;
10288  if (!EvalAndBitcastToAPInt(Info, SE, SValInt))
10289  return false;
10290  // Extract the elements
10291  QualType EltTy = VTy->getElementType();
10292  unsigned EltSize = Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(EltTy);
10293  bool BigEndian = Info.Ctx.getTargetInfo().isBigEndian();
10294  SmallVector<APValue, 4> Elts;
10295  if (EltTy->isRealFloatingType()) {
10296  const llvm::fltSemantics &Sem = Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(EltTy);
10297  unsigned FloatEltSize = EltSize;
10298  if (&Sem == &APFloat::x87DoubleExtended())
10299  FloatEltSize = 80;
10300  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NElts; i++) {
10301  llvm::APInt Elt;
10302  if (BigEndian)
10303  Elt = SValInt.rotl(i*EltSize+FloatEltSize).trunc(FloatEltSize);
10304  else
10305  Elt = SValInt.rotr(i*EltSize).trunc(FloatEltSize);
10306  Elts.push_back(APValue(APFloat(Sem, Elt)));
10307  }
10308  } else if (EltTy->isIntegerType()) {
10309  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NElts; i++) {
10310  llvm::APInt Elt;
10311  if (BigEndian)
10312  Elt = SValInt.rotl(i*EltSize+EltSize).zextOrTrunc(EltSize);
10313  else
10314  Elt = SValInt.rotr(i*EltSize).zextOrTrunc(EltSize);
10315  Elts.push_back(APValue(APSInt(Elt, !EltTy->isSignedIntegerType())));
10316  }
10317  } else {
10318  return Error(E);
10319  }
10320  return Success(Elts, E);
10321  }
10322  default:
10323  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
10324  }
10325 }
10326 
10327 bool
10328 VectorExprEvaluator::VisitInitListExpr(const InitListExpr *E) {
10329  const VectorType *VT = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>();
10330  unsigned NumInits = E->getNumInits();
10331  unsigned NumElements = VT->getNumElements();
10332 
10333  QualType EltTy = VT->getElementType();
10334  SmallVector<APValue, 4> Elements;
10335 
10336  // The number of initializers can be less than the number of
10337  // vector elements. For OpenCL, this can be due to nested vector
10338  // initialization. For GCC compatibility, missing trailing elements
10339  // should be initialized with zeroes.
10340  unsigned CountInits = 0, CountElts = 0;
10341  while (CountElts < NumElements) {
10342  // Handle nested vector initialization.
10343  if (CountInits < NumInits
10344  && E->getInit(CountInits)->getType()->isVectorType()) {
10345  APValue v;
10346  if (!EvaluateVector(E->getInit(CountInits), v, Info))
10347  return Error(E);
10348  unsigned vlen = v.getVectorLength();
10349  for (unsigned j = 0; j < vlen; j++)
10350  Elements.push_back(v.getVectorElt(j));
10351  CountElts += vlen;
10352  } else if (EltTy->isIntegerType()) {
10353  llvm::APSInt sInt(32);
10354  if (CountInits < NumInits) {
10355  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getInit(CountInits), sInt, Info))
10356  return false;
10357  } else // trailing integer zero.
10358  sInt = Info.Ctx.MakeIntValue(0, EltTy);
10359  Elements.push_back(APValue(sInt));
10360  CountElts++;
10361  } else {
10362  llvm::APFloat f(0.0);
10363  if (CountInits < NumInits) {
10364  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getInit(CountInits), f, Info))
10365  return false;
10366  } else // trailing float zero.
10367  f = APFloat::getZero(Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(EltTy));
10368  Elements.push_back(APValue(f));
10369  CountElts++;
10370  }
10371  CountInits++;
10372  }
10373  return Success(Elements, E);
10374 }
10375 
10376 bool
10377 VectorExprEvaluator::ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) {
10378  const auto *VT = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>();
10379  QualType EltTy = VT->getElementType();
10380  APValue ZeroElement;
10381  if (EltTy->isIntegerType())
10382  ZeroElement = APValue(Info.Ctx.MakeIntValue(0, EltTy));
10383  else
10384  ZeroElement =
10385  APValue(APFloat::getZero(Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(EltTy)));
10386 
10387  SmallVector<APValue, 4> Elements(VT->getNumElements(), ZeroElement);
10388  return Success(Elements, E);
10389 }

10391 bool VectorExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E) {
10392  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
10393  return ZeroInitialization(E);
10394 }
10395 
10396 bool VectorExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
10397  BinaryOperatorKind Op = E->getOpcode();
10398  assert(Op != BO_PtrMemD && Op != BO_PtrMemI && Op != BO_Cmp &&
10399  "Operation not supported on vector types");
10400 
10401  if (Op == BO_Comma)
10402  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
10403 
10404  Expr *LHS = E->getLHS();
10405  Expr *RHS = E->getRHS();
10406 
10407  assert(LHS->getType()->isVectorType() && RHS->getType()->isVectorType() &&
10408  "Must both be vector types");
10409  // Checking JUST the types are the same would be fine, except shifts don't
10410  // need to have their types be the same (since you always shift by an int).
10411  assert(LHS->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() ==
10412  E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() &&
10413  RHS->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() ==
10414  E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() &&
10415  "All operands must be the same size.");
10416 
10417  APValue LHSValue;
10418  APValue RHSValue;
10419  bool LHSOK = Evaluate(LHSValue, Info, LHS);
10420  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
10421  return false;
10422  if (!Evaluate(RHSValue, Info, RHS) || !LHSOK)
10423  return false;
10424 
10425  if (!handleVectorVectorBinOp(Info, E, Op, LHSValue, RHSValue))
10426  return false;
10427 
10428  return Success(LHSValue, E);
10429 }
10430 
10431 static llvm::Optional<APValue> handleVectorUnaryOperator(ASTContext &Ctx,
10432  QualType ResultTy,
10433  UnaryOperatorKind Op,
10434  APValue Elt) {
10435  switch (Op) {
10436  case UO_Plus:
10437  // Nothing to do here.
10438  return Elt;
10439  case UO_Minus:
10440  if (Elt.getKind() == APValue::Int) {
10441  Elt.getInt().negate();
10442  } else {
10443  assert(Elt.getKind() == APValue::Float &&
10444  "Vector can only be int or float type");
10445  Elt.getFloat().changeSign();
10446  }
10447  return Elt;
10448  case UO_Not:
10449  // This is only valid for integral types anyway, so we don't have to handle
10450  // float here.
10451  assert(Elt.getKind() == APValue::Int &&
10452  "Vector operator ~ can only be int");
10453  Elt.getInt().flipAllBits();
10454  return Elt;
10455  case UO_LNot: {
10456  if (Elt.getKind() == APValue::Int) {
10457  Elt.getInt() = !Elt.getInt();
10458  // operator ! on vectors returns -1 for 'truth', so negate it.
10459  Elt.getInt().negate();
10460  return Elt;
10461  }
10462  assert(Elt.getKind() == APValue::Float &&
10463  "Vector can only be int or float type");
10464  // Float types result in an int of the same size, but -1 for true, or 0 for
10465  // false.
10466  APSInt EltResult{Ctx.getIntWidth(ResultTy),
10467  ResultTy->isUnsignedIntegerType()};
10468  if (Elt.getFloat().isZero())
10469  EltResult.setAllBits();
10470  else
10471  EltResult.clearAllBits();
10472 
10473  return APValue{EltResult};
10474  }
10475  default:
10476  // FIXME: Implement the rest of the unary operators.
10477  return llvm::None;
10478  }
10479 }
10480 
10481 bool VectorExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryOperator(const UnaryOperator *E) {
10482  Expr *SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
10483  const auto *VD = SubExpr->getType()->castAs<VectorType>();
10484  // This result element type differs in the case of negating a floating point
10485  // vector, since the result type is the a vector of the equivilant sized
10486  // integer.
10487  const QualType ResultEltTy = VD->getElementType();
10488  UnaryOperatorKind Op = E->getOpcode();
10489 
10490  APValue SubExprValue;
10491  if (!Evaluate(SubExprValue, Info, SubExpr))
10492  return false;
10493 
10494  // FIXME: This vector evaluator someday needs to be changed to be LValue
10495  // aware/keep LValue information around, rather than dealing with just vector
10496  // types directly. Until then, we cannot handle cases where the operand to
10497  // these unary operators is an LValue. The only case I've been able to see
10498  // cause this is operator++ assigning to a member expression (only valid in
10499  // altivec compilations) in C mode, so this shouldn't limit us too much.
10500  if (SubExprValue.isLValue())
10501  return false;
10502 
10503  assert(SubExprValue.getVectorLength() == VD->getNumElements() &&
10504  "Vector length doesn't match type?");
10505 
10506  SmallVector<APValue, 4> ResultElements;
10507  for (unsigned EltNum = 0; EltNum < VD->getNumElements(); ++EltNum) {
10508  llvm::Optional<APValue> Elt = handleVectorUnaryOperator(
10509  Info.Ctx, ResultEltTy, Op, SubExprValue.getVectorElt(EltNum));
10510  if (!Elt)
10511  return false;
10512  ResultElements.push_back(*Elt);
10513  }
10514  return Success(APValue(ResultElements.data(), ResultElements.size()), E);
10515 }

10518 // Array Evaluation

10521 namespace {
10522  class ArrayExprEvaluator
10523  : public ExprEvaluatorBase<ArrayExprEvaluator> {
10524  const LValue &This;
10525  APValue &Result;
10526  public:
10527 
10528  ArrayExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &Info, const LValue &This, APValue &Result)
10529  : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(Info), This(This), Result(Result) {}
10530 
10531  bool Success(const APValue &V, const Expr *E) {
10532  assert(V.isArray() && "expected array");
10533  Result = V;
10534  return true;
10535  }
10536 
10537  bool ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) {
10538  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
10539  Info.Ctx.getAsConstantArrayType(E->getType());
10540  if (!CAT) {
10541  if (E->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
10542  // We can be asked to zero-initialize a flexible array member; this
10543  // is represented as an ImplicitValueInitExpr of incomplete array
10544  // type. In this case, the array has zero elements.
10545  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitArray(), 0, 0);
10546  return true;
10547  }
10548  // FIXME: We could handle VLAs here.
10549  return Error(E);
10550  }
10551 
10552  Result = APValue(APValue::UninitArray(), 0,
10553  CAT->getSize().getZExtValue());
10554  if (!Result.hasArrayFiller())
10555  return true;
10556 
10557  // Zero-initialize all elements.
10558  LValue Subobject = This;
10559  Subobject.addArray(Info, E, CAT);
10560  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(CAT->getElementType());
10561  return EvaluateInPlace(Result.getArrayFiller(), Info, Subobject, &VIE);
10562  }
10563 
10564  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
10565  return handleCallExpr(E, Result, &This);
10566  }
10567  bool VisitInitListExpr(const InitListExpr *E,
10568  QualType AllocType = QualType());
10569  bool VisitArrayInitLoopExpr(const ArrayInitLoopExpr *E);
10570  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E);
10571  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E,
10572  const LValue &Subobject,
10573  APValue *Value, QualType Type);
10574  bool VisitStringLiteral(const StringLiteral *E,
10575  QualType AllocType = QualType()) {
10576  expandStringLiteral(Info, E, Result, AllocType);
10577  return true;
10578  }
10579  };
10580 } // end anonymous namespace
