12050 
12051  case Builtin::BIstrcmp:
12052  case Builtin::BIwcscmp:
12053  case Builtin::BIstrncmp:
12054  case Builtin::BIwcsncmp:
12055  case Builtin::BImemcmp:
12056  case Builtin::BIbcmp:
12057  case Builtin::BIwmemcmp:
12058  // A call to strlen is not a constant expression.
12059  if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
12060  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_function)
12061  << /*isConstexpr*/0 << /*isConstructor*/0
12062  << (std::string("'") + Info.Ctx.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinOp) + "'");
12063  else
12064  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_invalid_subexpr_in_const_expr);
12065  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
12066  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strcmp:
12067  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wcscmp:
12068  case Builtin::BI__builtin_strncmp:
12069  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wcsncmp:
12070  case Builtin::BI__builtin_memcmp:
12071  case Builtin::BI__builtin_bcmp:
12072  case Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcmp: {
12073  LValue String1, String2;
12074  if (!EvaluatePointer(E->getArg(0), String1, Info) ||
12075  !EvaluatePointer(E->getArg(1), String2, Info))
12076  return false;
12077 
12078  uint64_t MaxLength = uint64_t(-1);
12079  if (BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIstrcmp &&
12080  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIwcscmp &&
12081  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_strcmp &&
12082  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_wcscmp) {
12083  APSInt N;
12084  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(2), N, Info))
12085  return false;
12086  MaxLength = N.getExtValue();
12087  }
12088 
12089  // Empty substrings compare equal by definition.
12090  if (MaxLength == 0u)
12091  return Success(0, E);
12092 
12093  if (!String1.checkNullPointerForFoldAccess(Info, E, AK_Read) ||
12094  !String2.checkNullPointerForFoldAccess(Info, E, AK_Read) ||
12095  String1.Designator.Invalid || String2.Designator.Invalid)
12096  return false;
12097 
12098  QualType CharTy1 = String1.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx);
12099  QualType CharTy2 = String2.Designator.getType(Info.Ctx);
12100 
12101  bool IsRawByte = BuiltinOp == Builtin::BImemcmp ||
12102  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIbcmp ||
12103  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_memcmp ||
12104  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_bcmp;
12105 
12106  assert(IsRawByte ||
12107  (Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
12108  CharTy1, E->getArg(0)->getType()->getPointeeType()) &&
12109  Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(CharTy1, CharTy2)));
12110 
12111  // For memcmp, allow comparing any arrays of '[[un]signed] char' or
12112  // 'char8_t', but no other types.
12113  if (IsRawByte &&
12114  !(isOneByteCharacterType(CharTy1) && isOneByteCharacterType(CharTy2))) {
12115  // FIXME: Consider using our bit_cast implementation to support this.
12116  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_memcmp_unsupported)
12117  << (std::string("'") + Info.Ctx.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinOp) + "'")
12118  << CharTy1 << CharTy2;
12119  return false;
12120  }
12121 
12122  const auto &ReadCurElems = [&](APValue &Char1, APValue &Char2) {
12123  return handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, CharTy1, String1, Char1) &&
12124  handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, CharTy2, String2, Char2) &&
12125  Char1.isInt() && Char2.isInt();
12126  };
12127  const auto &AdvanceElems = [&] {
12128  return HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, String1, CharTy1, 1) &&
12129  HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, String2, CharTy2, 1);
12130  };
12131 
12132  bool StopAtNull =
12133  (BuiltinOp != Builtin::BImemcmp && BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIbcmp &&
12134  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BIwmemcmp &&
12135  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_memcmp &&
12136  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_bcmp &&
12137  BuiltinOp != Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcmp);
12138  bool IsWide = BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwcscmp ||
12139  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwcsncmp ||
12140  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BIwmemcmp ||
12141  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wcscmp ||
12142  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wcsncmp ||
12143  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_wmemcmp;
12144 
12145  for (; MaxLength; --MaxLength) {
12146  APValue Char1, Char2;
12147  if (!ReadCurElems(Char1, Char2))
12148  return false;
12149  if (Char1.getInt().ne(Char2.getInt())) {
12150  if (IsWide) // wmemcmp compares with wchar_t signedness.
12151  return Success(Char1.getInt() < Char2.getInt() ? -1 : 1, E);
12152  // memcmp always compares unsigned chars.
12153  return Success(Char1.getInt().ult(Char2.getInt()) ? -1 : 1, E);
12154  }
12155  if (StopAtNull && !Char1.getInt())
12156  return Success(0, E);
12157  assert(!(StopAtNull && !Char2.getInt()));
12158  if (!AdvanceElems())
12159  return false;
12160  }
12161  // We hit the strncmp / memcmp limit.
12162  return Success(0, E);
12163  }
12164 
12165  case Builtin::BI__atomic_always_lock_free:
12166  case Builtin::BI__atomic_is_lock_free:
12167  case Builtin::BI__c11_atomic_is_lock_free: {
12168  APSInt SizeVal;
12169  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(0), SizeVal, Info))
12170  return false;
12171 
12172  // For __atomic_is_lock_free(sizeof(_Atomic(T))), if the size is a power
12173  // of two less than or equal to the maximum inline atomic width, we know it
12174  // is lock-free. If the size isn't a power of two, or greater than the
12175  // maximum alignment where we promote atomics, we know it is not lock-free
12176  // (at least not in the sense of atomic_is_lock_free). Otherwise,
12177  // the answer can only be determined at runtime; for example, 16-byte
12178  // atomics have lock-free implementations on some, but not all,
12179  // x86-64 processors.
12180 
12181  // Check power-of-two.
12182  CharUnits Size = CharUnits::fromQuantity(SizeVal.getZExtValue());
12183  if (Size.isPowerOfTwo()) {
12184  // Check against inlining width.
12185  unsigned InlineWidthBits =
12186  Info.Ctx.getTargetInfo().getMaxAtomicInlineWidth();
12187  if (Size <= Info.Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(InlineWidthBits)) {
12188  if (BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__c11_atomic_is_lock_free ||
12189  Size == CharUnits::One() ||
12190  E->getArg(1)->isNullPointerConstant(Info.Ctx,
12191  Expr::NPC_NeverValueDependent))
12192  // OK, we will inline appropriately-aligned operations of this size,
12193  // and _Atomic(T) is appropriately-aligned.
12194  return Success(1, E);
12195 
12196  QualType PointeeType = E->getArg(1)->IgnoreImpCasts()->getType()->
12197  castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
12198  if (!PointeeType->isIncompleteType() &&
12199  Info.Ctx.getTypeAlignInChars(PointeeType) >= Size) {
12200  // OK, we will inline operations on this object.
12201  return Success(1, E);
12202  }
12203  }
12204  }
12205 
12206  return BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__atomic_always_lock_free ?
12207  Success(0, E) : Error(E);
12208  }
12209  case Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow:
12210  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow:
12211  case Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow:
12212  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sadd_overflow:
12213  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uadd_overflow:
12214  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddl_overflow:
12215  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddll_overflow:
12216  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usub_overflow:
12217  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubl_overflow:
12218  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubll_overflow:
12219  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umul_overflow:
12220  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umull_overflow:
12221  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umulll_overflow:
12222  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddl_overflow:
12223  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddll_overflow:
12224  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssub_overflow:
12225  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubl_overflow:
12226  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubll_overflow:
12227  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smul_overflow:
12228  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smull_overflow:
12229  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smulll_overflow: {
12230  LValue ResultLValue;
12231  APSInt LHS, RHS;
12232 
12233  QualType ResultType = E->getArg(2)->getType()->getPointeeType();
12234  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(0), LHS, Info) ||
12235  !EvaluateInteger(E->getArg(1), RHS, Info) ||
12236  !EvaluatePointer(E->getArg(2), ResultLValue, Info))
12237  return false;
12238 
12239  APSInt Result;
12240  bool DidOverflow = false;
12241 
12242  // If the types don't have to match, enlarge all 3 to the largest of them.
12243  if (BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow ||
12244  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow ||
12245  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow) {
12246  bool IsSigned = LHS.isSigned() || RHS.isSigned() ||
12247  ResultType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
12248  bool AllSigned = LHS.isSigned() && RHS.isSigned() &&
12249  ResultType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
12250  uint64_t LHSSize = LHS.getBitWidth();
12251  uint64_t RHSSize = RHS.getBitWidth();
12252  uint64_t ResultSize = Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(ResultType);
12253  uint64_t MaxBits = std::max(std::max(LHSSize, RHSSize), ResultSize);
12254 
12255  // Add an additional bit if the signedness isn't uniformly agreed to. We
12256  // could do this ONLY if there is a signed and an unsigned that both have
12257  // MaxBits, but the code to check that is pretty nasty. The issue will be
12258  // caught in the shrink-to-result later anyway.
12259  if (IsSigned && !AllSigned)
12260  ++MaxBits;
12261 
12262  LHS = APSInt(LHS.extOrTrunc(MaxBits), !IsSigned);
12263  RHS = APSInt(RHS.extOrTrunc(MaxBits), !IsSigned);
12264  Result = APSInt(MaxBits, !IsSigned);
12265  }
12266 
12267  // Find largest int.
12268  switch (BuiltinOp) {
12269  default:
12270  llvm_unreachable("Invalid value for BuiltinOp");
12271  case Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow:
12272  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sadd_overflow:
12273  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddl_overflow:
12274  case Builtin::BI__builtin_saddll_overflow:
12275  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uadd_overflow:
12276  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddl_overflow:
12277  case Builtin::BI__builtin_uaddll_overflow:
12278  Result = LHS.isSigned() ? LHS.sadd_ov(RHS, DidOverflow)
12279  : LHS.uadd_ov(RHS, DidOverflow);
12280  break;
12281  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow:
12282  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssub_overflow:
12283  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubl_overflow:
12284  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ssubll_overflow:
12285  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usub_overflow:
12286  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubl_overflow:
12287  case Builtin::BI__builtin_usubll_overflow:
12288  Result = LHS.isSigned() ? LHS.ssub_ov(RHS, DidOverflow)
12289  : LHS.usub_ov(RHS, DidOverflow);
12290  break;
12291  case Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow:
12292  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smul_overflow:
12293  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smull_overflow:
12294  case Builtin::BI__builtin_smulll_overflow:
12295  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umul_overflow:
12296  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umull_overflow:
12297  case Builtin::BI__builtin_umulll_overflow:
12298  Result = LHS.isSigned() ? LHS.smul_ov(RHS, DidOverflow)
12299  : LHS.umul_ov(RHS, DidOverflow);
12300  break;
12301  }
12302 
12303  // In the case where multiple sizes are allowed, truncate and see if
12304  // the values are the same.
12305  if (BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_add_overflow ||
12306  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_sub_overflow ||
12307  BuiltinOp == Builtin::BI__builtin_mul_overflow) {
12308  // APSInt doesn't have a TruncOrSelf, so we use extOrTrunc instead,
12309  // since it will give us the behavior of a TruncOrSelf in the case where
12310  // its parameter <= its size. We previously set Result to be at least the
12311  // type-size of the result, so getTypeSize(ResultType) <= Result.BitWidth
12312  // will work exactly like TruncOrSelf.
12313  APSInt Temp = Result.extOrTrunc(Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(ResultType));
12314  Temp.setIsSigned(ResultType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
12315 
12316  if (!APSInt::isSameValue(Temp, Result))
12317  DidOverflow = true;
12318  Result = Temp;
12319  }
12320 
12321  APValue APV{Result};
12322  if (!handleAssignment(Info, E, ResultLValue, ResultType, APV))
12323  return false;
12324  return Success(DidOverflow, E);
12325  }
12326  }
12327 }
12328 
12329 /// Determine whether this is a pointer past the end of the complete
12330 /// object referred to by the lvalue.
12331 static bool isOnePastTheEndOfCompleteObject(const ASTContext &Ctx,
12332  const LValue &LV) {
12333  // A null pointer can be viewed as being "past the end" but we don't
12334  // choose to look at it that way here.
12335  if (!LV.getLValueBase())
12336  return false;
12337 
12338  // If the designator is valid and refers to a subobject, we're not pointing
12339  // past the end.
12340  if (!LV.getLValueDesignator().Invalid &&
12341  !LV.getLValueDesignator().isOnePastTheEnd())
12342  return false;
12343 
12344  // A pointer to an incomplete type might be past-the-end if the type's size is
12345  // zero. We cannot tell because the type is incomplete.
12346  QualType Ty = getType(LV.getLValueBase());
12347  if (Ty->isIncompleteType())
12348  return true;
12349 
12350  // We're a past-the-end pointer if we point to the byte after the object,
12351  // no matter what our type or path is.
12352  auto Size = Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
12353  return LV.getLValueOffset() == Size;
12354 }
12355 
12356 namespace {
12357 
12358 /// Data recursive integer evaluator of certain binary operators.
12359 ///
12360 /// We use a data recursive algorithm for binary operators so that we are able
12361 /// to handle extreme cases of chained binary operators without causing stack
12362 /// overflow.
12363 class DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator {
12364  struct EvalResult {
12365  APValue Val;
12366  bool Failed;
12367 
12368  EvalResult() : Failed(false) { }
12369 
12370  void swap(EvalResult &RHS) {
12371  Val.swap(RHS.Val);
12372  Failed = RHS.Failed;
12373  RHS.Failed = false;
12374  }
12375  };
12376 
12377  struct Job {
12378  const Expr *E;
12379  EvalResult LHSResult; // meaningful only for binary operator expression.
12380  enum { AnyExprKind, BinOpKind, BinOpVisitedLHSKind } Kind;
12381 
12382  Job() = default;
12383  Job(Job &&) = default;
12384 
12385  void startSpeculativeEval(EvalInfo &Info) {
12386  SpecEvalRAII = SpeculativeEvaluationRAII(Info);
12387  }
12388 
12389  private:
12390  SpeculativeEvaluationRAII SpecEvalRAII;
12391  };
12392 
12393  SmallVector<Job, 16> Queue;
12394 
12395  IntExprEvaluator &IntEval;
12396  EvalInfo &Info;
12397  APValue &FinalResult;
12398 
12399 public:
12400  DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator(IntExprEvaluator &IntEval, APValue &Result)
12401  : IntEval(IntEval), Info(IntEval.getEvalInfo()), FinalResult(Result) { }
12402 
12403  /// True if \param E is a binary operator that we are going to handle
12404  /// data recursively.
12405  /// We handle binary operators that are comma, logical, or that have operands
12406  /// with integral or enumeration type.
12407  static bool shouldEnqueue(const BinaryOperator *E) {
12408  return E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma || E->isLogicalOp() ||
12409  (E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
12410  E->getLHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
12411  E->getRHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType());
12412  }
12413 
12414  bool Traverse(const BinaryOperator *E) {
12415  enqueue(E);
12416  EvalResult PrevResult;
12417  while (!Queue.empty())
12418  process(PrevResult);
12419 
12420  if (PrevResult.Failed) return false;
12421 
12422  FinalResult.swap(PrevResult.Val);
12423  return true;
12424  }
12425 
12426 private:
12427  bool Success(uint64_t Value, const Expr *E, APValue &Result) {
12428  return IntEval.Success(Value, E, Result);
12429  }
12430  bool Success(const APSInt &Value, const Expr *E, APValue &Result) {
12431  return IntEval.Success(Value, E, Result);
12432  }
12433  bool Error(const Expr *E) {
12434  return IntEval.Error(E);
12435  }
12436  bool Error(const Expr *E, diag::kind D) {
12437  return IntEval.Error(E, D);
12438  }
12439 
12440  OptionalDiagnostic CCEDiag(const Expr *E, diag::kind D) {
12441  return Info.CCEDiag(E, D);
12442  }
12443 
12444  // Returns true if visiting the RHS is necessary, false otherwise.
12445  bool VisitBinOpLHSOnly(EvalResult &LHSResult, const BinaryOperator *E,
12446  bool &SuppressRHSDiags);
12447 
12448  bool VisitBinOp(const EvalResult &LHSResult, const EvalResult &RHSResult,
12449  const BinaryOperator *E, APValue &Result);
12450 
12451  void EvaluateExpr(const Expr *E, EvalResult &Result) {
12452  Result.Failed = !Evaluate(Result.Val, Info, E);
12453  if (Result.Failed)
12454  Result.Val = APValue();
12455  }
12456 
12457  void process(EvalResult &Result);
12458 
12459  void enqueue(const Expr *E) {
12460  E = E->IgnoreParens();
12461  Queue.resize(Queue.size()+1);
12462  Queue.back().E = E;
12463  Queue.back().Kind = Job::AnyExprKind;
12464  }
12465 };
12466 
12467 }
12468 
12469 bool DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator::
12470  VisitBinOpLHSOnly(EvalResult &LHSResult, const BinaryOperator *E,
12471  bool &SuppressRHSDiags) {
12472  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
12473  // Ignore LHS but note if we could not evaluate it.
12474  if (LHSResult.Failed)
12475  return Info.noteSideEffect();
12476  return true;
12477  }
12478 
12479  if (E->isLogicalOp()) {
12480  bool LHSAsBool;
12481  if (!LHSResult.Failed && HandleConversionToBool(LHSResult.Val, LHSAsBool)) {
12482  // We were able to evaluate the LHS, see if we can get away with not
12483  // evaluating the RHS: 0 && X -> 0, 1 || X -> 1
12484  if (LHSAsBool == (E->getOpcode() == BO_LOr)) {
12485  Success(LHSAsBool, E, LHSResult.Val);
12486  return false; // Ignore RHS
12487  }
12488  } else {
12489  LHSResult.Failed = true;
12490 
12491  // Since we weren't able to evaluate the left hand side, it
12492  // might have had side effects.
12493  if (!Info.noteSideEffect())
12494  return false;
12495 
12496  // We can't evaluate the LHS; however, sometimes the result
12497  // is determined by the RHS: X && 0 -> 0, X || 1 -> 1.
12498  // Don't ignore RHS and suppress diagnostics from this arm.
12499  SuppressRHSDiags = true;
12500  }
12501 
12502  return true;
12503  }
12504 
12505  assert(E->getLHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
12506  E->getRHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType());
12507 
12508  if (LHSResult.Failed && !Info.noteFailure())
12509  return false; // Ignore RHS;
12510 
12511  return true;
12512 }
12513 
12514 static void addOrSubLValueAsInteger(APValue &LVal, const APSInt &Index,
12515  bool IsSub) {
12516  // Compute the new offset in the appropriate width, wrapping at 64 bits.
12517  // FIXME: When compiling for a 32-bit target, we should use 32-bit
12518  // offsets.
12519  assert(!LVal.hasLValuePath() && "have designator for integer lvalue");
12520  CharUnits &Offset = LVal.getLValueOffset();
12521  uint64_t Offset64 = Offset.getQuantity();
12522  uint64_t Index64 = Index.extOrTrunc(64).getZExtValue();
12523  Offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(IsSub ? Offset64 - Index64
12524  : Offset64 + Index64);
12525 }
12526 
12527 bool DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator::
12528  VisitBinOp(const EvalResult &LHSResult, const EvalResult &RHSResult,
12529  const BinaryOperator *E, APValue &Result) {
12530  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
12531  if (RHSResult.Failed)
12532  return false;
12533  Result = RHSResult.Val;
12534  return true;
12535  }
12536 
12537  if (E->isLogicalOp()) {
12538  bool lhsResult, rhsResult;
12539  bool LHSIsOK = HandleConversionToBool(LHSResult.Val, lhsResult);
12540  bool RHSIsOK = HandleConversionToBool(RHSResult.Val, rhsResult);
12541 
12542  if (LHSIsOK) {
12543  if (RHSIsOK) {
12544  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_LOr)
12545  return Success(lhsResult || rhsResult, E, Result);
12546  else
12547  return Success(lhsResult && rhsResult, E, Result);
12548  }
12549  } else {
12550  if (RHSIsOK) {
12551  // We can't evaluate the LHS; however, sometimes the result
12552  // is determined by the RHS: X && 0 -> 0, X || 1 -> 1.
12553  if (rhsResult == (E->getOpcode() == BO_LOr))
12554  return Success(rhsResult, E, Result);
12555  }
12556  }
12557 
12558  return false;
12559  }
12560 
12561  assert(E->getLHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
12562  E->getRHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType());
12563 
12564  if (LHSResult.Failed || RHSResult.Failed)
12565  return false;
12566 
12567  const APValue &LHSVal = LHSResult.Val;
12568  const APValue &RHSVal = RHSResult.Val;
12569 
12570  // Handle cases like (unsigned long)&a + 4.
12571  if (E->isAdditiveOp() && LHSVal.isLValue() && RHSVal.isInt()) {
12572  Result = LHSVal;
12573  addOrSubLValueAsInteger(Result, RHSVal.getInt(), E->getOpcode() == BO_Sub);
12574  return true;
12575  }
12576 
12577  // Handle cases like 4 + (unsigned long)&a
12578  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Add &&
12579  RHSVal.isLValue() && LHSVal.isInt()) {
12580  Result = RHSVal;
12581  addOrSubLValueAsInteger(Result, LHSVal.getInt(), /*IsSub*/false);
12582  return true;
12583  }
12584 
12585  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Sub && LHSVal.isLValue() && RHSVal.isLValue()) {
12586  // Handle (intptr_t)&&A - (intptr_t)&&B.
12587  if (!LHSVal.getLValueOffset().isZero() ||
12588  !RHSVal.getLValueOffset().isZero())
12589  return false;
12590  const Expr *LHSExpr = LHSVal.getLValueBase().dyn_cast<const Expr*>();
12591  const Expr *RHSExpr = RHSVal.getLValueBase().dyn_cast<const Expr*>();
12592  if (!LHSExpr || !RHSExpr)
12593  return false;
12594  const AddrLabelExpr *LHSAddrExpr = dyn_cast<AddrLabelExpr>(LHSExpr);
12595  const AddrLabelExpr *RHSAddrExpr = dyn_cast<AddrLabelExpr>(RHSExpr);
12596  if (!LHSAddrExpr || !RHSAddrExpr)
12597  return false;
12598  // Make sure both labels come from the same function.
12599  if (LHSAddrExpr->getLabel()->getDeclContext() !=
12600  RHSAddrExpr->getLabel()->getDeclContext())
12601  return false;
12602  Result = APValue(LHSAddrExpr, RHSAddrExpr);
12603  return true;
12604  }
12605 
12606  // All the remaining cases expect both operands to be an integer
12607  if (!LHSVal.isInt() || !RHSVal.isInt())
12608  return Error(E);
12609 
12610  // Set up the width and signedness manually, in case it can't be deduced
12611  // from the operation we're performing.
12612  // FIXME: Don't do this in the cases where we can deduce it.
12613  APSInt Value(Info.Ctx.getIntWidth(E->getType()),
12614  E->getType()->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
12615  if (!handleIntIntBinOp(Info, E, LHSVal.getInt(), E->getOpcode(),
12616  RHSVal.getInt(), Value))
12617  return false;
12618  return Success(Value, E, Result);
12619 }
12620 
12621 void DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator::process(EvalResult &Result) {
12622  Job &job = Queue.back();
12623 
12624  switch (job.Kind) {
12625  case Job::AnyExprKind: {
12626  if (const BinaryOperator *Bop = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(job.E)) {
12627  if (shouldEnqueue(Bop)) {
12628  job.Kind = Job::BinOpKind;
12629  enqueue(Bop->getLHS());
12630  return;
12631  }
12632  }
12633 
12634  EvaluateExpr(job.E, Result);
12635  Queue.pop_back();
12636  return;
12637  }
12638 
12639  case Job::BinOpKind: {
12640  const BinaryOperator *Bop = cast<BinaryOperator>(job.E);
12641  bool SuppressRHSDiags = false;
12642  if (!VisitBinOpLHSOnly(Result, Bop, SuppressRHSDiags)) {
12643  Queue.pop_back();
12644  return;
12645  }
12646  if (SuppressRHSDiags)
12647  job.startSpeculativeEval(Info);
12648  job.LHSResult.swap(Result);
12649  job.Kind = Job::BinOpVisitedLHSKind;
12650  enqueue(Bop->getRHS());
12651  return;
12652  }
12653 
12654  case Job::BinOpVisitedLHSKind: {
12655  const BinaryOperator *Bop = cast<BinaryOperator>(job.E);
12656  EvalResult RHS;
12657  RHS.swap(Result);
12658  Result.Failed = !VisitBinOp(job.LHSResult, RHS, Bop, Result.Val);
12659  Queue.pop_back();
12660  return;
12661  }
12662  }
12663 
12664  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Job::Kind!");
12665 }
12666 
12667 namespace {
12668 enum class CmpResult {
12669  Unequal,
12670  Less,
12671  Equal,
12672  Greater,
12673  Unordered,
12674 };
12675 }
12676 
12677 template <class SuccessCB, class AfterCB>
12678 static bool
12679 EvaluateComparisonBinaryOperator(EvalInfo &Info, const BinaryOperator *E,
12680  SuccessCB &&Success, AfterCB &&DoAfter) {
12681  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
12682  assert(E->isComparisonOp() && "expected comparison operator");
12683  assert((E->getOpcode() == BO_Cmp ||
12684  E->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) &&
12685  "unsupported binary expression evaluation");
12686  auto Error = [&](const Expr *E) {
12687  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_invalid_subexpr_in_const_expr);
12688  return false;
12689  };
12690 
12691  bool IsRelational = E->isRelationalOp() || E->getOpcode() == BO_Cmp;
12692  bool IsEquality = E->isEqualityOp();
12693 
12694  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
12695  QualType RHSTy = E->getRHS()->getType();
12696 
12697  if (LHSTy->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
12698  RHSTy->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
12699  APSInt LHS, RHS;
12700  bool LHSOK = EvaluateInteger(E->getLHS(), LHS, Info);
12701  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12702  return false;
12703  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getRHS(), RHS, Info) || !LHSOK)
12704  return false;
12705  if (LHS < RHS)
12706  return Success(CmpResult::Less, E);
12707  if (LHS > RHS)
12708  return Success(CmpResult::Greater, E);
12709  return Success(CmpResult::Equal, E);
12710  }
12711 
12712  if (LHSTy->isFixedPointType() || RHSTy->isFixedPointType()) {
12713  APFixedPoint LHSFX(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(LHSTy));
12714  APFixedPoint RHSFX(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(RHSTy));
12715 
12716  bool LHSOK = EvaluateFixedPointOrInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSFX, Info);
12717  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12718  return false;
12719  if (!EvaluateFixedPointOrInteger(E->getRHS(), RHSFX, Info) || !LHSOK)
12720  return false;
12721  if (LHSFX < RHSFX)
12722  return Success(CmpResult::Less, E);
12723  if (LHSFX > RHSFX)
12724  return Success(CmpResult::Greater, E);
12725  return Success(CmpResult::Equal, E);
12726  }
12727 
12728  if (LHSTy->isAnyComplexType() || RHSTy->isAnyComplexType()) {
12729  ComplexValue LHS, RHS;
12730  bool LHSOK;
12731  if (E->isAssignmentOp()) {
12732  LValue LV;
12733  EvaluateLValue(E->getLHS(), LV, Info);
12734  LHSOK = false;
12735  } else if (LHSTy->isRealFloatingType()) {
12736  LHSOK = EvaluateFloat(E->getLHS(), LHS.FloatReal, Info);
12737  if (LHSOK) {
12738  LHS.makeComplexFloat();
12739  LHS.FloatImag = APFloat(LHS.FloatReal.getSemantics());
12740  }
12741  } else {
12742  LHSOK = EvaluateComplex(E->getLHS(), LHS, Info);
12743  }
12744  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12745  return false;
12746 
12747  if (E->getRHS()->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
12748  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getRHS(), RHS.FloatReal, Info) || !LHSOK)
12749  return false;
12750  RHS.makeComplexFloat();
12751  RHS.FloatImag = APFloat(RHS.FloatReal.getSemantics());
12752  } else if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getRHS(), RHS, Info) || !LHSOK)
12753  return false;
12754 
12755  if (LHS.isComplexFloat()) {
12756  APFloat::cmpResult CR_r =
12757  LHS.getComplexFloatReal().compare(RHS.getComplexFloatReal());
12758  APFloat::cmpResult CR_i =
12759  LHS.getComplexFloatImag().compare(RHS.getComplexFloatImag());
12760  bool IsEqual = CR_r == APFloat::cmpEqual && CR_i == APFloat::cmpEqual;
12761  return Success(IsEqual ? CmpResult::Equal : CmpResult::Unequal, E);
12762  } else {
12763  assert(IsEquality && "invalid complex comparison");
12764  bool IsEqual = LHS.getComplexIntReal() == RHS.getComplexIntReal() &&
12765  LHS.getComplexIntImag() == RHS.getComplexIntImag();
12766  return Success(IsEqual ? CmpResult::Equal : CmpResult::Unequal, E);
12767  }
12768  }
12769 
12770  if (LHSTy->isRealFloatingType() &&
12771  RHSTy->isRealFloatingType()) {
12772  APFloat RHS(0.0), LHS(0.0);
12773 
12774  bool LHSOK = EvaluateFloat(E->getRHS(), RHS, Info);
12775  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12776  return false;
12777 
12778  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getLHS(), LHS, Info) || !LHSOK)
12779  return false;
12780 
12781  assert(E->isComparisonOp() && "Invalid binary operator!");
12782  llvm::APFloatBase::cmpResult APFloatCmpResult = LHS.compare(RHS);
12783  if (!Info.InConstantContext &&
12784  APFloatCmpResult == APFloat::cmpUnordered &&
12785  E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(Info.Ctx.getLangOpts()).isFPConstrained()) {
12786  // Note: Compares may raise invalid in some cases involving NaN or sNaN.
12787  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_float_arithmetic_strict);
12788  return false;
12789  }
12790  auto GetCmpRes = [&]() {
12791  switch (APFloatCmpResult) {
12792  case APFloat::cmpEqual:
12793  return CmpResult::Equal;
12794  case APFloat::cmpLessThan:
12795  return CmpResult::Less;
12796  case APFloat::cmpGreaterThan:
12797  return CmpResult::Greater;
12798  case APFloat::cmpUnordered:
12799  return CmpResult::Unordered;
12800  }
12801  llvm_unreachable("Unrecognised APFloat::cmpResult enum");
12802  };
12803  return Success(GetCmpRes(), E);
12804  }
12805 
12806  if (LHSTy->isPointerType() && RHSTy->isPointerType()) {
12807  LValue LHSValue, RHSValue;
12808 
12809  bool LHSOK = EvaluatePointer(E->getLHS(), LHSValue, Info);
12810  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12811  return false;
12812 
12813  if (!EvaluatePointer(E->getRHS(), RHSValue, Info) || !LHSOK)
12814  return false;
12815 
12816  // Reject differing bases from the normal codepath; we special-case
12817  // comparisons to null.
12818  if (!HasSameBase(LHSValue, RHSValue)) {
12819  // Inequalities and subtractions between unrelated pointers have
12820  // unspecified or undefined behavior.
12821  if (!IsEquality) {
12822  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_comparison_unspecified);
12823  return false;
12824  }
12825  // A constant address may compare equal to the address of a symbol.
12826  // The one exception is that address of an object cannot compare equal
12827  // to a null pointer constant.
12828  if ((!LHSValue.Base && !LHSValue.Offset.isZero()) ||
12829  (!RHSValue.Base && !RHSValue.Offset.isZero()))
12830  return Error(E);
12831  // It's implementation-defined whether distinct literals will have
12832  // distinct addresses. In clang, the result of such a comparison is
12833  // unspecified, so it is not a constant expression. However, we do know
12834  // that the address of a literal will be non-null.
12835  if ((IsLiteralLValue(LHSValue) || IsLiteralLValue(RHSValue)) &&
12836  LHSValue.Base && RHSValue.Base)
12837  return Error(E);
12838  // We can't tell whether weak symbols will end up pointing to the same
12839  // object.
12840  if (IsWeakLValue(LHSValue) || IsWeakLValue(RHSValue))
12841  return Error(E);
12842  // We can't compare the address of the start of one object with the
12843  // past-the-end address of another object, per C++ DR1652.
12844  if ((LHSValue.Base && LHSValue.Offset.isZero() &&
12845  isOnePastTheEndOfCompleteObject(Info.Ctx, RHSValue)) ||
12846  (RHSValue.Base && RHSValue.Offset.isZero() &&
12847  isOnePastTheEndOfCompleteObject(Info.Ctx, LHSValue)))
12848  return Error(E);
12849  // We can't tell whether an object is at the same address as another
12850  // zero sized object.
12851  if ((RHSValue.Base && isZeroSized(LHSValue)) ||
12852  (LHSValue.Base && isZeroSized(RHSValue)))
12853  return Error(E);
12854  return Success(CmpResult::Unequal, E);
12855  }
12856 
12857  const CharUnits &LHSOffset = LHSValue.getLValueOffset();
12858  const CharUnits &RHSOffset = RHSValue.getLValueOffset();
12859 
12860  SubobjectDesignator &LHSDesignator = LHSValue.getLValueDesignator();
12861  SubobjectDesignator &RHSDesignator = RHSValue.getLValueDesignator();
12862 
12863  // C++11 [expr.rel]p3:
12864  // Pointers to void (after pointer conversions) can be compared, with a
12865  // result defined as follows: If both pointers represent the same
12866  // address or are both the null pointer value, the result is true if the
12867  // operator is <= or >= and false otherwise; otherwise the result is
12868  // unspecified.
12869  // We interpret this as applying to pointers to *cv* void.
12870  if (LHSTy->isVoidPointerType() && LHSOffset != RHSOffset && IsRelational)
12871  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_void_comparison);
12872 
12873  // C++11 [expr.rel]p2:
12874  // - If two pointers point to non-static data members of the same object,
12875  // or to subobjects or array elements fo such members, recursively, the
12876  // pointer to the later declared member compares greater provided the
12877  // two members have the same access control and provided their class is
12878  // not a union.
12879  // [...]
12880  // - Otherwise pointer comparisons are unspecified.
12881  if (!LHSDesignator.Invalid && !RHSDesignator.Invalid && IsRelational) {
12882  bool WasArrayIndex;
12883  unsigned Mismatch = FindDesignatorMismatch(
12884  getType(LHSValue.Base), LHSDesignator, RHSDesignator, WasArrayIndex);
12885  // At the point where the designators diverge, the comparison has a
12886  // specified value if:
12887  // - we are comparing array indices
12888  // - we are comparing fields of a union, or fields with the same access
12889  // Otherwise, the result is unspecified and thus the comparison is not a
12890  // constant expression.
12891  if (!WasArrayIndex && Mismatch < LHSDesignator.Entries.size() &&
12892  Mismatch < RHSDesignator.Entries.size()) {
12893  const FieldDecl *LF = getAsField(LHSDesignator.Entries[Mismatch]);
12894  const FieldDecl *RF = getAsField(RHSDesignator.Entries[Mismatch]);
12895  if (!LF && !RF)
12896  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_comparison_base_classes);
12897  else if (!LF)
12898  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_comparison_base_field)
12899  << getAsBaseClass(LHSDesignator.Entries[Mismatch])
12900  << RF->getParent() << RF;
12901  else if (!RF)
12902  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_comparison_base_field)
12903  << getAsBaseClass(RHSDesignator.Entries[Mismatch])
12904  << LF->getParent() << LF;
12905  else if (!LF->getParent()->isUnion() &&
12906  LF->getAccess() != RF->getAccess())
12907  Info.CCEDiag(E,
12908  diag::note_constexpr_pointer_comparison_differing_access)
12909  << LF << LF->getAccess() << RF << RF->getAccess()
12910  << LF->getParent();
12911  }
12912  }
12913 
12914  // The comparison here must be unsigned, and performed with the same
12915  // width as the pointer.
12916  unsigned PtrSize = Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(LHSTy);
12917  uint64_t CompareLHS = LHSOffset.getQuantity();
12918  uint64_t CompareRHS = RHSOffset.getQuantity();
12919  assert(PtrSize <= 64 && "Unexpected pointer width");
12920  uint64_t Mask = ~0ULL >> (64 - PtrSize);
12921  CompareLHS &= Mask;
12922  CompareRHS &= Mask;
12923 
12924  // If there is a base and this is a relational operator, we can only
12925  // compare pointers within the object in question; otherwise, the result
12926  // depends on where the object is located in memory.
12927  if (!LHSValue.Base.isNull() && IsRelational) {
12928  QualType BaseTy = getType(LHSValue.Base);
12929  if (BaseTy->isIncompleteType())
12930  return Error(E);
12931  CharUnits Size = Info.Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(BaseTy);
12932  uint64_t OffsetLimit = Size.getQuantity();
12933  if (CompareLHS > OffsetLimit || CompareRHS > OffsetLimit)
12934  return Error(E);
12935  }
12936 
12937  if (CompareLHS < CompareRHS)
12938  return Success(CmpResult::Less, E);
12939  if (CompareLHS > CompareRHS)
12940  return Success(CmpResult::Greater, E);
12941  return Success(CmpResult::Equal, E);
12942  }
12943 
12944  if (LHSTy->isMemberPointerType()) {
12945  assert(IsEquality && "unexpected member pointer operation");
12946  assert(RHSTy->isMemberPointerType() && "invalid comparison");
12947 
12948  MemberPtr LHSValue, RHSValue;
12949 
12950  bool LHSOK = EvaluateMemberPointer(E->getLHS(), LHSValue, Info);
12951  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
12952  return false;
12953 
12954  if (!EvaluateMemberPointer(E->getRHS(), RHSValue, Info) || !LHSOK)
12955  return false;
12956 
12957  // C++11 [expr.eq]p2:
12958  // If both operands are null, they compare equal. Otherwise if only one is
12959  // null, they compare unequal.
12960  if (!LHSValue.getDecl() || !RHSValue.getDecl()) {
12961  bool Equal = !LHSValue.getDecl() && !RHSValue.getDecl();
12962  return Success(Equal ? CmpResult::Equal : CmpResult::Unequal, E);
12963  }
12964 
12965  // Otherwise if either is a pointer to a virtual member function, the
12966  // result is unspecified.
12967  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(LHSValue.getDecl()))
12968  if (MD->isVirtual())
12969  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_compare_virtual_mem_ptr) << MD;
12970  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(RHSValue.getDecl()))
12971  if (MD->isVirtual())
12972  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_compare_virtual_mem_ptr) << MD;
12973 
12974  // Otherwise they compare equal if and only if they would refer to the
12975  // same member of the same most derived object or the same subobject if
12976  // they were dereferenced with a hypothetical object of the associated
12977  // class type.
12978  bool Equal = LHSValue == RHSValue;
12979  return Success(Equal ? CmpResult::Equal : CmpResult::Unequal, E);
12980  }
12981 
12982  if (LHSTy->isNullPtrType()) {
12983  assert(E->isComparisonOp() && "unexpected nullptr operation");
12984  assert(RHSTy->isNullPtrType() && "missing pointer conversion");
12985  // C++11 [expr.rel]p4, [expr.eq]p3: If two operands of type std::nullptr_t
12986  // are compared, the result is true of the operator is <=, >= or ==, and
12987  // false otherwise.
12988  return Success(CmpResult::Equal, E);
12989  }
12990 
12991  return DoAfter();
12992 }
12993 
12994 bool RecordExprEvaluator::VisitBinCmp(const BinaryOperator *E) {
12995  if (!CheckLiteralType(Info, E))
12996  return false;
12997 
12998  auto OnSuccess = [&](CmpResult CR, const BinaryOperator *E) {
12999  ComparisonCategoryResult CCR;
13000  switch (CR) {
13001  case CmpResult::Unequal:
13002  llvm_unreachable("should never produce Unequal for three-way comparison");
13003  case CmpResult::Less:
13004  CCR = ComparisonCategoryResult::Less;
13005  break;
13006  case CmpResult::Equal:
13007  CCR = ComparisonCategoryResult::Equal;
13008  break;
13009  case CmpResult::Greater:
13010  CCR = ComparisonCategoryResult::Greater;
13011  break;
13012  case CmpResult::Unordered:
13013  CCR = ComparisonCategoryResult::Unordered;
13014  break;
13015  }
13016  // Evaluation succeeded. Lookup the information for the comparison category
13017  // type and fetch the VarDecl for the result.
13018  const ComparisonCategoryInfo &CmpInfo =
13019  Info.Ctx.CompCategories.getInfoForType(E->getType());
13020  const VarDecl *VD = CmpInfo.getValueInfo(CmpInfo.makeWeakResult(CCR))->VD;
13021  // Check and evaluate the result as a constant expression.
13022  LValue LV;
13023  LV.set(VD);
13024  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, E->getType(), LV, Result))
13025  return false;
13026  return CheckConstantExpression(Info, E->getExprLoc(), E->getType(), Result,
13027  ConstantExprKind::Normal);
13028  };
13029  return EvaluateComparisonBinaryOperator(Info, E, OnSuccess, [&]() {
13030  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinCmp(E);
13031  });
13032 }
13033 
13034 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
13035  // We don't support assignment in C. C++ assignments don't get here because
13036  // assignment is an lvalue in C++.
13037  if (E->isAssignmentOp()) {
13038  Error(E);
13039  if (!Info.noteFailure())
13040  return false;
13041  }
13042 
13043  if (DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator::shouldEnqueue(E))
13044  return DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator(*this, Result).Traverse(E);
13045 
13046  assert((!E->getLHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() ||
13047  !E->getRHS()->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) &&
13048  "DataRecursiveIntBinOpEvaluator should have handled integral types");
13049 
13050  if (E->isComparisonOp()) {
13051  // Evaluate builtin binary comparisons by evaluating them as three-way
13052  // comparisons and then translating the result.
13053  auto OnSuccess = [&](CmpResult CR, const BinaryOperator *E) {
13054  assert((CR != CmpResult::Unequal || E->isEqualityOp()) &&
13055  "should only produce Unequal for equality comparisons");
13056  bool IsEqual = CR == CmpResult::Equal,
13057  IsLess = CR == CmpResult::Less,
13058  IsGreater = CR == CmpResult::Greater;
13059  auto Op = E->getOpcode();
13060  switch (Op) {
13061  default:
13062  llvm_unreachable("unsupported binary operator");
13063  case BO_EQ:
13064  case BO_NE:
13065  return Success(IsEqual == (Op == BO_EQ), E);
13066  case BO_LT:
13067  return Success(IsLess, E);
13068  case BO_GT:
13069  return Success(IsGreater, E);
13070  case BO_LE:
13071  return Success(IsEqual || IsLess, E);
13072  case BO_GE:
13073  return Success(IsEqual || IsGreater, E);
13074  }
13075  };
13076  return EvaluateComparisonBinaryOperator(Info, E, OnSuccess, [&]() {
13077  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
13078  });
13079  }
13080 
13081  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
13082  QualType RHSTy = E->getRHS()->getType();
13083 
13084  if (LHSTy->isPointerType() && RHSTy->isPointerType() &&
13085  E->getOpcode() == BO_Sub) {
13086  LValue LHSValue, RHSValue;
13087 
13088  bool LHSOK = EvaluatePointer(E->getLHS(), LHSValue, Info);
13089  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
13090  return false;
13091 
13092  if (!EvaluatePointer(E->getRHS(), RHSValue, Info) || !LHSOK)
13093  return false;
13094 
13095  // Reject differing bases from the normal codepath; we special-case
13096  // comparisons to null.
13097  if (!HasSameBase(LHSValue, RHSValue)) {
13098  // Handle &&A - &&B.
13099  if (!LHSValue.Offset.isZero() || !RHSValue.Offset.isZero())
13100  return Error(E);
13101  const Expr *LHSExpr = LHSValue.Base.dyn_cast<const Expr *>();
13102  const Expr *RHSExpr = RHSValue.Base.dyn_cast<const Expr *>();
13103  if (!LHSExpr || !RHSExpr)
13104  return Error(E);
13105  const AddrLabelExpr *LHSAddrExpr = dyn_cast<AddrLabelExpr>(LHSExpr);
13106  const AddrLabelExpr *RHSAddrExpr = dyn_cast<AddrLabelExpr>(RHSExpr);
13107  if (!LHSAddrExpr || !RHSAddrExpr)
13108  return Error(E);
13109  // Make sure both labels come from the same function.
13110  if (LHSAddrExpr->getLabel()->getDeclContext() !=
13111  RHSAddrExpr->getLabel()->getDeclContext())
13112  return Error(E);
13113  return Success(APValue(LHSAddrExpr, RHSAddrExpr), E);
13114  }
13115  const CharUnits &LHSOffset = LHSValue.getLValueOffset();
13116  const CharUnits &RHSOffset = RHSValue.getLValueOffset();
13117 
13118  SubobjectDesignator &LHSDesignator = LHSValue.getLValueDesignator();
13119  SubobjectDesignator &RHSDesignator = RHSValue.getLValueDesignator();
13120 
13121  // C++11 [expr.add]p6:
13122  // Unless both pointers point to elements of the same array object, or
13123  // one past the last element of the array object, the behavior is
13124  // undefined.
13125  if (!LHSDesignator.Invalid && !RHSDesignator.Invalid &&
13126  !AreElementsOfSameArray(getType(LHSValue.Base), LHSDesignator,
13127  RHSDesignator))
13128  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_subtraction_not_same_array);
13129 
13130  QualType Type = E->getLHS()->getType();
13131  QualType ElementType = Type->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
13132 
13133  CharUnits ElementSize;
13134  if (!HandleSizeof(Info, E->getExprLoc(), ElementType, ElementSize))
13135  return false;
13136 
13137  // As an extension, a type may have zero size (empty struct or union in
13138  // C, array of zero length). Pointer subtraction in such cases has
13139  // undefined behavior, so is not constant.
13140  if (ElementSize.isZero()) {
13141  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_pointer_subtraction_zero_size)
13142  << ElementType;
13143  return false;
13144  }
13145 
13146  // FIXME: LLVM and GCC both compute LHSOffset - RHSOffset at runtime,
13147  // and produce incorrect results when it overflows. Such behavior
13148  // appears to be non-conforming, but is common, so perhaps we should
13149  // assume the standard intended for such cases to be undefined behavior
13150  // and check for them.
13151 
13152  // Compute (LHSOffset - RHSOffset) / Size carefully, checking for
13153  // overflow in the final conversion to ptrdiff_t.
13154  APSInt LHS(llvm::APInt(65, (int64_t)LHSOffset.getQuantity(), true), false);
13155  APSInt RHS(llvm::APInt(65, (int64_t)RHSOffset.getQuantity(), true), false);
13156  APSInt ElemSize(llvm::APInt(65, (int64_t)ElementSize.getQuantity(), true),
13157  false);
13158  APSInt TrueResult = (LHS - RHS) / ElemSize;
13159  APSInt Result = TrueResult.trunc(Info.Ctx.getIntWidth(E->getType()));
13160 
13161  if (Result.extend(65) != TrueResult &&
13162  !HandleOverflow(Info, E, TrueResult, E->getType()))
13163  return false;
13164  return Success(Result, E);
13165  }
13166 
13167  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
13168 }
13169 
13170 /// VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr - Evaluate a sizeof, alignof or vec_step with
13171 /// a result as the expression's type.
13172 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
13173  const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
13174  switch(E->getKind()) {
13175  case UETT_PreferredAlignOf:
13176  case UETT_AlignOf: {
13177  if (E->isArgumentType())
13178  return Success(GetAlignOfType(Info, E->getArgumentType(), E->getKind()),
13179  E);
13180  else
13181  return Success(GetAlignOfExpr(Info, E->getArgumentExpr(), E->getKind()),
13182  E);
13183  }
13184 
13185  case UETT_VecStep: {
13186  QualType Ty = E->getTypeOfArgument();
13187 
13188  if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
13189  unsigned n = Ty->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
13190 
13191  // The vec_step built-in functions that take a 3-component
13192  // vector return 4. (OpenCL 1.1 spec 6.11.12)
13193  if (n == 3)
13194  n = 4;
13195 
13196  return Success(n, E);
13197  } else
13198  return Success(1, E);
13199  }
13200 
13201  case UETT_SizeOf: {
13202  QualType SrcTy = E->getTypeOfArgument();
13203  // C++ [expr.sizeof]p2: "When applied to a reference or a reference type,
13204  // the result is the size of the referenced type."
13205  if (const ReferenceType *Ref = SrcTy->getAs<ReferenceType>())
13206  SrcTy = Ref->getPointeeType();
13207 
13208  CharUnits Sizeof;
13209  if (!HandleSizeof(Info, E->getExprLoc(), SrcTy, Sizeof))
13210  return false;
13211  return Success(Sizeof, E);
13212  }
13213  case UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign:
13214  assert(E->isArgumentType());
13215  return Success(
13216  Info.Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(
13217  Info.Ctx.getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(E->getArgumentType()))
13218  .getQuantity(),
13219  E);
13220  }
13221 
13222  llvm_unreachable("unknown expr/type trait");
13223 }
13224 
13225 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitOffsetOfExpr(const OffsetOfExpr *OOE) {
13226  CharUnits Result;
13227  unsigned n = OOE->getNumComponents();
13228  if (n == 0)
13229  return Error(OOE);
13230  QualType CurrentType = OOE->getTypeSourceInfo()->getType();
13231  for (unsigned i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
13232  OffsetOfNode ON = OOE->getComponent(i);
13233  switch (ON.getKind()) {
13234  case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
13235  const Expr *Idx = OOE->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
13236  APSInt IdxResult;
13237  if (!EvaluateInteger(Idx, IdxResult, Info))
13238  return false;
13239  const ArrayType *AT = Info.Ctx.getAsArrayType(CurrentType);
13240  if (!AT)
13241  return Error(OOE);
13242  CurrentType = AT->getElementType();
13243  CharUnits ElementSize = Info.Ctx.getTypeSizeInChars(CurrentType);
13244  Result += IdxResult.getSExtValue() * ElementSize;
13245  break;
13246  }
13247 
13248  case OffsetOfNode::Field: {
13249  FieldDecl *MemberDecl = ON.getField();
13250  const RecordType *RT = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>();
13251  if (!RT)
13252  return Error(OOE);
13253  RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
13254  if (RD->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
13255  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = Info.Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
13256  unsigned i = MemberDecl->getFieldIndex();
13257  assert(i < RL.getFieldCount() && "offsetof field in wrong type");
13258  Result += Info.Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(RL.getFieldOffset(i));
13259  CurrentType = MemberDecl->getType().getNonReferenceType();
13260  break;
13261  }
13262 
13263  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
13264  llvm_unreachable("dependent __builtin_offsetof");
13265 
13266  case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
13267  CXXBaseSpecifier *BaseSpec = ON.getBase();
13268  if (BaseSpec->isVirtual())
13269  return Error(OOE);
13270 
13271  // Find the layout of the class whose base we are looking into.
13272  const RecordType *RT = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>();
13273  if (!RT)
13274  return Error(OOE);
13275  RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
13276  if (RD->isInvalidDecl()) return false;
13277  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = Info.Ctx.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
13278 
13279  // Find the base class itself.
13280  CurrentType = BaseSpec->getType();
13281  const RecordType *BaseRT = CurrentType->getAs<RecordType>();
13282  if (!BaseRT)
13283  return Error(OOE);
13284 
13285  // Add the offset to the base.
13286  Result += RL.getBaseClassOffset(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseRT->getDecl()));
13287  break;
13288  }
13289  }
13290  }
13291  return Success(Result, OOE);
13292 }
13293 
13294 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryOperator(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13295  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
13296  default:
13297  // Address, indirect, pre/post inc/dec, etc are not valid constant exprs.
13298  // See C99 6.6p3.
13299  return Error(E);
13300  case UO_Extension:
13301  // FIXME: Should extension allow i-c-e extension expressions in its scope?
13302  // If so, we could clear the diagnostic ID.
13303  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
13304  case UO_Plus:
13305  // The result is just the value.
13306  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
13307  case UO_Minus: {
13308  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
13309  return false;
13310  if (!Result.isInt()) return Error(E);
13311  const APSInt &Value = Result.getInt();
13312  if (Value.isSigned() && Value.isMinSignedValue() && E->canOverflow() &&
13313  !HandleOverflow(Info, E, -Value.extend(Value.getBitWidth() + 1),
13314  E->getType()))
13315  return false;
13316  return Success(-Value, E);
13317  }
13318  case UO_Not: {
13319  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
13320  return false;
13321  if (!Result.isInt()) return Error(E);
13322  return Success(~Result.getInt(), E);
13323  }
13324  case UO_LNot: {
13325  bool bres;
13326  if (!EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(E->getSubExpr(), bres, Info))
13327  return false;
13328  return Success(!bres, E);
13329  }
13330  }
13331 }
13332 
13333 /// HandleCast - This is used to evaluate implicit or explicit casts where the
13334 /// result type is integer.
13335 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
13336  const Expr *SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
13337  QualType DestType = E->getType();
13338  QualType SrcType = SubExpr->getType();
13339 
13340  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
13341  case CK_BaseToDerived:
13342  case CK_DerivedToBase:
13343  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
13344  case CK_Dynamic:
13345  case CK_ToUnion:
13346  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
13347  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
13348  case CK_NullToPointer:
13349  case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
13350  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
13351  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
13352  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
13353  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
13354  case CK_IntegralToPointer:
13355  case CK_ToVoid:
13356  case CK_VectorSplat:
13357  case CK_IntegralToFloating:
13358  case CK_FloatingCast:
13359  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
13360  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
13361  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
13362  case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast:
13363  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
13364  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
13365  case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
13366  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
13367  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
13368  case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
13369  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
13370  case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
13371  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType:
13372  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
13373  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
13374  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
13375  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint:
13376  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
13377  case CK_FixedPointCast:
13378  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
13379  case CK_MatrixCast:
13380  llvm_unreachable("invalid cast kind for integral value");
13381 
13382  case CK_BitCast:
13383  case CK_Dependent:
13384  case CK_LValueBitCast:
13385  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
13386  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
13387  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
13388  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
13389  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
13390  return Error(E);
13391 
13392  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
13393  case CK_LValueToRValue:
13394  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
13395  case CK_NoOp:
13396  case CK_LValueToRValueBitCast:
13397  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
13398 
13399  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean:
13400  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
13401  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
13402  case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
13403  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral:
13404  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
13405  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean: {
13406  bool BoolResult;
13407  if (!EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(SubExpr, BoolResult, Info))
13408  return false;
13409  uint64_t IntResult = BoolResult;
13410  if (BoolResult && E->getCastKind() == CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral)
13411  IntResult = (uint64_t)-1;
13412  return Success(IntResult, E);
13413  }
13414 
13415  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral: {
13416  APFixedPoint Src(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(SrcType));
13417  if (!EvaluateFixedPoint(SubExpr, Src, Info))
13418  return false;
13419  bool Overflowed;
13420  llvm::APSInt Result = Src.convertToInt(
13421  Info.Ctx.getIntWidth(DestType),
13422  DestType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType(), &Overflowed);
13423  if (Overflowed && !HandleOverflow(Info, E, Result, DestType))
13424  return false;
13425  return Success(Result, E);
13426  }
13427 
13428  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean: {
13429  // Unsigned padding does not affect this.
13430  APValue Val;
13431  if (!Evaluate(Val, Info, SubExpr))
13432  return false;
13433  return Success(Val.getFixedPoint().getBoolValue(), E);
13434  }
13435 
13436  case CK_IntegralCast: {
13437  if (!Visit(SubExpr))
13438  return false;
13439 
13440  if (!Result.isInt()) {
13441  // Allow casts of address-of-label differences if they are no-ops
13442  // or narrowing. (The narrowing case isn't actually guaranteed to
13443  // be constant-evaluatable except in some narrow cases which are hard
13444  // to detect here. We let it through on the assumption the user knows
13445  // what they are doing.)
13446  if (Result.isAddrLabelDiff())
13447  return Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(DestType) <= Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(SrcType);
13448  // Only allow casts of lvalues if they are lossless.
13449  return Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(DestType) == Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(SrcType);
13450  }
13451 
13452  return Success(HandleIntToIntCast(Info, E, DestType, SrcType,
13453  Result.getInt()), E);
13454  }
13455 
13456  case CK_PointerToIntegral: {
13457  CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_invalid_cast) << 2;
13458 
13459  LValue LV;
13460  if (!EvaluatePointer(SubExpr, LV, Info))
13461  return false;
13462 
13463  if (LV.getLValueBase()) {
13464  // Only allow based lvalue casts if they are lossless.
13465  // FIXME: Allow a larger integer size than the pointer size, and allow
13466  // narrowing back down to pointer width in subsequent integral casts.
13467  // FIXME: Check integer type's active bits, not its type size.
13468  if (Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(DestType) != Info.Ctx.getTypeSize(SrcType))
13469  return Error(E);
13470 
13471  LV.Designator.setInvalid();
13472  LV.moveInto(Result);
13473  return true;
13474  }
13475 
13476  APSInt AsInt;
13477  APValue V;
13478  LV.moveInto(V);
13479  if (!V.toIntegralConstant(AsInt, SrcType, Info.Ctx))
13480  llvm_unreachable("Can't cast this!");
13481 
13482  return Success(HandleIntToIntCast(Info, E, DestType, SrcType, AsInt), E);
13483  }
13484 
13485  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal: {
13486  ComplexValue C;
13487  if (!EvaluateComplex(SubExpr, C, Info))
13488  return false;
13489  return Success(C.getComplexIntReal(), E);
13490  }
13491 
13492  case CK_FloatingToIntegral: {
13493  APFloat F(0.0);
13494  if (!EvaluateFloat(SubExpr, F, Info))
13495  return false;
13496 
13497  APSInt Value;
13498  if (!HandleFloatToIntCast(Info, E, SrcType, F, DestType, Value))
13499  return false;
13500  return Success(Value, E);
13501  }
13502  }
13503 
13504  llvm_unreachable("unknown cast resulting in integral value");
13505 }
13506 
13507 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryReal(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13508  if (E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
13509  ComplexValue LV;
13510  if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getSubExpr(), LV, Info))
13511  return false;
13512  if (!LV.isComplexInt())
13513  return Error(E);
13514  return Success(LV.getComplexIntReal(), E);
13515  }
13516 
13517  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
13518 }
13519 
13520 bool IntExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13521  if (E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isComplexIntegerType()) {
13522  ComplexValue LV;
13523  if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getSubExpr(), LV, Info))
13524  return false;
13525  if (!LV.isComplexInt())
13526  return Error(E);
13527  return Success(LV.getComplexIntImag(), E);
13528  }
13529 
13530  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
13531  return Success(0, E);
13532 }

13550 
13551 bool FixedPointExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryOperator(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13552  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
13553  default:
13554  // Invalid unary operators
13555  return Error(E);
13556  case UO_Plus:
13557  // The result is just the value.
13558  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
13559  case UO_Minus: {
13560  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr())) return false;
13561  if (!Result.isFixedPoint())
13562  return Error(E);
13563  bool Overflowed;
13564  APFixedPoint Negated = Result.getFixedPoint().negate(&Overflowed);
13565  if (Overflowed && !HandleOverflow(Info, E, Negated, E->getType()))
13566  return false;
13567  return Success(Negated, E);
13568  }
13569  case UO_LNot: {
13570  bool bres;
13571  if (!EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(E->getSubExpr(), bres, Info))
13572  return false;
13573  return Success(!bres, E);
13574  }
13575  }
13576 }
13577 
13578 bool FixedPointExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
13579  const Expr *SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
13580  QualType DestType = E->getType();
13581  assert(DestType->isFixedPointType() &&
13582  "Expected destination type to be a fixed point type");
13583  auto DestFXSema = Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(DestType);
13584 
13585  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
13586  case CK_FixedPointCast: {
13587  APFixedPoint Src(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(SubExpr->getType()));
13588  if (!EvaluateFixedPoint(SubExpr, Src, Info))
13589  return false;
13590  bool Overflowed;
13591  APFixedPoint Result = Src.convert(DestFXSema, &Overflowed);
13592  if (Overflowed) {
13593  if (Info.checkingForUndefinedBehavior())
13594  Info.Ctx.getDiagnostics().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
13595  diag::warn_fixedpoint_constant_overflow)
13596  << Result.toString() << E->getType();
13597  if (!HandleOverflow(Info, E, Result, E->getType()))
13598  return false;
13599  }
13600  return Success(Result, E);
13601  }
13602  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint: {
13603  APSInt Src;
13604  if (!EvaluateInteger(SubExpr, Src, Info))
13605  return false;
13606 
13607  bool Overflowed;
13608  APFixedPoint IntResult = APFixedPoint::getFromIntValue(
13609  Src, Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(DestType), &Overflowed);
13610 
13611  if (Overflowed) {
13612  if (Info.checkingForUndefinedBehavior())
13613  Info.Ctx.getDiagnostics().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
13614  diag::warn_fixedpoint_constant_overflow)
13615  << IntResult.toString() << E->getType();
13616  if (!HandleOverflow(Info, E, IntResult, E->getType()))
13617  return false;
13618  }
13619 
13620  return Success(IntResult, E);
13621  }
13622  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint: {
13623  APFloat Src(0.0);
13624  if (!EvaluateFloat(SubExpr, Src, Info))
13625  return false;
13626 
13627  bool Overflowed;
13628  APFixedPoint Result = APFixedPoint::getFromFloatValue(
13629  Src, Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(DestType), &Overflowed);
13630 
13631  if (Overflowed) {
13632  if (Info.checkingForUndefinedBehavior())
13633  Info.Ctx.getDiagnostics().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
13634  diag::warn_fixedpoint_constant_overflow)
13635  << Result.toString() << E->getType();
13636  if (!HandleOverflow(Info, E, Result, E->getType()))
13637  return false;
13638  }
13639 
13640  return Success(Result, E);
13641  }
13642  case CK_NoOp:
13643  case CK_LValueToRValue:
13644  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
13645  default:
13646  return Error(E);
13647  }
13648 }
13649 
13650 bool FixedPointExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
13651  if (E->isPtrMemOp() || E->isAssignmentOp() || E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma)
13652  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
13653 
13654  const Expr *LHS = E->getLHS();
13655  const Expr *RHS = E->getRHS();
13656  FixedPointSemantics ResultFXSema =
13657  Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(E->getType());
13658 
13659  APFixedPoint LHSFX(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(LHS->getType()));
13660  if (!EvaluateFixedPointOrInteger(LHS, LHSFX, Info))
13661  return false;
13662  APFixedPoint RHSFX(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(RHS->getType()));
13663  if (!EvaluateFixedPointOrInteger(RHS, RHSFX, Info))
13664  return false;
13665 
13666  bool OpOverflow = false, ConversionOverflow = false;
13667  APFixedPoint Result(LHSFX.getSemantics());
13668  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
13669  case BO_Add: {
13670  Result = LHSFX.add(RHSFX, &OpOverflow)
13671  .convert(ResultFXSema, &ConversionOverflow);
13672  break;
13673  }
13674  case BO_Sub: {
13675  Result = LHSFX.sub(RHSFX, &OpOverflow)
13676  .convert(ResultFXSema, &ConversionOverflow);
13677  break;
13678  }
13679  case BO_Mul: {
13680  Result = LHSFX.mul(RHSFX, &OpOverflow)
13681  .convert(ResultFXSema, &ConversionOverflow);
13682  break;
13683  }
13684  case BO_Div: {
13685  if (RHSFX.getValue() == 0) {
13686  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_expr_divide_by_zero);
13687  return false;
13688  }
13689  Result = LHSFX.div(RHSFX, &OpOverflow)
13690  .convert(ResultFXSema, &ConversionOverflow);
13691  break;
13692  }
13693  case BO_Shl:
13694  case BO_Shr: {
13695  FixedPointSemantics LHSSema = LHSFX.getSemantics();
13696  llvm::APSInt RHSVal = RHSFX.getValue();
13697 
13698  unsigned ShiftBW =
13699  LHSSema.getWidth() - (unsigned)LHSSema.hasUnsignedPadding();
13700  unsigned Amt = RHSVal.getLimitedValue(ShiftBW - 1);
13701  // Embedded-C 4.1.6.2.2:
13702  // The right operand must be nonnegative and less than the total number
13703  // of (nonpadding) bits of the fixed-point operand ...
13704  if (RHSVal.isNegative())
13705  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_negative_shift) << RHSVal;
13706  else if (Amt != RHSVal)
13707  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_large_shift)
13708  << RHSVal << E->getType() << ShiftBW;
13709 
13710  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Shl)
13711  Result = LHSFX.shl(Amt, &OpOverflow);
13712  else
13713  Result = LHSFX.shr(Amt, &OpOverflow);
13714  break;
13715  }
13716  default:
13717  return false;
13718  }
13719  if (OpOverflow || ConversionOverflow) {
13720  if (Info.checkingForUndefinedBehavior())
13721  Info.Ctx.getDiagnostics().Report(E->getExprLoc(),
13722  diag::warn_fixedpoint_constant_overflow)
13723  << Result.toString() << E->getType();
13724  if (!HandleOverflow(Info, E, Result, E->getType()))
13725  return false;
13726  }
13727  return Success(Result, E);
13728 }

13766 static bool EvaluateFloat(const Expr* E, APFloat& Result, EvalInfo &Info) {
13767  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
13768  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isRealFloatingType());
13769  return FloatExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E);
13770 }
13771 
13772 static bool TryEvaluateBuiltinNaN(const ASTContext &Context,
13773  QualType ResultTy,
13774  const Expr *Arg,
13775  bool SNaN,
13776  llvm::APFloat &Result) {
13777  const StringLiteral *S = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Arg->IgnoreParenCasts());
13778  if (!S) return false;
13779 
13780  const llvm::fltSemantics &Sem = Context.getFloatTypeSemantics(ResultTy);
13781 
13782  llvm::APInt fill;
13783 
13784  // Treat empty strings as if they were zero.
13785  if (S->getString().empty())
13786  fill = llvm::APInt(32, 0);
13787  else if (S->getString().getAsInteger(0, fill))
13788  return false;
13789 
13790  if (Context.getTargetInfo().isNan2008()) {
13791  if (SNaN)
13792  Result = llvm::APFloat::getSNaN(Sem, false, &fill);
13793  else
13794  Result = llvm::APFloat::getQNaN(Sem, false, &fill);
13795  } else {
13796  // Prior to IEEE 754-2008, architectures were allowed to choose whether
13797  // the first bit of their significand was set for qNaN or sNaN. MIPS chose
13798  // a different encoding to what became a standard in 2008, and for pre-
13799  // 2008 revisions, MIPS interpreted sNaN-2008 as qNan and qNaN-2008 as
13800  // sNaN. This is now known as "legacy NaN" encoding.
13801  if (SNaN)
13802  Result = llvm::APFloat::getQNaN(Sem, false, &fill);
13803  else
13804  Result = llvm::APFloat::getSNaN(Sem, false, &fill);
13805  }
13806 
13807  return true;
13808 }
13809 
13810 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
13811  switch (E->getBuiltinCallee()) {
13812  default:
13813  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCallExpr(E);
13814 
13815  case Builtin::BI__builtin_huge_val:
13816  case Builtin::BI__builtin_huge_valf:
13817  case Builtin::BI__builtin_huge_vall:
13818  case Builtin::BI__builtin_huge_valf128:
13819  case Builtin::BI__builtin_inf:
13820  case Builtin::BI__builtin_inff:
13821  case Builtin::BI__builtin_infl:
13822  case Builtin::BI__builtin_inff128: {
13823  const llvm::fltSemantics &Sem =
13824  Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(E->getType());
13825  Result = llvm::APFloat::getInf(Sem);
13826  return true;
13827  }
13828 
13829  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nans:
13830  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nansf:
13831  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nansl:
13832  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nansf128:
13833  if (!TryEvaluateBuiltinNaN(Info.Ctx, E->getType(), E->getArg(0),
13834  true, Result))
13835  return Error(E);
13836  return true;
13837 
13838  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nan:
13839  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nanf:
13840  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nanl:
13841  case Builtin::BI__builtin_nanf128:
13842  // If this is __builtin_nan() turn this into a nan, otherwise we
13843  // can't constant fold it.
13844  if (!TryEvaluateBuiltinNaN(Info.Ctx, E->getType(), E->getArg(0),
13845  false, Result))
13846  return Error(E);
13847  return true;
13848 
13849  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabs:
13850  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf:
13851  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
13852  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsf128:
13853  // The C standard says "fabs raises no floating-point exceptions,
13854  // even if x is a signaling NaN. The returned value is independent of
13855  // the current rounding direction mode." Therefore constant folding can
13856  // proceed without regard to the floating point settings.
13857  // Reference, WG14 N2478 F.10.4.3
13858  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(0), Result, Info))
13859  return false;
13860 
13861  if (Result.isNegative())
13862  Result.changeSign();
13863  return true;
13864 
13865  case Builtin::BI__arithmetic_fence:
13866  return EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(0), Result, Info);
13867 
13868  // FIXME: Builtin::BI__builtin_powi
13869  // FIXME: Builtin::BI__builtin_powif
13870  // FIXME: Builtin::BI__builtin_powil
13871 
13872  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysign:
13873  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysignf:
13874  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysignl:
13875  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysignf128: {
13876  APFloat RHS(0.);
13877  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(0), Result, Info) ||
13878  !EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(1), RHS, Info))
13879  return false;
13880  Result.copySign(RHS);
13881  return true;
13882  }
13883  }
13884 }
13885 
13886 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryReal(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13887  if (E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
13888  ComplexValue CV;
13889  if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getSubExpr(), CV, Info))
13890  return false;
13891  Result = CV.FloatReal;
13892  return true;
13893  }
13894 
13895  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
13896 }
13897 
13898 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13899  if (E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
13900  ComplexValue CV;
13901  if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getSubExpr(), CV, Info))
13902  return false;
13903  Result = CV.FloatImag;
13904  return true;
13905  }
13906 
13907  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
13908  const llvm::fltSemantics &Sem = Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(E->getType());
13909  Result = llvm::APFloat::getZero(Sem);
13910  return true;
13911 }
13912 
13913 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryOperator(const UnaryOperator *E) {
13914  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
13915  default: return Error(E);
13916  case UO_Plus:
13917  return EvaluateFloat(E->getSubExpr(), Result, Info);
13918  case UO_Minus:
13919  // In C standard, WG14 N2478 F.3 p4
13920  // "the unary - raises no floating point exceptions,
13921  // even if the operand is signalling."
13922  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getSubExpr(), Result, Info))
13923  return false;
13924  Result.changeSign();
13925  return true;
13926  }
13927 }
13928 
13929 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
13930  if (E->isPtrMemOp() || E->isAssignmentOp() || E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma)
13931  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
13932 
13933  APFloat RHS(0.0);
13934  bool LHSOK = EvaluateFloat(E->getLHS(), Result, Info);
13935  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
13936  return false;
13937  return EvaluateFloat(E->getRHS(), RHS, Info) && LHSOK &&
13938  handleFloatFloatBinOp(Info, E, Result, E->getOpcode(), RHS);
13939 }
13940 
13941 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitFloatingLiteral(const FloatingLiteral *E) {
13942  Result = E->getValue();
13943  return true;
13944 }
13945 
13946 bool FloatExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
13947  const Expr* SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
13948 
13949  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
13950  default:
13951  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
13952 
13953  case CK_IntegralToFloating: {
13954  APSInt IntResult;
13955  const FPOptions FPO = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(
13956  Info.Ctx.getLangOpts());
13957  return EvaluateInteger(SubExpr, IntResult, Info) &&
13958  HandleIntToFloatCast(Info, E, FPO, SubExpr->getType(),
13959  IntResult, E->getType(), Result);
13960  }
13961 
13962  case CK_FixedPointToFloating: {
13963  APFixedPoint FixResult(Info.Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(SubExpr->getType()));
13964  if (!EvaluateFixedPoint(SubExpr, FixResult, Info))
13965  return false;
13966  Result =
13967  FixResult.convertToFloat(Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(E->getType()));
13968  return true;
13969  }
13970 
13971  case CK_FloatingCast: {
13972  if (!Visit(SubExpr))
13973  return false;
13974  return HandleFloatToFloatCast(Info, E, SubExpr->getType(), E->getType(),
13975  Result);
13976  }
13977 
13978  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal: {
13979  ComplexValue V;
13980  if (!EvaluateComplex(SubExpr, V, Info))
13981  return false;
13982  Result = V.getComplexFloatReal();
13983  return true;
13984  }
13985  }
13986 }
