14021 static bool EvaluateComplex(const Expr *E, ComplexValue &Result,
14022  EvalInfo &Info) {
14023  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14024  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isAnyComplexType());
14025  return ComplexExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E);
14026 }
14027 
14028 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) {
14029  QualType ElemTy = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14030  if (ElemTy->isRealFloatingType()) {
14031  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14032  APFloat Zero = APFloat::getZero(Info.Ctx.getFloatTypeSemantics(ElemTy));
14033  Result.FloatReal = Zero;
14034  Result.FloatImag = Zero;
14035  } else {
14036  Result.makeComplexInt();
14037  APSInt Zero = Info.Ctx.MakeIntValue(0, ElemTy);
14038  Result.IntReal = Zero;
14039  Result.IntImag = Zero;
14040  }
14041  return true;
14042 }
14043 
14044 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitImaginaryLiteral(const ImaginaryLiteral *E) {
14045  const Expr* SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
14046 
14047  if (SubExpr->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
14048  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14049  APFloat &Imag = Result.FloatImag;
14050  if (!EvaluateFloat(SubExpr, Imag, Info))
14051  return false;
14052 
14053  Result.FloatReal = APFloat(Imag.getSemantics());
14054  return true;
14055  } else {
14056  assert(SubExpr->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
14057  "Unexpected imaginary literal.");
14058 
14059  Result.makeComplexInt();
14060  APSInt &Imag = Result.IntImag;
14061  if (!EvaluateInteger(SubExpr, Imag, Info))
14062  return false;
14063 
14064  Result.IntReal = APSInt(Imag.getBitWidth(), !Imag.isSigned());
14065  return true;
14066  }
14067 }
14068 
14069 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
14070 
14071  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
14072  case CK_BitCast:
14073  case CK_BaseToDerived:
14074  case CK_DerivedToBase:
14075  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
14076  case CK_Dynamic:
14077  case CK_ToUnion:
14078  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
14079  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
14080  case CK_NullToPointer:
14081  case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
14082  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
14083  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
14084  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean:
14085  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
14086  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
14087  case CK_IntegralToPointer:
14088  case CK_PointerToIntegral:
14089  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
14090  case CK_ToVoid:
14091  case CK_VectorSplat:
14092  case CK_IntegralCast:
14093  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral:
14094  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
14095  case CK_IntegralToFloating:
14096  case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
14097  case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
14098  case CK_FloatingCast:
14099  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
14100  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
14101  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
14102  case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast:
14103  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
14104  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
14105  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
14106  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean:
14107  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
14108  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
14109  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
14110  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
14111  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
14112  case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
14113  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType:
14114  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
14115  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
14116  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
14117  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint:
14118  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
14119  case CK_FixedPointCast:
14120  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
14121  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
14122  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
14123  case CK_MatrixCast:
14124  llvm_unreachable("invalid cast kind for complex value");
14125 
14126  case CK_LValueToRValue:
14127  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
14128  case CK_NoOp:
14129  case CK_LValueToRValueBitCast:
14130  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
14131 
14132  case CK_Dependent:
14133  case CK_LValueBitCast:
14134  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
14135  return Error(E);
14136 
14137  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex: {
14138  APFloat &Real = Result.FloatReal;
14139  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getSubExpr(), Real, Info))
14140  return false;
14141 
14142  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14143  Result.FloatImag = APFloat(Real.getSemantics());
14144  return true;
14145  }
14146 
14147  case CK_FloatingComplexCast: {
14148  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
14149  return false;
14150 
14151  QualType To = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14152  QualType From
14153  = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14154 
14155  return HandleFloatToFloatCast(Info, E, From, To, Result.FloatReal) &&
14156  HandleFloatToFloatCast(Info, E, From, To, Result.FloatImag);
14157  }
14158 
14159  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex: {
14160  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
14161  return false;
14162 
14163  QualType To = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14164  QualType From
14165  = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14166  Result.makeComplexInt();
14167  return HandleFloatToIntCast(Info, E, From, Result.FloatReal,
14168  To, Result.IntReal) &&
14169  HandleFloatToIntCast(Info, E, From, Result.FloatImag,
14170  To, Result.IntImag);
14171  }
14172 
14173  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex: {
14174  APSInt &Real = Result.IntReal;
14175  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getSubExpr(), Real, Info))
14176  return false;
14177 
14178  Result.makeComplexInt();
14179  Result.IntImag = APSInt(Real.getBitWidth(), !Real.isSigned());
14180  return true;
14181  }
14182 
14183  case CK_IntegralComplexCast: {
14184  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
14185  return false;
14186 
14187  QualType To = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14188  QualType From
14189  = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14190 
14191  Result.IntReal = HandleIntToIntCast(Info, E, To, From, Result.IntReal);
14192  Result.IntImag = HandleIntToIntCast(Info, E, To, From, Result.IntImag);
14193  return true;
14194  }
14195 
14196  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex: {
14197  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
14198  return false;
14199 
14200  const FPOptions FPO = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(
14201  Info.Ctx.getLangOpts());
14202  QualType To = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14203  QualType From
14204  = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
14205  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14206  return HandleIntToFloatCast(Info, E, FPO, From, Result.IntReal,
14207  To, Result.FloatReal) &&
14208  HandleIntToFloatCast(Info, E, FPO, From, Result.IntImag,
14209  To, Result.FloatImag);
14210  }
14211  }
14212 
14213  llvm_unreachable("unknown cast resulting in complex value");
14214 }
14215 
14216 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *E) {
14217  if (E->isPtrMemOp() || E->isAssignmentOp() || E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma)
14218  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitBinaryOperator(E);
14219 
14220  // Track whether the LHS or RHS is real at the type system level. When this is
14221  // the case we can simplify our evaluation strategy.
14222  bool LHSReal = false, RHSReal = false;
14223 
14224  bool LHSOK;
14225  if (E->getLHS()->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
14226  LHSReal = true;
14227  APFloat &Real = Result.FloatReal;
14228  LHSOK = EvaluateFloat(E->getLHS(), Real, Info);
14229  if (LHSOK) {
14230  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14231  Result.FloatImag = APFloat(Real.getSemantics());
14232  }
14233  } else {
14234  LHSOK = Visit(E->getLHS());
14235  }
14236  if (!LHSOK && !Info.noteFailure())
14237  return false;
14238 
14239  ComplexValue RHS;
14240  if (E->getRHS()->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
14241  RHSReal = true;
14242  APFloat &Real = RHS.FloatReal;
14243  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getRHS(), Real, Info) || !LHSOK)
14244  return false;
14245  RHS.makeComplexFloat();
14246  RHS.FloatImag = APFloat(Real.getSemantics());
14247  } else if (!EvaluateComplex(E->getRHS(), RHS, Info) || !LHSOK)
14248  return false;
14249 
14250  assert(!(LHSReal && RHSReal) &&
14251  "Cannot have both operands of a complex operation be real.");
14252  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
14253  default: return Error(E);
14254  case BO_Add:
14255  if (Result.isComplexFloat()) {
14256  Result.getComplexFloatReal().add(RHS.getComplexFloatReal(),
14257  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14258  if (LHSReal)
14259  Result.getComplexFloatImag() = RHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14260  else if (!RHSReal)
14261  Result.getComplexFloatImag().add(RHS.getComplexFloatImag(),
14262  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14263  } else {
14264  Result.getComplexIntReal() += RHS.getComplexIntReal();
14265  Result.getComplexIntImag() += RHS.getComplexIntImag();
14266  }
14267  break;
14268  case BO_Sub:
14269  if (Result.isComplexFloat()) {
14270  Result.getComplexFloatReal().subtract(RHS.getComplexFloatReal(),
14271  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14272  if (LHSReal) {
14273  Result.getComplexFloatImag() = RHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14274  Result.getComplexFloatImag().changeSign();
14275  } else if (!RHSReal) {
14276  Result.getComplexFloatImag().subtract(RHS.getComplexFloatImag(),
14277  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14278  }
14279  } else {
14280  Result.getComplexIntReal() -= RHS.getComplexIntReal();
14281  Result.getComplexIntImag() -= RHS.getComplexIntImag();
14282  }
14283  break;
14284  case BO_Mul:
14285  if (Result.isComplexFloat()) {
14286  // This is an implementation of complex multiplication according to the
14287  // constraints laid out in C11 Annex G. The implementation uses the
14288  // following naming scheme:
14289  // (a + ib) * (c + id)
14290  ComplexValue LHS = Result;
14291  APFloat &A = LHS.getComplexFloatReal();
14292  APFloat &B = LHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14293  APFloat &C = RHS.getComplexFloatReal();
14294  APFloat &D = RHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14295  APFloat &ResR = Result.getComplexFloatReal();
14296  APFloat &ResI = Result.getComplexFloatImag();
14297  if (LHSReal) {
14298  assert(!RHSReal && "Cannot have two real operands for a complex op!");
14299  ResR = A * C;
14300  ResI = A * D;
14301  } else if (RHSReal) {
14302  ResR = C * A;
14303  ResI = C * B;
14304  } else {
14305  // In the fully general case, we need to handle NaNs and infinities
14306  // robustly.
14307  APFloat AC = A * C;
14308  APFloat BD = B * D;
14309  APFloat AD = A * D;
14310  APFloat BC = B * C;
14311  ResR = AC - BD;
14312  ResI = AD + BC;
14313  if (ResR.isNaN() && ResI.isNaN()) {
14314  bool Recalc = false;
14315  if (A.isInfinity() || B.isInfinity()) {
14316  A = APFloat::copySign(
14317  APFloat(A.getSemantics(), A.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), A);
14318  B = APFloat::copySign(
14319  APFloat(B.getSemantics(), B.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), B);
14320  if (C.isNaN())
14321  C = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(C.getSemantics()), C);
14322  if (D.isNaN())
14323  D = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(D.getSemantics()), D);
14324  Recalc = true;
14325  }
14326  if (C.isInfinity() || D.isInfinity()) {
14327  C = APFloat::copySign(
14328  APFloat(C.getSemantics(), C.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), C);
14329  D = APFloat::copySign(
14330  APFloat(D.getSemantics(), D.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), D);
14331  if (A.isNaN())
14332  A = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(A.getSemantics()), A);
14333  if (B.isNaN())
14334  B = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(B.getSemantics()), B);
14335  Recalc = true;
14336  }
14337  if (!Recalc && (AC.isInfinity() || BD.isInfinity() ||
14338  AD.isInfinity() || BC.isInfinity())) {
14339  if (A.isNaN())
14340  A = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(A.getSemantics()), A);
14341  if (B.isNaN())
14342  B = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(B.getSemantics()), B);
14343  if (C.isNaN())
14344  C = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(C.getSemantics()), C);
14345  if (D.isNaN())
14346  D = APFloat::copySign(APFloat(D.getSemantics()), D);
14347  Recalc = true;
14348  }
14349  if (Recalc) {
14350  ResR = APFloat::getInf(A.getSemantics()) * (A * C - B * D);
14351  ResI = APFloat::getInf(A.getSemantics()) * (A * D + B * C);
14352  }
14353  }
14354  }
14355  } else {
14356  ComplexValue LHS = Result;
14357  Result.getComplexIntReal() =
14358  (LHS.getComplexIntReal() * RHS.getComplexIntReal() -
14359  LHS.getComplexIntImag() * RHS.getComplexIntImag());
14360  Result.getComplexIntImag() =
14361  (LHS.getComplexIntReal() * RHS.getComplexIntImag() +
14362  LHS.getComplexIntImag() * RHS.getComplexIntReal());
14363  }
14364  break;
14365  case BO_Div:
14366  if (Result.isComplexFloat()) {
14367  // This is an implementation of complex division according to the
14368  // constraints laid out in C11 Annex G. The implementation uses the
14369  // following naming scheme:
14370  // (a + ib) / (c + id)
14371  ComplexValue LHS = Result;
14372  APFloat &A = LHS.getComplexFloatReal();
14373  APFloat &B = LHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14374  APFloat &C = RHS.getComplexFloatReal();
14375  APFloat &D = RHS.getComplexFloatImag();
14376  APFloat &ResR = Result.getComplexFloatReal();
14377  APFloat &ResI = Result.getComplexFloatImag();
14378  if (RHSReal) {
14379  ResR = A / C;
14380  ResI = B / C;
14381  } else {
14382  if (LHSReal) {
14383  // No real optimizations we can do here, stub out with zero.
14384  B = APFloat::getZero(A.getSemantics());
14385  }
14386  int DenomLogB = 0;
14387  APFloat MaxCD = maxnum(abs(C), abs(D));
14388  if (MaxCD.isFinite()) {
14389  DenomLogB = ilogb(MaxCD);
14390  C = scalbn(C, -DenomLogB, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14391  D = scalbn(D, -DenomLogB, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14392  }
14393  APFloat Denom = C * C + D * D;
14394  ResR = scalbn((A * C + B * D) / Denom, -DenomLogB,
14395  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14396  ResI = scalbn((B * C - A * D) / Denom, -DenomLogB,
14397  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
14398  if (ResR.isNaN() && ResI.isNaN()) {
14399  if (Denom.isPosZero() && (!A.isNaN() || !B.isNaN())) {
14400  ResR = APFloat::getInf(ResR.getSemantics(), C.isNegative()) * A;
14401  ResI = APFloat::getInf(ResR.getSemantics(), C.isNegative()) * B;
14402  } else if ((A.isInfinity() || B.isInfinity()) && C.isFinite() &&
14403  D.isFinite()) {
14404  A = APFloat::copySign(
14405  APFloat(A.getSemantics(), A.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), A);
14406  B = APFloat::copySign(
14407  APFloat(B.getSemantics(), B.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), B);
14408  ResR = APFloat::getInf(ResR.getSemantics()) * (A * C + B * D);
14409  ResI = APFloat::getInf(ResI.getSemantics()) * (B * C - A * D);
14410  } else if (MaxCD.isInfinity() && A.isFinite() && B.isFinite()) {
14411  C = APFloat::copySign(
14412  APFloat(C.getSemantics(), C.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), C);
14413  D = APFloat::copySign(
14414  APFloat(D.getSemantics(), D.isInfinity() ? 1 : 0), D);
14415  ResR = APFloat::getZero(ResR.getSemantics()) * (A * C + B * D);
14416  ResI = APFloat::getZero(ResI.getSemantics()) * (B * C - A * D);
14417  }
14418  }
14419  }
14420  } else {
14421  if (RHS.getComplexIntReal() == 0 && RHS.getComplexIntImag() == 0)
14422  return Error(E, diag::note_expr_divide_by_zero);
14423 
14424  ComplexValue LHS = Result;
14425  APSInt Den = RHS.getComplexIntReal() * RHS.getComplexIntReal() +
14426  RHS.getComplexIntImag() * RHS.getComplexIntImag();
14427  Result.getComplexIntReal() =
14428  (LHS.getComplexIntReal() * RHS.getComplexIntReal() +
14429  LHS.getComplexIntImag() * RHS.getComplexIntImag()) / Den;
14430  Result.getComplexIntImag() =
14431  (LHS.getComplexIntImag() * RHS.getComplexIntReal() -
14432  LHS.getComplexIntReal() * RHS.getComplexIntImag()) / Den;
14433  }
14434  break;
14435  }
14436 
14437  return true;
14438 }
14439 
14440 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitUnaryOperator(const UnaryOperator *E) {
14441  // Get the operand value into 'Result'.
14442  if (!Visit(E->getSubExpr()))
14443  return false;
14444 
14445  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
14446  default:
14447  return Error(E);
14448  case UO_Extension:
14449  return true;
14450  case UO_Plus:
14451  // The result is always just the subexpr.
14452  return true;
14453  case UO_Minus:
14454  if (Result.isComplexFloat()) {
14455  Result.getComplexFloatReal().changeSign();
14456  Result.getComplexFloatImag().changeSign();
14457  }
14458  else {
14459  Result.getComplexIntReal() = -Result.getComplexIntReal();
14460  Result.getComplexIntImag() = -Result.getComplexIntImag();
14461  }
14462  return true;
14463  case UO_Not:
14464  if (Result.isComplexFloat())
14465  Result.getComplexFloatImag().changeSign();
14466  else
14467  Result.getComplexIntImag() = -Result.getComplexIntImag();
14468  return true;
14469  }
14470 }
14471 
14472 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitInitListExpr(const InitListExpr *E) {
14473  if (E->getNumInits() == 2) {
14474  if (E->getType()->isComplexType()) {
14475  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14476  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getInit(0), Result.FloatReal, Info))
14477  return false;
14478  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getInit(1), Result.FloatImag, Info))
14479  return false;
14480  } else {
14481  Result.makeComplexInt();
14482  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getInit(0), Result.IntReal, Info))
14483  return false;
14484  if (!EvaluateInteger(E->getInit(1), Result.IntImag, Info))
14485  return false;
14486  }
14487  return true;
14488  }
14489  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitInitListExpr(E);
14490 }
14491 
14492 bool ComplexExprEvaluator::VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
14493  switch (E->getBuiltinCallee()) {
14494  case Builtin::BI__builtin_complex:
14495  Result.makeComplexFloat();
14496  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(0), Result.FloatReal, Info))
14497  return false;
14498  if (!EvaluateFloat(E->getArg(1), Result.FloatImag, Info))
14499  return false;
14500  return true;
14501 
14502  default:
14503  break;
14504  }
14505 
14506  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCallExpr(E);
14507 }

14509 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14510 // Atomic expression evaluation, essentially just handling the NonAtomicToAtomic
14511 // implicit conversion.
14512 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14513 
14514 namespace {
14515 class AtomicExprEvaluator :
14516  public ExprEvaluatorBase<AtomicExprEvaluator> {
14517  const LValue *This;
14518  APValue &Result;
14519 public:
14520  AtomicExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &Info, const LValue *This, APValue &Result)
14521  : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(Info), This(This), Result(Result) {}
14522 
14523  bool Success(const APValue &V, const Expr *E) {
14524  Result = V;
14525  return true;
14526  }
14527 
14528  bool ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) {
14529  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(
14530  E->getType()->castAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType());
14531  // For atomic-qualified class (and array) types in C++, initialize the
14532  // _Atomic-wrapped subobject directly, in-place.
14533  return This ? EvaluateInPlace(Result, Info, *This, &VIE)
14534  : Evaluate(Result, Info, &VIE);
14535  }
14536 
14537  bool VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
14538  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
14539  default:
14540  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
14541  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
14542  return This ? EvaluateInPlace(Result, Info, *This, E->getSubExpr())
14543  : Evaluate(Result, Info, E->getSubExpr());
14544  }
14545  }
14546 };
14547 } // end anonymous namespace
14548 
14549 static bool EvaluateAtomic(const Expr *E, const LValue *This, APValue &Result,
14550  EvalInfo &Info) {
14551  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14552  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isAtomicType());
14553  return AtomicExprEvaluator(Info, This, Result).Visit(E);
14554 }
14555 
14556 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14557 // Void expression evaluation, primarily for a cast to void on the LHS of a
14558 // comma operator
14559 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14560 
14561 namespace {
14562 class VoidExprEvaluator
14563  : public ExprEvaluatorBase<VoidExprEvaluator> {
14564 public:
14565  VoidExprEvaluator(EvalInfo &Info) : ExprEvaluatorBaseTy(Info) {}
14566 
14567  bool Success(const APValue &V, const Expr *e) { return true; }
14568 
14569  bool ZeroInitialization(const Expr *E) { return true; }
14570 
14571  bool VisitCastExpr(const CastExpr *E) {
14572  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
14573  default:
14574  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCastExpr(E);
14575  case CK_ToVoid:
14576  VisitIgnoredValue(E->getSubExpr());
14577  return true;
14578  }
14579  }
14580 
14581  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
14582  switch (E->getBuiltinCallee()) {
14583  case Builtin::BI__assume:
14584  case Builtin::BI__builtin_assume:
14585  // The argument is not evaluated!
14586  return true;
14587 
14588  case Builtin::BI__builtin_operator_delete:
14589  return HandleOperatorDeleteCall(Info, E);
14590 
14591  default:
14592  break;
14593  }
14594 
14595  return ExprEvaluatorBaseTy::VisitCallExpr(E);
14596  }
14597 
14598  bool VisitCXXDeleteExpr(const CXXDeleteExpr *E);
14599 };
14600 } // end anonymous namespace
14601 
14602 bool VoidExprEvaluator::VisitCXXDeleteExpr(const CXXDeleteExpr *E) {
14603  // We cannot speculatively evaluate a delete expression.
14604  if (Info.SpeculativeEvaluationDepth)
14605  return false;
14606 
14607  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = E->getOperatorDelete();
14608  if (!OperatorDelete->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
14609  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_new_non_replaceable)
14610  << isa<CXXMethodDecl>(OperatorDelete) << OperatorDelete;
14611  return false;
14612  }
14613 
14614  const Expr *Arg = E->getArgument();
14615 
14616  LValue Pointer;
14617  if (!EvaluatePointer(Arg, Pointer, Info))
14618  return false;
14619  if (Pointer.Designator.Invalid)
14620  return false;
14621 
14622  // Deleting a null pointer has no effect.
14623  if (Pointer.isNullPointer()) {
14624  // This is the only case where we need to produce an extension warning:
14625  // the only other way we can succeed is if we find a dynamic allocation,
14626  // and we will have warned when we allocated it in that case.
14627  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
14628  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_new);
14629  return true;
14630  }
14631 
14632  Optional<DynAlloc *> Alloc = CheckDeleteKind(
14633  Info, E, Pointer, E->isArrayForm() ? DynAlloc::ArrayNew : DynAlloc::New);
14634  if (!Alloc)
14635  return false;
14636  QualType AllocType = Pointer.Base.getDynamicAllocType();
14637 
14638  // For the non-array case, the designator must be empty if the static type
14639  // does not have a virtual destructor.
14640  if (!E->isArrayForm() && Pointer.Designator.Entries.size() != 0 &&
14641  !hasVirtualDestructor(Arg->getType()->getPointeeType())) {
14642  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_delete_base_nonvirt_dtor)
14643  << Arg->getType()->getPointeeType() << AllocType;
14644  return false;
14645  }
14646 
14647  // For a class type with a virtual destructor, the selected operator delete
14648  // is the one looked up when building the destructor.
14649  if (!E->isArrayForm() && !E->isGlobalDelete()) {
14650  const FunctionDecl *VirtualDelete = getVirtualOperatorDelete(AllocType);
14651  if (VirtualDelete &&
14652  !VirtualDelete->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
14653  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_new_non_replaceable)
14654  << isa<CXXMethodDecl>(VirtualDelete) << VirtualDelete;
14655  return false;
14656  }
14657  }
14658 
14659  if (!HandleDestruction(Info, E->getExprLoc(), Pointer.getLValueBase(),
14660  (*Alloc)->Value, AllocType))
14661  return false;
14662 
14663  if (!Info.HeapAllocs.erase(Pointer.Base.dyn_cast<DynamicAllocLValue>())) {
14664  // The element was already erased. This means the destructor call also
14665  // deleted the object.
14666  // FIXME: This probably results in undefined behavior before we get this
14667  // far, and should be diagnosed elsewhere first.
14668  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_double_delete);
14669  return false;
14670  }
14671 
14672  return true;
14673 }
14674 
14675 static bool EvaluateVoid(const Expr *E, EvalInfo &Info) {
14676  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14677  assert(E->isPRValue() && E->getType()->isVoidType());
14678  return VoidExprEvaluator(Info).Visit(E);
14679 }
14680 
14681 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14682 // Top level Expr::EvaluateAsRValue method.
14683 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
14684 
14685 static bool Evaluate(APValue &Result, EvalInfo &Info, const Expr *E) {
14686  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14687  // In C, function designators are not lvalues, but we evaluate them as if they
14688  // are.
14689  QualType T = E->getType();
14690  if (E->isGLValue() || T->isFunctionType()) {
14691  LValue LV;
14692  if (!EvaluateLValue(E, LV, Info))
14693  return false;
14694  LV.moveInto(Result);
14695  } else if (T->isVectorType()) {
14696  if (!EvaluateVector(E, Result, Info))
14697  return false;
14698  } else if (T->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
14699  if (!IntExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E))
14700  return false;
14701  } else if (T->hasPointerRepresentation()) {
14702  LValue LV;
14703  if (!EvaluatePointer(E, LV, Info))
14704  return false;
14705  LV.moveInto(Result);
14706  } else if (T->isRealFloatingType()) {
14707  llvm::APFloat F(0.0);
14708  if (!EvaluateFloat(E, F, Info))
14709  return false;
14710  Result = APValue(F);
14711  } else if (T->isAnyComplexType()) {
14712  ComplexValue C;
14713  if (!EvaluateComplex(E, C, Info))
14714  return false;
14715  C.moveInto(Result);
14716  } else if (T->isFixedPointType()) {
14717  if (!FixedPointExprEvaluator(Info, Result).Visit(E)) return false;
14718  } else if (T->isMemberPointerType()) {
14719  MemberPtr P;
14720  if (!EvaluateMemberPointer(E, P, Info))
14721  return false;
14722  P.moveInto(Result);
14723  return true;
14724  } else if (T->isArrayType()) {
14725  LValue LV;
14726  APValue &Value =
14727  Info.CurrentCall->createTemporary(E, T, ScopeKind::FullExpression, LV);
14728  if (!EvaluateArray(E, LV, Value, Info))
14729  return false;
14730  Result = Value;
14731  } else if (T->isRecordType()) {
14732  LValue LV;
14733  APValue &Value =
14734  Info.CurrentCall->createTemporary(E, T, ScopeKind::FullExpression, LV);
14735  if (!EvaluateRecord(E, LV, Value, Info))
14736  return false;
14737  Result = Value;
14738  } else if (T->isVoidType()) {
14739  if (!Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
14740  Info.CCEDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_nonliteral)
14741  << E->getType();
14742  if (!EvaluateVoid(E, Info))
14743  return false;
14744  } else if (T->isAtomicType()) {
14745  QualType Unqual = T.getAtomicUnqualifiedType();
14746  if (Unqual->isArrayType() || Unqual->isRecordType()) {
14747  LValue LV;
14748  APValue &Value = Info.CurrentCall->createTemporary(
14749  E, Unqual, ScopeKind::FullExpression, LV);
14750  if (!EvaluateAtomic(E, &LV, Value, Info))
14751  return false;
14752  } else {
14753  if (!EvaluateAtomic(E, nullptr, Result, Info))
14754  return false;
14755  }
14756  } else if (Info.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
14757  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_constexpr_nonliteral) << E->getType();
14758  return false;
14759  } else {
14760  Info.FFDiag(E, diag::note_invalid_subexpr_in_const_expr);
14761  return false;
14762  }
14763 
14764  return true;
14765 }
14766 
14767 /// EvaluateInPlace - Evaluate an expression in-place in an APValue. In some
14768 /// cases, the in-place evaluation is essential, since later initializers for
14769 /// an object can indirectly refer to subobjects which were initialized earlier.
14770 static bool EvaluateInPlace(APValue &Result, EvalInfo &Info, const LValue &This,
14771  const Expr *E, bool AllowNonLiteralTypes) {
14772  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14773 
14774  if (!AllowNonLiteralTypes && !CheckLiteralType(Info, E, &This))
14775  return false;
14776 
14777  if (E->isPRValue()) {
14778  // Evaluate arrays and record types in-place, so that later initializers can
14779  // refer to earlier-initialized members of the object.
14780  QualType T = E->getType();
14781  if (T->isArrayType())
14782  return EvaluateArray(E, This, Result, Info);
14783  else if (T->isRecordType())
14784  return EvaluateRecord(E, This, Result, Info);
14785  else if (T->isAtomicType()) {
14786  QualType Unqual = T.getAtomicUnqualifiedType();
14787  if (Unqual->isArrayType() || Unqual->isRecordType())
14788  return EvaluateAtomic(E, &This, Result, Info);
14789  }
14790  }
14791 
14792  // For any other type, in-place evaluation is unimportant.
14793  return Evaluate(Result, Info, E);
14794 }
14795 
14796 /// EvaluateAsRValue - Try to evaluate this expression, performing an implicit
14797 /// lvalue-to-rvalue cast if it is an lvalue.
14798 static bool EvaluateAsRValue(EvalInfo &Info, const Expr *E, APValue &Result) {
14799  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14800  if (Info.EnableNewConstInterp) {
14801  if (!Info.Ctx.getInterpContext().evaluateAsRValue(Info, E, Result))
14802  return false;
14803  } else {
14804  if (E->getType().isNull())
14805  return false;
14806 
14807  if (!CheckLiteralType(Info, E))
14808  return false;
14809 
14810  if (!::Evaluate(Result, Info, E))
14811  return false;
14812 
14813  if (E->isGLValue()) {
14814  LValue LV;
14815  LV.setFrom(Info.Ctx, Result);
14816  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, E->getType(), LV, Result))
14817  return false;
14818  }
14819  }
14820 
14821  // Check this core constant expression is a constant expression.
14822  return CheckConstantExpression(Info, E->getExprLoc(), E->getType(), Result,
14823  ConstantExprKind::Normal) &&
14824  CheckMemoryLeaks(Info);
14825 }
14826 
14827 static bool FastEvaluateAsRValue(const Expr *Exp, Expr::EvalResult &Result,
14828  const ASTContext &Ctx, bool &IsConst) {
14829  // Fast-path evaluations of integer literals, since we sometimes see files
14830  // containing vast quantities of these.
14831  if (const IntegerLiteral *L = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(Exp)) {
14832  Result.Val = APValue(APSInt(L->getValue(),
14833  L->getType()->isUnsignedIntegerType()));
14834  IsConst = true;
14835  return true;
14836  }
14837 
14838  // This case should be rare, but we need to check it before we check on
14839  // the type below.
14840  if (Exp->getType().isNull()) {
14841  IsConst = false;
14842  return true;
14843  }
14844 
14845  // FIXME: Evaluating values of large array and record types can cause
14846  // performance problems. Only do so in C++11 for now.
14847  if (Exp->isPRValue() &&
14848  (Exp->getType()->isArrayType() || Exp->getType()->isRecordType()) &&
14849  !Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
14850  IsConst = false;
14851  return true;
14852  }
14853  return false;
14854 }
14855 
14856 static bool hasUnacceptableSideEffect(Expr::EvalStatus &Result,
14857  Expr::SideEffectsKind SEK) {
14858  return (SEK < Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects && Result.HasSideEffects) ||
14859  (SEK < Expr::SE_AllowUndefinedBehavior && Result.HasUndefinedBehavior);
14860 }
14861 
14862 static bool EvaluateAsRValue(const Expr *E, Expr::EvalResult &Result,
14863  const ASTContext &Ctx, EvalInfo &Info) {
14864  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14865  bool IsConst;
14866  if (FastEvaluateAsRValue(E, Result, Ctx, IsConst))
14867  return IsConst;
14868 
14869  return EvaluateAsRValue(Info, E, Result.Val);
14870 }
14871 
14872 static bool EvaluateAsInt(const Expr *E, Expr::EvalResult &ExprResult,
14873  const ASTContext &Ctx,
14874  Expr::SideEffectsKind AllowSideEffects,
14875  EvalInfo &Info) {
14876  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14877  if (!E->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
14878  return false;
14879 
14880  if (!::EvaluateAsRValue(E, ExprResult, Ctx, Info) ||
14881  !ExprResult.Val.isInt() ||
14882  hasUnacceptableSideEffect(ExprResult, AllowSideEffects))
14883  return false;
14884 
14885  return true;
14886 }
14887 
14888 static bool EvaluateAsFixedPoint(const Expr *E, Expr::EvalResult &ExprResult,
14889  const ASTContext &Ctx,
14890  Expr::SideEffectsKind AllowSideEffects,
14891  EvalInfo &Info) {
14892  assert(!E->isValueDependent());
14893  if (!E->getType()->isFixedPointType())
14894  return false;
14895 
14896  if (!::EvaluateAsRValue(E, ExprResult, Ctx, Info))
14897  return false;
14898 
14899  if (!ExprResult.Val.isFixedPoint() ||
14900  hasUnacceptableSideEffect(ExprResult, AllowSideEffects))
14901  return false;
14902 
14903  return true;
14904 }

14906 /// EvaluateAsRValue - Return true if this is a constant which we can fold using
14907 /// any crazy technique (that has nothing to do with language standards) that
14908 /// we want to. If this function returns true, it returns the folded constant
14909 /// in Result. If this expression is a glvalue, an lvalue-to-rvalue conversion
14910 /// will be applied to the result.
14911 bool Expr::EvaluateAsRValue(EvalResult &Result, const ASTContext &Ctx,
14912  bool InConstantContext) const {
14913  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
14914  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
14915  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Result, EvalInfo::EM_IgnoreSideEffects);
14916  Info.InConstantContext = InConstantContext;
14917  return ::EvaluateAsRValue(this, Result, Ctx, Info);
14918 }

14923  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");

14925  return EvaluateAsRValue(Scratch, Ctx, InConstantContext) &&
14926  HandleConversionToBool(Scratch.Val, Result);

14949 bool Expr::EvaluateAsFloat(APFloat &Result, const ASTContext &Ctx,
14950  SideEffectsKind AllowSideEffects,
14951  bool InConstantContext) const {
14952  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
14953  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
14954 
14955  if (!getType()->isRealFloatingType())
14956  return false;
14957 
14958  EvalResult ExprResult;
14959  if (!EvaluateAsRValue(ExprResult, Ctx, InConstantContext) ||
14960  !ExprResult.Val.isFloat() ||
14961  hasUnacceptableSideEffect(ExprResult, AllowSideEffects))
14962  return false;
14963 
14964  Result = ExprResult.Val.getFloat();
14965  return true;
14966 }
14967 
14968 bool Expr::EvaluateAsLValue(EvalResult &Result, const ASTContext &Ctx,
14969  bool InConstantContext) const {
14970  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
14971  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
14972 
14973  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Result, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantFold);
14974  Info.InConstantContext = InConstantContext;
14975  LValue LV;
14976  CheckedTemporaries CheckedTemps;
14977  if (!EvaluateLValue(this, LV, Info) || !Info.discardCleanups() ||
14978  Result.HasSideEffects ||
14979  !CheckLValueConstantExpression(Info, getExprLoc(),
14980  Ctx.getLValueReferenceType(getType()), LV,
14981  ConstantExprKind::Normal, CheckedTemps))
14982  return false;
14983 
14984  LV.moveInto(Result.Val);
14985  return true;
14986 }
14987 
14988 static bool EvaluateDestruction(const ASTContext &Ctx, APValue::LValueBase Base,
14989  APValue DestroyedValue, QualType Type,
14990  SourceLocation Loc, Expr::EvalStatus &EStatus,
14991  bool IsConstantDestruction) {
14992  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, EStatus,
14993  IsConstantDestruction ? EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression
14994  : EvalInfo::EM_ConstantFold);
14995  Info.setEvaluatingDecl(Base, DestroyedValue,
14996  EvalInfo::EvaluatingDeclKind::Dtor);
14997  Info.InConstantContext = IsConstantDestruction;
14998 
14999  LValue LVal;
15000  LVal.set(Base);
15001 
15002  if (!HandleDestruction(Info, Loc, Base, DestroyedValue, Type) ||
15003  EStatus.HasSideEffects)
15004  return false;
15005 
15006  if (!Info.discardCleanups())
15007  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled cleanup; missing full expression marker?");
15008 
15009  return true;
15010 }
15011 
15012 bool Expr::EvaluateAsConstantExpr(EvalResult &Result, const ASTContext &Ctx,
15013  ConstantExprKind Kind) const {
15014  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15015  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15016 
15017  EvalInfo::EvaluationMode EM = EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression;
15018  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Result, EM);
15019  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15020 
15021  // The type of the object we're initializing is 'const T' for a class NTTP.
15022  QualType T = getType();
15023  if (Kind == ConstantExprKind::ClassTemplateArgument)
15024  T.addConst();
15025 
15026  // If we're evaluating a prvalue, fake up a MaterializeTemporaryExpr to
15027  // represent the result of the evaluation. CheckConstantExpression ensures
15028  // this doesn't escape.
15029  MaterializeTemporaryExpr BaseMTE(T, const_cast<Expr*>(this), true);
15030  APValue::LValueBase Base(&BaseMTE);
15031 
15032  Info.setEvaluatingDecl(Base, Result.Val);
15033  LValue LVal;
15034  LVal.set(Base);
15035 
15036  if (!::EvaluateInPlace(Result.Val, Info, LVal, this) || Result.HasSideEffects)
15037  return false;
15038 
15039  if (!Info.discardCleanups())
15040  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled cleanup; missing full expression marker?");
15041 
15042  if (!CheckConstantExpression(Info, getExprLoc(), getStorageType(Ctx, this),
15043  Result.Val, Kind))
15044  return false;
15045  if (!CheckMemoryLeaks(Info))
15046  return false;
15047 
15048  // If this is a class template argument, it's required to have constant
15049  // destruction too.
15050  if (Kind == ConstantExprKind::ClassTemplateArgument &&
15051  (!EvaluateDestruction(Ctx, Base, Result.Val, T, getBeginLoc(), Result,
15052  true) ||
15053  Result.HasSideEffects)) {
15054  // FIXME: Prefix a note to indicate that the problem is lack of constant
15055  // destruction.
15056  return false;
15057  }
15058 
15059  return true;
15060 }
15061 
15062 bool Expr::EvaluateAsInitializer(APValue &Value, const ASTContext &Ctx,
15063  const VarDecl *VD,
15064  SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> &Notes,
15065  bool IsConstantInitialization) const {
15066  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15067  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15068 
15069  // FIXME: Evaluating initializers for large array and record types can cause
15070  // performance problems. Only do so in C++11 for now.
15071  if (isPRValue() && (getType()->isArrayType() || getType()->isRecordType()) &&
15072  !Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
15073  return false;
15074 
15075  Expr::EvalStatus EStatus;
15076  EStatus.Diag = &Notes;
15077 
15078  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, EStatus,
15079  (IsConstantInitialization && Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
15080  ? EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression
15081  : EvalInfo::EM_ConstantFold);
15082  Info.setEvaluatingDecl(VD, Value);
15083  Info.InConstantContext = IsConstantInitialization;
15084 
15085  SourceLocation DeclLoc = VD->getLocation();
15086  QualType DeclTy = VD->getType();
15087 
15088  if (Info.EnableNewConstInterp) {
15089  auto &InterpCtx = const_cast<ASTContext &>(Ctx).getInterpContext();
15090  if (!InterpCtx.evaluateAsInitializer(Info, VD, Value))
15091  return false;
15092  } else {
15093  LValue LVal;
15094  LVal.set(VD);
15095 
15096  if (!EvaluateInPlace(Value, Info, LVal, this,
15097  /*AllowNonLiteralTypes=*/true) ||
15098  EStatus.HasSideEffects)
15099  return false;
15100 
15101  // At this point, any lifetime-extended temporaries are completely
15102  // initialized.
15103  Info.performLifetimeExtension();
15104 
15105  if (!Info.discardCleanups())
15106  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled cleanup; missing full expression marker?");
15107  }
15108  return CheckConstantExpression(Info, DeclLoc, DeclTy, Value,
15109  ConstantExprKind::Normal) &&
15110  CheckMemoryLeaks(Info);
15111 }
15112 
15113 bool VarDecl::evaluateDestruction(
15114  SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> &Notes) const {
15115  Expr::EvalStatus EStatus;
15116  EStatus.Diag = &Notes;
15117 
15118  // Only treat the destruction as constant destruction if we formally have
15119  // constant initialization (or are usable in a constant expression).
15120  bool IsConstantDestruction = hasConstantInitialization();
15121 
15122  // Make a copy of the value for the destructor to mutate, if we know it.
15123  // Otherwise, treat the value as default-initialized; if the destructor works
15124  // anyway, then the destruction is constant (and must be essentially empty).
15125  APValue DestroyedValue;
15126  if (getEvaluatedValue() && !getEvaluatedValue()->isAbsent())
15127  DestroyedValue = *getEvaluatedValue();
15128  else if (!getDefaultInitValue(getType(), DestroyedValue))
15129  return false;
15130 
15131  if (!EvaluateDestruction(getASTContext(), this, std::move(DestroyedValue),
15132  getType(), getLocation(), EStatus,
15133  IsConstantDestruction) ||
15134  EStatus.HasSideEffects)
15135  return false;
15136 
15137  ensureEvaluatedStmt()->HasConstantDestruction = true;
15138  return true;
15139 }
15140 
15141 /// isEvaluatable - Call EvaluateAsRValue to see if this expression can be
15142 /// constant folded, but discard the result.
15143 bool Expr::isEvaluatable(const ASTContext &Ctx, SideEffectsKind SEK) const {
15144  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15145  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15146 
15147  EvalResult Result;
15148  return EvaluateAsRValue(Result, Ctx, /* in constant context */ true) &&
15149  !hasUnacceptableSideEffect(Result, SEK);
15150 }
15151 
15152 APSInt Expr::EvaluateKnownConstInt(const ASTContext &Ctx,
15153  SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> *Diag) const {
15154  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15155  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15156 
15157  EvalResult EVResult;
15158  EVResult.Diag = Diag;
15159  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, EVResult, EvalInfo::EM_IgnoreSideEffects);
15160  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15161 
15162  bool Result = ::EvaluateAsRValue(this, EVResult, Ctx, Info);
15163  (void)Result;
15164  assert(Result && "Could not evaluate expression");
15165  assert(EVResult.Val.isInt() && "Expression did not evaluate to integer");
15166 
15167  return EVResult.Val.getInt();
15168 }

15170 APSInt Expr::EvaluateKnownConstIntCheckOverflow(
15171  const ASTContext &Ctx, SmallVectorImpl<PartialDiagnosticAt> *Diag) const {
15172  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15173  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15174 
15175  EvalResult EVResult;
15176  EVResult.Diag = Diag;
15177  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, EVResult, EvalInfo::EM_IgnoreSideEffects);
15178  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15179  Info.CheckingForUndefinedBehavior = true;
15180 
15181  bool Result = ::EvaluateAsRValue(Info, this, EVResult.Val);
15182  (void)Result;
15183  assert(Result && "Could not evaluate expression");
15184  assert(EVResult.Val.isInt() && "Expression did not evaluate to integer");
15185 
15186  return EVResult.Val.getInt();
15187 }

15189 void Expr::EvaluateForOverflow(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
15190  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15191  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15192 
15193  bool IsConst;
15194  EvalResult EVResult;
15195  if (!FastEvaluateAsRValue(this, EVResult, Ctx, IsConst)) {
15196  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, EVResult, EvalInfo::EM_IgnoreSideEffects);
15197  Info.CheckingForUndefinedBehavior = true;
15198  (void)::EvaluateAsRValue(Info, this, EVResult.Val);
15199  }
15200 }

15202 bool Expr::EvalResult::isGlobalLValue() const {
15203  assert(Val.isLValue());
15204  return IsGlobalLValue(Val.getLValueBase());
15205 }
15206 
15207 /// isIntegerConstantExpr - this recursive routine will test if an expression is
15208 /// an integer constant expression.
15209 
15210 /// FIXME: Pass up a reason why! Invalid operation in i-c-e, division by zero,
15211 /// comma, etc
15212 
15213 // CheckICE - This function does the fundamental ICE checking: the returned
15214 // ICEDiag contains an ICEKind indicating whether the expression is an ICE,
15215 // and a (possibly null) SourceLocation indicating the location of the problem.
15216 //
15217 // Note that to reduce code duplication, this helper does no evaluation
15218 // itself; the caller checks whether the expression is evaluatable, and
15219 // in the rare cases where CheckICE actually cares about the evaluated
15220 // value, it calls into Evaluate.
15221 
15222 namespace {
15223 
15224 enum ICEKind {
15225  /// This expression is an ICE.
15226  IK_ICE,
15227  /// This expression is not an ICE, but if it isn't evaluated, it's
15228  /// a legal subexpression for an ICE. This return value is used to handle
15229  /// the comma operator in C99 mode, and non-constant subexpressions.
15230  IK_ICEIfUnevaluated,
15231  /// This expression is not an ICE, and is not a legal subexpression for one.
15232  IK_NotICE
15233 };
15234 
15235 struct ICEDiag {
15236  ICEKind Kind;
15237  SourceLocation Loc;
15238 
15239  ICEDiag(ICEKind IK, SourceLocation l) : Kind(IK), Loc(l) {}
15240 };
15241 
15242 }
15243 
15244 static ICEDiag NoDiag() { return ICEDiag(IK_ICE, SourceLocation()); }
15245 
15246 static ICEDiag Worst(ICEDiag A, ICEDiag B) { return A.Kind >= B.Kind ? A : B; }
15247 
15248 static ICEDiag CheckEvalInICE(const Expr* E, const ASTContext &Ctx) {
15249  Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
15250  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15251  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression);
15252 
15253  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15254  if (!::EvaluateAsRValue(E, EVResult, Ctx, Info) || EVResult.HasSideEffects ||
15255  !EVResult.Val.isInt())
15256  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15257 
15258  return NoDiag();
15259 }
15260 
15261 static ICEDiag CheckICE(const Expr* E, const ASTContext &Ctx) {
15262  assert(!E->isValueDependent() && "Should not see value dependent exprs!");
15263  if (!E->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
15264  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15265 
15266  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
15267 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Node)
15268 #define STMT(Node, Base) case Expr::Node##Class:
15269 #define EXPR(Node, Base)
15270 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
15271  case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
15272  case Expr::FloatingLiteralClass:
15273  case Expr::ImaginaryLiteralClass:
15274  case Expr::StringLiteralClass:
15275  case Expr::ArraySubscriptExprClass:
15276  case Expr::MatrixSubscriptExprClass:
15277  case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
15278  case Expr::OMPArrayShapingExprClass:
15279  case Expr::OMPIteratorExprClass:
15280  case Expr::MemberExprClass:
15281  case Expr::CompoundAssignOperatorClass:
15282  case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
15283  case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
15284  case Expr::DesignatedInitExprClass:
15285  case Expr::ArrayInitLoopExprClass:
15286  case Expr::ArrayInitIndexExprClass:
15287  case Expr::NoInitExprClass:
15288  case Expr::DesignatedInitUpdateExprClass:
15289  case Expr::ImplicitValueInitExprClass:
15290  case Expr::ParenListExprClass:
15291  case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
15292  case Expr::AddrLabelExprClass:
15293  case Expr::StmtExprClass:
15294  case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass:
15295  case Expr::CUDAKernelCallExprClass:
15296  case Expr::CXXAddrspaceCastExprClass:
15297  case Expr::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
15298  case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass:
15299  case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass:
15300  case Expr::MSPropertyRefExprClass:
15301  case Expr::MSPropertySubscriptExprClass:
15302  case Expr::CXXNullPtrLiteralExprClass:
15303  case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
15304  case Expr::CXXThisExprClass:
15305  case Expr::CXXThrowExprClass:
15306  case Expr::CXXNewExprClass:
15307  case Expr::CXXDeleteExprClass:
15308  case Expr::CXXPseudoDestructorExprClass:
15309  case Expr::UnresolvedLookupExprClass:
15310  case Expr::TypoExprClass:
15311  case Expr::RecoveryExprClass:
15312  case Expr::DependentScopeDeclRefExprClass:
15313  case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass:
15314  case Expr::CXXInheritedCtorInitExprClass:
15315  case Expr::CXXStdInitializerListExprClass:
15316  case Expr::CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
15317  case Expr::ExprWithCleanupsClass:
15318  case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass:
15319  case Expr::CXXUnresolvedConstructExprClass:
15320  case Expr::CXXDependentScopeMemberExprClass:
15321  case Expr::UnresolvedMemberExprClass:
15322  case Expr::ObjCStringLiteralClass:
15323  case Expr::ObjCBoxedExprClass:
15324  case Expr::ObjCArrayLiteralClass:
15325  case Expr::ObjCDictionaryLiteralClass:
15326  case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
15327  case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
15328  case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
15329  case Expr::ObjCProtocolExprClass:
15330  case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
15331  case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
15332  case Expr::ObjCSubscriptRefExprClass:
15333  case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
15334  case Expr::ObjCAvailabilityCheckExprClass:
15335  case Expr::ShuffleVectorExprClass:
15336  case Expr::ConvertVectorExprClass:
15337  case Expr::BlockExprClass:
15338  case Expr::NoStmtClass:
15339  case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
15340  case Expr::PackExpansionExprClass:
15341  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmPackExprClass:
15342  case Expr::FunctionParmPackExprClass:
15343  case Expr::AsTypeExprClass:
15344  case Expr::ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExprClass:
15345  case Expr::MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
15346  case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
15347  case Expr::AtomicExprClass:
15348  case Expr::LambdaExprClass:
15349  case Expr::CXXFoldExprClass:
15350  case Expr::CoawaitExprClass:
15351  case Expr::DependentCoawaitExprClass:
15352  case Expr::CoyieldExprClass:
15353  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExprClass:
15354  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExprClass:
15355  case Expr::SYCLUniqueStableNameExprClass:
15356  case Expr::SYCLUniqueStableIdExprClass:
15357  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15358 
15359  case Expr::InitListExprClass: {
15360  // C++03 [dcl.init]p13: If T is a scalar type, then a declaration of the
15361  // form "T x = { a };" is equivalent to "T x = a;".
15362  // Unless we're initializing a reference, T is a scalar as it is known to be
15363  // of integral or enumeration type.
15364  if (E->isPRValue())
15365  if (cast<InitListExpr>(E)->getNumInits() == 1)
15366  return CheckICE(cast<InitListExpr>(E)->getInit(0), Ctx);
15367  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15368  }
15369 
15370  case Expr::SizeOfPackExprClass:
15371  case Expr::GNUNullExprClass:
15372  case Expr::SourceLocExprClass:
15373  return NoDiag();
15374 
15375  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
15376  return
15377  CheckICE(cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement(), Ctx);
15378 
15379  case Expr::ConstantExprClass:
15380  return CheckICE(cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15381 
15382  case Expr::ParenExprClass:
15383  return CheckICE(cast<ParenExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15384  case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
15385  return CheckICE(cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)->getResultExpr(), Ctx);
15386  case Expr::IntegerLiteralClass:
15387  case Expr::FixedPointLiteralClass:
15388  case Expr::CharacterLiteralClass:
15389  case Expr::ObjCBoolLiteralExprClass:
15390  case Expr::CXXBoolLiteralExprClass:
15391  case Expr::CXXScalarValueInitExprClass:
15392  case Expr::TypeTraitExprClass:
15393  case Expr::ConceptSpecializationExprClass:
15394  case Expr::RequiresExprClass:
15395  case Expr::ArrayTypeTraitExprClass:
15396  case Expr::ExpressionTraitExprClass:
15397  case Expr::CXXNoexceptExprClass:
15398  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExprClass:
15399  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinNumBasesExprClass:
15400  return NoDiag();
15401  case Expr::CallExprClass:
15402  case Expr::CXXOperatorCallExprClass: {
15403  // C99 6.6/3 allows function calls within unevaluated subexpressions of
15404  // constant expressions, but they can never be ICEs because an ICE cannot
15405  // contain an operand of (pointer to) function type.
15406  const CallExpr *CE = cast<CallExpr>(E);
15407  if (CE->getBuiltinCallee())
15408  return CheckEvalInICE(E, Ctx);
15409  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15410  }
15411  case Expr::CXXRewrittenBinaryOperatorClass:
15412  return CheckICE(cast<CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator>(E)->getSemanticForm(),
15413  Ctx);
15414  case Expr::DeclRefExprClass: {
15415  const NamedDecl *D = cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl();
15416  if (isa<EnumConstantDecl>(D))
15417  return NoDiag();
15418 
15419  // C++ and OpenCL (FIXME: spec reference?) allow reading const-qualified
15420  // integer variables in constant expressions:
15421  //
15422  // C++ 7.1.5.1p2
15423  // A variable of non-volatile const-qualified integral or enumeration
15424  // type initialized by an ICE can be used in ICEs.
15425  //
15426  // We sometimes use CheckICE to check the C++98 rules in C++11 mode. In
15427  // that mode, use of reference variables should not be allowed.
15428  const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
15429  if (VD && VD->isUsableInConstantExpressions(Ctx) &&
15430  !VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
15431  return NoDiag();
15432 
15433  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15434  }
15435  case Expr::UnaryOperatorClass: {
15436  const UnaryOperator *Exp = cast<UnaryOperator>(E);
15437  switch (Exp->getOpcode()) {
15438  case UO_PostInc:
15439  case UO_PostDec:
15440  case UO_PreInc:
15441  case UO_PreDec:
15442  case UO_AddrOf:
15443  case UO_Deref:
15444  case UO_Coawait:
15445  // C99 6.6/3 allows increment and decrement within unevaluated
15446  // subexpressions of constant expressions, but they can never be ICEs
15447  // because an ICE cannot contain an lvalue operand.
15448  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15449  case UO_Extension:
15450  case UO_LNot:
15451  case UO_Plus:
15452  case UO_Minus:
15453  case UO_Not:
15454  case UO_Real:
15455  case UO_Imag:
15456  return CheckICE(Exp->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15457  }
15458  llvm_unreachable("invalid unary operator class");
15459  }
15460  case Expr::OffsetOfExprClass: {
15461  // Note that per C99, offsetof must be an ICE. And AFAIK, using
15462  // EvaluateAsRValue matches the proposed gcc behavior for cases like
15463  // "offsetof(struct s{int x[4];}, x[1.0])". This doesn't affect
15464  // compliance: we should warn earlier for offsetof expressions with
15465  // array subscripts that aren't ICEs, and if the array subscripts
15466  // are ICEs, the value of the offsetof must be an integer constant.
15467  return CheckEvalInICE(E, Ctx);
15468  }
15469  case Expr::UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExprClass: {
15470  const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *Exp = cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr>(E);
15471  if ((Exp->getKind() == UETT_SizeOf) &&
15472  Exp->getTypeOfArgument()->isVariableArrayType())
15473  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15474  return NoDiag();
15475  }
15476  case Expr::BinaryOperatorClass: {
15477  const BinaryOperator *Exp = cast<BinaryOperator>(E);
15478  switch (Exp->getOpcode()) {
15479  case BO_PtrMemD:
15480  case BO_PtrMemI:
15481  case BO_Assign:
15482  case BO_MulAssign:
15483  case BO_DivAssign:
15484  case BO_RemAssign:
15485  case BO_AddAssign:
15486  case BO_SubAssign:
15487  case BO_ShlAssign:
15488  case BO_ShrAssign:
15489  case BO_AndAssign:
15490  case BO_XorAssign:
15491  case BO_OrAssign:
15492  // C99 6.6/3 allows assignments within unevaluated subexpressions of
15493  // constant expressions, but they can never be ICEs because an ICE cannot
15494  // contain an lvalue operand.
15495  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15496 
15497  case BO_Mul:
15498  case BO_Div:
15499  case BO_Rem:
15500  case BO_Add:
15501  case BO_Sub:
15502  case BO_Shl:
15503  case BO_Shr:
15504  case BO_LT:
15505  case BO_GT:
15506  case BO_LE:
15507  case BO_GE:
15508  case BO_EQ:
15509  case BO_NE:
15510  case BO_And:
15511  case BO_Xor:
15512  case BO_Or:
15513  case BO_Comma:
15514  case BO_Cmp: {
15515  ICEDiag LHSResult = CheckICE(Exp->getLHS(), Ctx);
15516  ICEDiag RHSResult = CheckICE(Exp->getRHS(), Ctx);
15517  if (Exp->getOpcode() == BO_Div ||
15518  Exp->getOpcode() == BO_Rem) {
15519  // EvaluateAsRValue gives an error for undefined Div/Rem, so make sure
15520  // we don't evaluate one.
15521  if (LHSResult.Kind == IK_ICE && RHSResult.Kind == IK_ICE) {
15522  llvm::APSInt REval = Exp->getRHS()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx);
15523  if (REval == 0)
15524  return ICEDiag(IK_ICEIfUnevaluated, E->getBeginLoc());
15525  if (REval.isSigned() && REval.isAllOnes()) {
15526  llvm::APSInt LEval = Exp->getLHS()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx);
15527  if (LEval.isMinSignedValue())
15528  return ICEDiag(IK_ICEIfUnevaluated, E->getBeginLoc());
15529  }
15530  }
15531  }
15532  if (Exp->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
15533  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().C99) {
15534  // C99 6.6p3 introduces a strange edge case: comma can be in an ICE
15535  // if it isn't evaluated.
15536  if (LHSResult.Kind == IK_ICE && RHSResult.Kind == IK_ICE)
15537  return ICEDiag(IK_ICEIfUnevaluated, E->getBeginLoc());
15538  } else {
15539  // In both C89 and C++, commas in ICEs are illegal.
15540  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15541  }
15542  }
15543  return Worst(LHSResult, RHSResult);
15544  }
15545  case BO_LAnd:
15546  case BO_LOr: {
15547  ICEDiag LHSResult = CheckICE(Exp->getLHS(), Ctx);
15548  ICEDiag RHSResult = CheckICE(Exp->getRHS(), Ctx);
15549  if (LHSResult.Kind == IK_ICE && RHSResult.Kind == IK_ICEIfUnevaluated) {
15550  // Rare case where the RHS has a comma "side-effect"; we need
15551  // to actually check the condition to see whether the side
15552  // with the comma is evaluated.
15553  if ((Exp->getOpcode() == BO_LAnd) !=
15554  (Exp->getLHS()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx) == 0))
15555  return RHSResult;
15556  return NoDiag();
15557  }
15558 
15559  return Worst(LHSResult, RHSResult);
15560  }
15561  }
15562  llvm_unreachable("invalid binary operator kind");
15563  }
15564  case Expr::ImplicitCastExprClass:
15565  case Expr::CStyleCastExprClass:
15566  case Expr::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass:
15567  case Expr::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
15568  case Expr::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
15569  case Expr::CXXConstCastExprClass:
15570  case Expr::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass: {
15571  const Expr *SubExpr = cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
15572  if (isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
15573  if (const FloatingLiteral *FL
15574  = dyn_cast<FloatingLiteral>(SubExpr->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
15575  unsigned DestWidth = Ctx.getIntWidth(E->getType());
15576  bool DestSigned = E->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
15577  APSInt IgnoredVal(DestWidth, !DestSigned);
15578  bool Ignored;
15579  // If the value does not fit in the destination type, the behavior is
15580  // undefined, so we are not required to treat it as a constant
15581  // expression.
15582  if (FL->getValue().convertToInteger(IgnoredVal,
15583  llvm::APFloat::rmTowardZero,
15584  &Ignored) & APFloat::opInvalidOp)
15585  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15586  return NoDiag();
15587  }
15588  }
15589  switch (cast<CastExpr>(E)->getCastKind()) {
15590  case CK_LValueToRValue:
15591  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
15592  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
15593  case CK_NoOp:
15594  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
15595  case CK_IntegralCast:
15596  return CheckICE(SubExpr, Ctx);
15597  default:
15598  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15599  }
15600  }
15601  case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass: {
15602  const BinaryConditionalOperator *Exp = cast<BinaryConditionalOperator>(E);
15603  ICEDiag CommonResult = CheckICE(Exp->getCommon(), Ctx);
15604  if (CommonResult.Kind == IK_NotICE) return CommonResult;
15605  ICEDiag FalseResult = CheckICE(Exp->getFalseExpr(), Ctx);
15606  if (FalseResult.Kind == IK_NotICE) return FalseResult;
15607  if (CommonResult.Kind == IK_ICEIfUnevaluated) return CommonResult;
15608  if (FalseResult.Kind == IK_ICEIfUnevaluated &&
15609  Exp->getCommon()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx) != 0) return NoDiag();
15610  return FalseResult;
15611  }
15612  case Expr::ConditionalOperatorClass: {
15613  const ConditionalOperator *Exp = cast<ConditionalOperator>(E);
15614  // If the condition (ignoring parens) is a __builtin_constant_p call,
15615  // then only the true side is actually considered in an integer constant
15616  // expression, and it is fully evaluated. This is an important GNU
15617  // extension. See GCC PR38377 for discussion.
15618  if (const CallExpr *CallCE
15619  = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(Exp->getCond()->IgnoreParenCasts()))
15620  if (CallCE->getBuiltinCallee() == Builtin::BI__builtin_constant_p)
15621  return CheckEvalInICE(E, Ctx);
15622  ICEDiag CondResult = CheckICE(Exp->getCond(), Ctx);
15623  if (CondResult.Kind == IK_NotICE)
15624  return CondResult;
15625 
15626  ICEDiag TrueResult = CheckICE(Exp->getTrueExpr(), Ctx);
15627  ICEDiag FalseResult = CheckICE(Exp->getFalseExpr(), Ctx);
15628 
15629  if (TrueResult.Kind == IK_NotICE)
15630  return TrueResult;
15631  if (FalseResult.Kind == IK_NotICE)
15632  return FalseResult;
15633  if (CondResult.Kind == IK_ICEIfUnevaluated)
15634  return CondResult;
15635  if (TrueResult.Kind == IK_ICE && FalseResult.Kind == IK_ICE)
15636  return NoDiag();
15637  // Rare case where the diagnostics depend on which side is evaluated
15638  // Note that if we get here, CondResult is 0, and at least one of
15639  // TrueResult and FalseResult is non-zero.
15640  if (Exp->getCond()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx) == 0)
15641  return FalseResult;
15642  return TrueResult;
15643  }
15644  case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass:
15645  return CheckICE(cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E)->getExpr(), Ctx);
15646  case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass:
15647  return CheckICE(cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E)->getExpr(), Ctx);
15648  case Expr::ChooseExprClass: {
15649  return CheckICE(cast<ChooseExpr>(E)->getChosenSubExpr(), Ctx);
15650  }
15651  case Expr::BuiltinBitCastExprClass: {
15652  if (!checkBitCastConstexprEligibility(nullptr, Ctx, cast<CastExpr>(E)))
15653  return ICEDiag(IK_NotICE, E->getBeginLoc());
15654  return CheckICE(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr(), Ctx);
15655  }
15656  }
15657 
15658  llvm_unreachable("Invalid StmtClass!");
15659 }
15660 
15661 /// Evaluate an expression as a C++11 integral constant expression.
15662 static bool EvaluateCPlusPlus11IntegralConstantExpr(const ASTContext &Ctx,
15663  const Expr *E,
15664  llvm::APSInt *Value,
15665  SourceLocation *Loc) {
15666  if (!E->getType()->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType()) {
15667  if (Loc) *Loc = E->getExprLoc();
15668  return false;
15669  }
15670 
15671  APValue Result;
15672  if (!E->isCXX11ConstantExpr(Ctx, &Result, Loc))
15673  return false;
15674 
15675  if (!Result.isInt()) {
15676  if (Loc) *Loc = E->getExprLoc();
15677  return false;
15678  }
15679 
15680  if (Value) *Value = Result.getInt();
15681  return true;
15682 }
15683 
15684 bool Expr::isIntegerConstantExpr(const ASTContext &Ctx,
15685  SourceLocation *Loc) const {
15686  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15687  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15688 
15689  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
15690  return EvaluateCPlusPlus11IntegralConstantExpr(Ctx, this, nullptr, Loc);
15691 
15692  ICEDiag D = CheckICE(this, Ctx);
15693  if (D.Kind != IK_ICE) {
15694  if (Loc) *Loc = D.Loc;
15695  return false;
15696  }
15697  return true;
15698 }
15699 
15700 Optional<llvm::APSInt> Expr::getIntegerConstantExpr(const ASTContext &Ctx,
15701  SourceLocation *Loc,
15702  bool isEvaluated) const {
15703  if (isValueDependent()) {
15704  // Expression evaluator can't succeed on a dependent expression.
15705  return None;
15706  }
15707 
15708  APSInt Value;
15709 
15710  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
15711  if (EvaluateCPlusPlus11IntegralConstantExpr(Ctx, this, &Value, Loc))
15712  return Value;
15713  return None;
15714  }
15715 
15716  if (!isIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx, Loc))
15717  return None;
15718 
15719  // The only possible side-effects here are due to UB discovered in the
15720  // evaluation (for instance, INT_MAX + 1). In such a case, we are still
15721  // required to treat the expression as an ICE, so we produce the folded
15722  // value.
15723  EvalResult ExprResult;
15724  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15725  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_IgnoreSideEffects);
15726  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15727 
15728  if (!::EvaluateAsInt(this, ExprResult, Ctx, SE_AllowSideEffects, Info))
15729  llvm_unreachable("ICE cannot be evaluated!");
15730 
15731  return ExprResult.Val.getInt();
15732 }
15733 
15734 bool Expr::isCXX98IntegralConstantExpr(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
15735  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15736  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15737 
15738  return CheckICE(this, Ctx).Kind == IK_ICE;
15739 }
15740 
15741 bool Expr::isCXX11ConstantExpr(const ASTContext &Ctx, APValue *Result,
15742  SourceLocation *Loc) const {
15743  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15744  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15745 
15746  // We support this checking in C++98 mode in order to diagnose compatibility
15747  // issues.
15748  assert(Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
15749 
15750  // Build evaluation settings.
15751  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15752  SmallVector<PartialDiagnosticAt, 8> Diags;
15753  Status.Diag = &Diags;
15754  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression);
15755 
15756  APValue Scratch;
15757  bool IsConstExpr =
15758  ::EvaluateAsRValue(Info, this, Result ? *Result : Scratch) &&
15759  // FIXME: We don't produce a diagnostic for this, but the callers that
15760  // call us on arbitrary full-expressions should generally not care.
15761  Info.discardCleanups() && !Status.HasSideEffects;
15762 
15763  if (!Diags.empty()) {
15764  IsConstExpr = false;
15765  if (Loc) *Loc = Diags[0].first;
15766  } else if (!IsConstExpr) {
15767  // FIXME: This shouldn't happen.
15768  if (Loc) *Loc = getExprLoc();
15769  }
15770 
15771  return IsConstExpr;
15772 }
15773 
15774 bool Expr::EvaluateWithSubstitution(APValue &Value, ASTContext &Ctx,
15775  const FunctionDecl *Callee,
15776  ArrayRef<const Expr*> Args,
15777  const Expr *This) const {
15778  assert(!isValueDependent() &&
15779  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15780 
15781  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15782  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpressionUnevaluated);
15783  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15784 
15785  LValue ThisVal;
15786  const LValue *ThisPtr = nullptr;
15787  if (This) {
15788 #ifndef NDEBUG
15789  auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Callee);
15790  assert(MD && "Don't provide `this` for non-methods.");
15791  assert(!MD->isStatic() && "Don't provide `this` for static methods.");
15792 #endif
15793  if (!This->isValueDependent() &&
15794  EvaluateObjectArgument(Info, This, ThisVal) &&
15795  !Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects)
15796  ThisPtr = &ThisVal;
15797 
15798  // Ignore any side-effects from a failed evaluation. This is safe because
15799  // they can't interfere with any other argument evaluation.
15800  Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects = false;
15801  }
15802 
15803  CallRef Call = Info.CurrentCall->createCall(Callee);
15804  for (ArrayRef<const Expr*>::iterator I = Args.begin(), E = Args.end();
15805  I != E; ++I) {
15806  unsigned Idx = I - Args.begin();
15807  if (Idx >= Callee->getNumParams())
15808  break;
15809  const ParmVarDecl *PVD = Callee->getParamDecl(Idx);
15810  if ((*I)->isValueDependent() ||
15811  !EvaluateCallArg(PVD, *I, Call, Info) ||
15812  Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects) {
15813  // If evaluation fails, throw away the argument entirely.
15814  if (APValue *Slot = Info.getParamSlot(Call, PVD))
15815  *Slot = APValue();
15816  }
15817 
15818  // Ignore any side-effects from a failed evaluation. This is safe because
15819  // they can't interfere with any other argument evaluation.
15820  Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects = false;
15821  }
15822 
15823  // Parameter cleanups happen in the caller and are not part of this
15824  // evaluation.
15825  Info.discardCleanups();
15826  Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects = false;
15827 
15828  // Build fake call to Callee.
15829  CallStackFrame Frame(Info, Callee->getLocation(), Callee, ThisPtr, Call);
15830  // FIXME: Missing ExprWithCleanups in enable_if conditions?
15831  FullExpressionRAII Scope(Info);
15832  return Evaluate(Value, Info, this) && Scope.destroy() &&
15833  !Info.EvalStatus.HasSideEffects;
15834 }
15835 
15836 bool Expr::isPotentialConstantExpr(const FunctionDecl *FD,
15837  SmallVectorImpl<
15838  PartialDiagnosticAt> &Diags) {
15839  // FIXME: It would be useful to check constexpr function templates, but at the
15840  // moment the constant expression evaluator cannot cope with the non-rigorous
15841  // ASTs which we build for dependent expressions.
15842  if (FD->isDependentContext())
15843  return true;
15844 
15845  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15846  Status.Diag = &Diags;
15847 
15848  EvalInfo Info(FD->getASTContext(), Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpression);
15849  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15850  Info.CheckingPotentialConstantExpression = true;
15851 
15852  // The constexpr VM attempts to compile all methods to bytecode here.
15853  if (Info.EnableNewConstInterp) {
15854  Info.Ctx.getInterpContext().isPotentialConstantExpr(Info, FD);
15855  return Diags.empty();
15856  }
15857 
15858  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD);
15859  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD ? MD->getParent()->getCanonicalDecl() : nullptr;
15860 
15861  // Fabricate an arbitrary expression on the stack and pretend that it
15862  // is a temporary being used as the 'this' pointer.
15863  LValue This;
15864  ImplicitValueInitExpr VIE(RD ? Info.Ctx.getRecordType(RD) : Info.Ctx.IntTy);
15865  This.set({&VIE, Info.CurrentCall->Index});
15866 
15867  ArrayRef<const Expr*> Args;
15868 
15869  APValue Scratch;
15870  if (const CXXConstructorDecl *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(FD)) {
15871  // Evaluate the call as a constant initializer, to allow the construction
15872  // of objects of non-literal types.
15873  Info.setEvaluatingDecl(This.getLValueBase(), Scratch);
15874  HandleConstructorCall(&VIE, This, Args, CD, Info, Scratch);
15875  } else {
15876  SourceLocation Loc = FD->getLocation();
15877  HandleFunctionCall(Loc, FD, (MD && MD->isInstance()) ? &This : nullptr,
15878  Args, CallRef(), FD->getBody(), Info, Scratch, nullptr);
15879  }
15880 
15881  return Diags.empty();
15882 }
15883 
15884 bool Expr::isPotentialConstantExprUnevaluated(Expr *E,
15885  const FunctionDecl *FD,
15886  SmallVectorImpl<
15887  PartialDiagnosticAt> &Diags) {
15888  assert(!E->isValueDependent() &&
15889  "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
15890 
15891  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15892  Status.Diag = &Diags;
15893 
15894  EvalInfo Info(FD->getASTContext(), Status,
15895  EvalInfo::EM_ConstantExpressionUnevaluated);
15896  Info.InConstantContext = true;
15897  Info.CheckingPotentialConstantExpression = true;
15898 
15899  // Fabricate a call stack frame to give the arguments a plausible cover story.
15900  CallStackFrame Frame(Info, SourceLocation(), FD, /*This*/ nullptr, CallRef());
15901 
15902  APValue ResultScratch;
15903  Evaluate(ResultScratch, Info, E);
15904  return Diags.empty();
15905 }
15906 
15907 bool Expr::tryEvaluateObjectSize(uint64_t &Result, ASTContext &Ctx,
15908  unsigned Type) const {
15909  if (!getType()->isPointerType())
15910  return false;
15911 
15912  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15913  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantFold);
15914  return tryEvaluateBuiltinObjectSize(this, Type, Info, Result);
15915 }
15916 
15917 static bool EvaluateBuiltinStrLen(const Expr *E, uint64_t &Result,
15918  EvalInfo &Info) {
15919  if (!E->getType()->hasPointerRepresentation() || !E->isPRValue())
15920  return false;
15921 
15922  LValue String;
15923 
15924  if (!EvaluatePointer(E, String, Info))
15925  return false;
15926 
15927  QualType CharTy = E->getType()->getPointeeType();
15928 
15929  // Fast path: if it's a string literal, search the string value.
15930  if (const StringLiteral *S = dyn_cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(
15931  String.getLValueBase().dyn_cast<const Expr *>())) {
15932  StringRef Str = S->getBytes();
15933  int64_t Off = String.Offset.getQuantity();
15934  if (Off >= 0 && (uint64_t)Off <= (uint64_t)Str.size() &&
15935  S->getCharByteWidth() == 1 &&
15936  // FIXME: Add fast-path for wchar_t too.
15937  Info.Ctx.hasSameUnqualifiedType(CharTy, Info.Ctx.CharTy)) {
15938  Str = Str.substr(Off);
15939 
15940  StringRef::size_type Pos = Str.find(0);
15941  if (Pos != StringRef::npos)
15942  Str = Str.substr(0, Pos);
15943 
15944  Result = Str.size();
15945  return true;
15946  }
15947 
15948  // Fall through to slow path.
15949  }
15950 
15951  // Slow path: scan the bytes of the string looking for the terminating 0.
15952  for (uint64_t Strlen = 0; /**/; ++Strlen) {
15953  APValue Char;
15954  if (!handleLValueToRValueConversion(Info, E, CharTy, String, Char) ||
15955  !Char.isInt())
15956  return false;
15957  if (!Char.getInt()) {
15958  Result = Strlen;
15959  return true;
15960  }
15961  if (!HandleLValueArrayAdjustment(Info, E, String, CharTy, 1))
15962  return false;
15963  }
15964 }
15965 
15966 bool Expr::tryEvaluateStrLen(uint64_t &Result, ASTContext &Ctx) const {
15967  Expr::EvalStatus Status;
15968  EvalInfo Info(Ctx, Status, EvalInfo::EM_ConstantFold);
15969  return EvaluateBuiltinStrLen(this, Result, Info);
15970 }
